19Ps 1:1 How happy is the man who does not follow the advice of the wicked, or take the path of sinners, or join a group of mockers!
19Ps 1:2 Instead, his delight is in the LORD's instruction, and he meditates on it day and night.
19Ps 1:3 He is like a tree planted beside streams of water that bears its fruit in season and whose leaf does not wither. Whatever he does prospers.
19Ps 1:4 The wicked are not like this; instead, they are like chaff that the wind blows away.
19Ps 1:5 Therefore the wicked will not survive the judgment, and sinners will not be in the community of the righteous.
19Ps 1:6 For the LORD watches over the way of the righteous, but the way of the wicked leads to ruin.
19Ps 2:1 Why do the nations rebel and the peoples plot in vain?
19Ps 2:2 The kings of the earth take their stand and the rulers conspire together against the LORD and His Anointed One:
19Ps 2:3 "Let us tear off their chains and free ourselves from their restraints."
19Ps 2:4 The One enthroned in heaven laughs; the Lord ridicules them.
19Ps 2:5 Then He speaks to them in His anger and terrifies them in His wrath:
19Ps 2:6 "I have consecrated My King on Zion, My holy mountain."
19Ps 2:7 I will declare the LORD's decree: He said to Me, "You are My Son; today I have become Your Father.
19Ps 2:8 Ask of Me, and I will make the nations Your inheritance and the ends of the earth Your possession.
19Ps 2:9 You will break them with a rod of iron; You will shatter them like pottery."
19Ps 2:10 So now, kings, be wise; receive instruction, you judges of the earth.
19Ps 2:11 Serve the LORD with reverential awe, and rejoice with trembling.
19Ps 2:12 Pay homage to the Son, or He will be angry, and you will perish in your rebellion, for His anger may ignite at any moment. All those who take refuge in Him are happy.
19Ps 3:1 [A psalm of David when he fled from his son Absalom.] LORD, how my foes increase! There are many who attack me.
19Ps 3:2 Many say about me, "There is no help for him in God." Selah
19Ps 3:3 But You, LORD, are a shield around me, my glory, and the One who lifts up my head.
19Ps 3:4 I cry aloud to the LORD, and He answers me from His holy mountain. Selah
19Ps 3:5 I lie down and sleep; I wake again because the LORD sustains me.
19Ps 3:6 I am not afraid of the thousands of people who have taken their stand against me on every side.
19Ps 3:7 Rise up, LORD! Save me, my God! You strike all my enemies on the cheek; You break the teeth of the wicked.
19Ps 3:8 Salvation belongs to the LORD; may Your blessing be on Your people. Selah
19Ps 4:1 [For the choir director: with stringed instruments. A Davidic psalm.] Answer me when I call, God, who vindicates me. You freed me from affliction; be gracious to me and hear my prayer.
19Ps 4:2 How long, exalted men, will my honor be insulted? [How long] will you love what is worthless and pursue a lie? Selah
19Ps 4:3 Know that the LORD has set apart the faithful for Himself; the LORD will hear when I call to Him.
19Ps 4:4 Be angry and do not sin; on your bed, reflect in your heart and be still. Selah
19Ps 4:5 Offer sacrifices in righteousness and trust in the LORD.
19Ps 4:6 Many are saying, "Who can show us anything good?" Look on us with favor, LORD.
19Ps 4:7 You have put more joy in my heart than they have when their grain and new wine abound.
19Ps 4:8 I will both lie down and sleep in peace, for You alone, LORD, make me live in safety.
19Ps 5:1 [For the choir director: with the flutes. A Davidic psalm.] Listen to my words, LORD; consider my sighing.
19Ps 5:2 Pay attention to the sound of my cry, my King and my God, for I pray to You.
19Ps 5:3 At daybreak, LORD, You hear my voice; at daybreak I plead my case to You and watch expectantly.
19Ps 5:4 For You are not a God who delights in wickedness; evil cannot lodge with You.
19Ps 5:5 The boastful cannot stand in Your presence; You hate all evildoers.
19Ps 5:6 You destroy those who tell lies; the LORD abhors a man of bloodshed and treachery.
19Ps 5:7 But I enter Your house by the abundance of Your faithful love; I bow down toward Your holy temple in reverential awe of You.
19Ps 5:8 LORD, lead me in Your righteousness, because of my adversaries; make Your way straight before me.
19Ps 5:9 For there is nothing reliable in what they say; destruction is within them; their throat is an open grave; they flatter with their tongues.
19Ps 5:10 Punish them, God; let them fall by their own schemes. Drive them out because of their many crimes, for they rebel against You.
19Ps 5:11 But let all who take refuge in You rejoice; let them shout for joy forever. May You shelter them, and may those who love Your name boast about You.
19Ps 5:12 For You, LORD, bless the righteous one; You surround him with favor like a shield.
19Ps 6:1 [For the choir director: with stringed instruments, according to Sheminith. A Davidic psalm.] LORD, do not rebuke me in Your anger; do not discipline me in Your wrath.
19Ps 6:2 Be gracious to me, LORD, for I am weak; heal me, LORD, for my bones are shaking;
19Ps 6:3 my whole being is shaken with terror. And You, Lord-- how long?
19Ps 6:4 Turn, LORD! Rescue me; save me because of Your faithful love.
19Ps 6:5 For there is no remembrance of You in death; who can thank You in Sheol?
19Ps 6:6 I am weary from my groaning; with my tears I dampen my pillow and drench my bed every night.
19Ps 6:7 My eyes are swollen from grief; they grow old because of all my enemies.
19Ps 6:8 Depart from me, all evildoers, for the LORD has heard the sound of my weeping.
19Ps 6:9 The LORD has heard my plea for help; the LORD accepts my prayer.
19Ps 6:10 All my enemies will be ashamed and shake with terror; they will turn back and suddenly be disgraced.
19Ps 7:1 [A Shiggaion of David, which he sang to the LORD concerning the words of Cush, a Benjaminite.] LORD my God, I seek refuge in You; save me from all my pursuers and rescue me,
19Ps 7:2 or they will tear me like a lion, ripping me apart, with no one to rescue me.
19Ps 7:3 LORD my God, if I have done this, if there is injustice on my hands,
19Ps 7:4 if I have done harm to one at peace with me or have plundered my adversary without cause,
19Ps 7:5 may an enemy pursue and overtake me; may he trample me to the ground and leave my honor in the dust. Selah
19Ps 7:6 Rise up, LORD, in Your anger; lift Yourself up against the fury of my adversaries; awake for me; You have ordained a judgment.
19Ps 7:7 Let the assembly of peoples gather around You; take Your seat on high over it.
19Ps 7:8 The LORD judges the peoples; vindicate me, LORD, according to my righteousness and my integrity.
19Ps 7:9 Let the evil of the wicked come to an end, but establish the righteous. The One who examines the thoughts and emotions is a righteous God.
19Ps 7:10 My shield is with God, who saves the upright in heart.
19Ps 7:11 God is a righteous judge, and a God who executes justice every day.
19Ps 7:12 If anyone does not repent, God will sharpen His sword; He has strung His bow and made it ready.
19Ps 7:13 He has prepared His deadly weapons; He tips His arrows with fire.
19Ps 7:14 See, he is pregnant with evil, conceives trouble, and gives birth to deceit.
19Ps 7:15 He dug a pit and hollowed it out, but fell into the hole he had made.
19Ps 7:16 His trouble comes back on his own head, and his violence falls on the top of his head.
19Ps 7:17 I will thank the LORD for His righteousness; I will sing about the name of the LORD, the Most High.
19Ps 8:1 [For the choir director: on the Gittith. A Davidic psalm.] LORD, our Lord, how magnificent is Your name throughout the earth! You have covered the heavens with Your majesty.
19Ps 8:2 Because of Your adversaries, You have established a stronghold from the mouths of children and nursing infants, to silence the enemy and the avenger.
19Ps 8:3 When I observe Your heavens, the work of Your fingers, the moon and the stars, which You set in place,
19Ps 8:4 what is man that You remember him, the son of man that You look after him?
19Ps 8:5 You made him little less than God and crowned him with glory and honor.
19Ps 8:6 You made him lord over the works of Your hands; You put everything under his feet:
19Ps 8:7 all the sheep and oxen, as well as animals in the wild,
19Ps 8:8 birds of the sky, and fish of the sea passing through the currents of the seas.
19Ps 8:9 LORD, our Lord, how magnificent is Your name throughout the earth!
19Ps 9:1 [For the choir director: according to Muth-labben. A Davidic psalm.] I will thank the LORD with all my heart; I will declare all Your wonderful works.
19Ps 9:2 I will rejoice and boast about You; I will sing about Your name, Most High.
19Ps 9:3 When my enemies retreat, they stumble and perish before You.
19Ps 9:4 For You have upheld my just cause; You are seated on Your throne as a righteous judge.
19Ps 9:5 You have rebuked the nations: You have destroyed the wicked; You have erased their name forever and ever.
19Ps 9:6 The enemy has come to eternal ruin; You have uprooted the cities, and the very memory of them has perished.
19Ps 9:7 But the LORD sits enthroned forever; He has established His throne for judgment.
19Ps 9:8 He judges the world with righteousness; He executes judgment on the peoples with fairness.
19Ps 9:9 The LORD is a refuge for the oppressed, a refuge in times of trouble.
19Ps 9:10 Those who know Your name trust in You because You have not abandoned those who seek You, LORD.
19Ps 9:11 Sing to the LORD, who dwells in Zion; proclaim His deeds among the peoples.
19Ps 9:12 For the One who seeks an accounting for bloodshed remembers them; He does not forget the cry of the afflicted.
19Ps 9:13 Be gracious to me, LORD; consider my affliction at the hands of those who hate me. Lift me up from the gates of death,
19Ps 9:14 so that I may declare all Your praises. I will rejoice in Your salvation within the gates of Daughter Zion.
19Ps 9:15 The nations have fallen into the pit they made; their foot is caught in the net they have concealed.
19Ps 9:16 The LORD has revealed Himself; He has executed justice, striking down the wicked by the work of their hands. Higgaion. Selah
19Ps 9:17 The wicked will return to Sheol-- all the nations that forget God.
19Ps 9:18 For the oppressed will not always be forgotten; the hope of the afflicted will not perish forever.
19Ps 9:19 Rise up, LORD! Do not let man prevail; let the nations be judged in Your presence.
19Ps 9:20 Put terror in them, LORD; let the nations know they are only men. Selah
19Ps 10:1 LORD, why do You stand so far away? Why do You hide in times of trouble?
19Ps 10:2 In arrogance the wicked relentlessly pursue the afflicted; let them be caught in the schemes they have devised.
19Ps 10:3 For the wicked one boasts about his own cravings; the one who is greedy curses and despises the LORD.
19Ps 10:4 In all his scheming, the wicked arrogantly thinks: "There is no accountability, [since] God does not exist."
19Ps 10:5 His ways are always secure; Your lofty judgments are beyond his sight; he scoffs at all his adversaries.
19Ps 10:6 He says to himself, "I will never be moved-- from generation to generation without calamity."
19Ps 10:7 Cursing, deceit, and violence fill his mouth; trouble and malice are under his tongue.
19Ps 10:8 He waits in ambush near the villages; he kills the innocent in secret places; his eyes are on the lookout for the helpless.
19Ps 10:9 He lurks in secret like a lion in a thicket. He lurks in order to seize the afflicted. He seizes the afflicted and drags him in his net.
19Ps 10:10 He crouches and bends down; the helpless fall because of his strength.
19Ps 10:11 He says to himself, "God has forgotten; He hides His face and will never see."
19Ps 10:12 Rise up, LORD God! Lift up Your hand. Do not forget the afflicted.
19Ps 10:13 Why has the wicked despised God? He says to himself, "You will not demand an account."
19Ps 10:14 But You Yourself have seen trouble and grief, observing it in order to take the matter into Your hands. The helpless entrusts himself to You; You are a helper of the fatherless.
19Ps 10:15 Break the arm of the wicked and evil person; call his wickedness into account until nothing remains of it.
19Ps 10:16 The LORD is King forever and ever; the nations will perish from His land.
19Ps 10:17 LORD, You have heard the desire of the humble; You will strengthen their hearts. You will listen carefully,
19Ps 10:18 doing justice for the fatherless and the oppressed, so that men of the earth may terrify [them] no more.
19Ps 11:1 [For the choir director. Davidic.] I have taken refuge in the LORD. How can you say to me, "Escape to the mountain like a bird!
19Ps 11:2 For look, the wicked string the bow; they put the arrow on the bowstring to shoot from the shadows at the upright in heart.
19Ps 11:3 When the foundations are destroyed, what can the righteous do?"
19Ps 11:4 The LORD is in His holy temple; the LORD's throne is in heaven. His eyes watch; He examines everyone.
19Ps 11:5 The LORD examines the righteous and the wicked. He hates the lover of violence.
19Ps 11:6 He will rain burning coals and sulfur on the wicked; a scorching wind will be their portion.
19Ps 11:7 For the LORD is righteous; He loves righteous deeds. The upright will see His face.
19Ps 12:1 [For the choir director: according to Sheminith. A Davidic psalm.] Help, LORD, for no faithful one remains; the loyal have disappeared from the human race.
19Ps 12:2 They lie to one another; they speak with flattering lips and deceptive hearts.
19Ps 12:3 May the LORD cut off all flattering lips and the tongue that speaks boastfully.
19Ps 12:4 They say, "Through our tongues we have power; our lips are our own-- who can be our master?"
19Ps 12:5 "Because of the oppression of the afflicted and the groaning of the poor, I will now rise up," says the LORD. "I will put in a safe place the one who longs for it."
19Ps 12:6 The words of the LORD are pure words, like silver refined in an earthen furnace, purified seven times.
19Ps 12:7 You, LORD, will guard us; You will protect us from this generation forever.
19Ps 12:8 The wicked wander everywhere, and what is worthless is exalted by the human race.
19Ps 13:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic psalm.] LORD, how long will You continually forget me? How long will You hide Your face from me?
19Ps 13:2 How long will I store up anxious concerns within me, agony in my mind every day? How long will my enemy dominate me?
19Ps 13:3 Consider me and answer, LORD, my God. Restore brightness to my eyes; otherwise, I will sleep in death,
19Ps 13:4 my enemy will say, "I have triumphed over him," and my foes will rejoice because I am shaken.
19Ps 13:5 But I have trusted in Your faithful love; my heart will rejoice in Your deliverance.
19Ps 13:6 I will sing to the LORD because He has treated me generously.
19Ps 14:1 [For the choir director. Davidic.] The fool says in his heart, "God does not exist." They are corrupt; their actions are revolting. There is no one who does good.
19Ps 14:2 The LORD looks down from heaven on the human race to see if there is one who is wise, one who seeks God.
19Ps 14:3 All have turned away; all alike have become corrupt. There is no one who does good, not even one.
19Ps 14:4 Will evildoers never understand? They consume my people as they consume bread; they do not call on the LORD.
19Ps 14:5 Then they will be filled with terror, for God is with those who are righteous.
19Ps 14:6 You [sinners] frustrate the plans of the afflicted, but the LORD is his refuge.
19Ps 14:7 Oh, that Israel's deliverance would come from Zion! When the LORD restores His captive people, Jacob will rejoice; Israel will be glad.
19Ps 15:1 [A Davidic psalm.] LORD, who can dwell in Your tent? Who can live on Your holy mountain?
19Ps 15:2 The one who lives honestly, practices righteousness, and acknowledges the truth in his heart--
19Ps 15:3 who does not slander with his tongue, who does not harm his friend or discredit his neighbor,
19Ps 15:4 who despises the one rejected by the LORD, but honors those who fear the LORD, who keeps his word whatever the cost,
19Ps 15:5 who does not lend his money at interest or take a bribe against the innocent-- the one who does these things will never be moved.
19Ps 16:1 [A Davidic Miktam.] Protect me, God, for I take refuge in You.
19Ps 16:2 I said to the LORD, "You are my Lord; I have no good besides You."
19Ps 16:3 As for the holy people who are in the land, they are the noble ones in whom is all my delight.
19Ps 16:4 The sorrows of those who take another [god] for themselves multiply; I will not pour out their drink offerings of blood, and I will not speak their names with my lips.
19Ps 16:5 LORD, You are my portion and my cup [of blessing]; You hold my future.
19Ps 16:6 The boundary lines have fallen for me in pleasant places; indeed, I have a beautiful inheritance.
19Ps 16:7 I will praise the LORD who counsels me-- even at night my conscience instructs me.
19Ps 16:8 I keep the LORD in mind always. Because He is at my right hand, I will not be shaken.
19Ps 16:9 Therefore my heart is glad, and my spirit rejoices; my body also rests securely.
19Ps 16:10 For You will not abandon me to Sheol; You will not allow Your Faithful One to see the Pit.
19Ps 16:11 You reveal the path of life to me; in Your presence is abundant joy; in Your right hand are eternal pleasures.
19Ps 17:1 [A Davidic prayer.] LORD, hear a just cause; pay attention to my cry; listen to my prayer-- from lips free of deceit.
19Ps 17:2 Let my vindication come from You, [for] You see what is right.
19Ps 17:3 You have tested my heart; You have visited by night; You have tried me and found nothing [evil]; I have determined that my mouth will not sin.
19Ps 17:4 Concerning what people do: by the word of Your lips I have avoided the ways of the violent.
19Ps 17:5 My steps are on Your paths; my feet have not slipped.
19Ps 17:6 I call on You, God, because You will answer me; listen closely to me; hear what I say.
19Ps 17:7 Display the wonders of Your faithful love, Savior of all who seek refuge from those who rebel against Your right hand.
19Ps 17:8 Guard me as the apple of Your eye; hide me in the shadow of Your wings
19Ps 17:9 from the wicked who treat me violently, my deadly enemies who surround me.
19Ps 17:10 They have become hardened; their mouths speak arrogantly.
19Ps 17:11 They advance against me; now they surround me. They are determined to throw [me] to the ground.
19Ps 17:12 They are like a lion eager to tear, like a young lion lurking in ambush.
19Ps 17:13 Rise up, LORD! Confront him; bring him down. With Your sword, save me from the wicked.
19Ps 17:14 With Your hand, LORD, [save me] from men, from men of the world, whose portion is in this life: You fill their bellies with what You have in store, their sons are satisfied, and they leave their surplus to their children.
19Ps 17:15 But I will see Your face in righteousness; when I awake, I will be satisfied with Your presence.
19Ps 18:1 [For the choir director. Of the servant of the LORD, David, who spoke the words of this song to the LORD on the day the LORD rescued him from the hand of all his enemies and from the hand of Saul. He said:] I love You, LORD, my strength.
19Ps 18:2 The LORD is my rock, my fortress, and my deliverer, my God, my mountain where I seek refuge, my shield and the horn of my salvation, my stronghold.
19Ps 18:3 I called to the LORD, who is worthy of praise, and I was saved from my enemies.
19Ps 18:4 The ropes of death were wrapped around me; the torrents of destruction terrified me.
19Ps 18:5 The ropes of Sheol entangled me; the snares of death confronted me.
19Ps 18:6 I called to the LORD in my distress, and I cried to my God for help. From His temple He heard my voice, and my cry to Him reached His ears.
19Ps 18:7 Then the earth shook and quaked; the foundations of the mountains trembled; they shook because He burned with anger.
19Ps 18:8 Smoke rose from His nostrils, and consuming fire [came] from His mouth; coals were set ablaze by it.
19Ps 18:9 He parted the heavens and came down, a dark cloud beneath His feet.
19Ps 18:10 He rode on a cherub and flew, soaring on the wings of the wind.
19Ps 18:11 He made darkness His hiding place, dark storm clouds His canopy around Him.
19Ps 18:12 From the radiance of His presence, His clouds swept onward with hail and blazing coals.
19Ps 18:13 The LORD thundered from heaven; the Most High projected His voice.
19Ps 18:14 He shot His arrows and scattered them; He hurled lightning bolts and routed them.
19Ps 18:15 The depths of the sea became visible, the foundations of the world were exposed, at Your rebuke, LORD, at the blast of the breath of Your nostrils.
19Ps 18:16 He reached down from on high and took hold of me; He pulled me out of deep waters.
19Ps 18:17 He rescued me from my powerful enemy and from those who hated me, for they were too strong for me.
19Ps 18:18 They confronted me in the day of my distress, but the LORD was my support.
19Ps 18:19 He brought me out to a wide-open place; He rescued me because He delighted in me.
19Ps 18:20 The LORD rewarded me according to my righteousness; He repaid me according to the cleanness of my hands.
19Ps 18:21 For I have kept the ways of the LORD and have not turned from my God to wickedness.
19Ps 18:22 Indeed, I have kept all His ordinances in mind and have not disregarded His statutes.
19Ps 18:23 I was blameless toward Him and kept myself from sinning.
19Ps 18:24 So the LORD repaid me according to my righteousness, according to the cleanness of my hands in His sight.
19Ps 18:25 With the faithful You prove Yourself faithful; with the blameless man You prove Yourself blameless;
19Ps 18:26 with the pure You prove Yourself pure, but with the crooked You prove Yourself shrewd.
19Ps 18:27 For You rescue an afflicted people, but You humble those with haughty eyes.
19Ps 18:28 LORD, You light my lamp; my God illuminates my darkness.
19Ps 18:29 With You I can attack a barrier, and with my God I can leap over a wall.
19Ps 18:30 God-- His way is perfect; the word of the LORD is pure. He is a shield to all who take refuge in Him.
19Ps 18:31 For who is God besides the LORD? And who is a rock? Only our God.
19Ps 18:32 God-- He clothes me with strength and makes my way perfect.
19Ps 18:33 He makes my feet like the feet of a deer and sets me securely on the heights.
19Ps 18:34 He trains my hands for war; my arms can bend a bow of bronze.
19Ps 18:35 You have given me the shield of Your salvation; Your right hand upholds me, and Your humility exalts me.
19Ps 18:36 You widen [a place] beneath me for my steps, and my ankles do not give way.
19Ps 18:37 I pursue my enemies and overtake them; I do not turn back until they are wiped out.
19Ps 18:38 I crush them, and they cannot get up; they fall beneath my feet.
19Ps 18:39 You have clothed me with strength for battle; You subdue my adversaries beneath me.
19Ps 18:40 You have made my enemies retreat before me; I annihilate those who hate me.
19Ps 18:41 They cry for help, but there is no one to save [them]-- [they cry] to the LORD, but He does not answer them.
19Ps 18:42 I pulverize them like dust before the wind; I trample them like mud in the streets.
19Ps 18:43 You have freed me from the feuds among the people; You have appointed me the head of nations; a people I had not known serve me.
19Ps 18:44 Foreigners submit to me grudgingly; as soon as they hear, they obey me.
19Ps 18:45 Foreigners lose heart and come trembling from their fortifications.
19Ps 18:46 The LORD lives-- may my rock be praised! The God of my salvation is exalted.
19Ps 18:47 God-- He gives me vengeance and subdues peoples under me.
19Ps 18:48 He frees me from my enemies. You exalt me above my adversaries; You rescue me from violent men.
19Ps 18:49 Therefore I will praise You, LORD, among the nations; I will sing about Your name.
19Ps 18:50 He gives great victories to His king; He shows loyalty to His anointed, to David and his descendants forever.
19Ps 19:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic psalm.] The heavens declare the glory of God, and the sky proclaims the work of His hands.
19Ps 19:2 Day after day they pour out speech; night after night they communicate knowledge.
19Ps 19:3 There is no speech; there are no words; their voice is not heard.
19Ps 19:4 Their message has gone out to all the earth, and their words to the ends of the inhabited world. In the heavens He has pitched a tent for the sun.
19Ps 19:5 It is like a groom coming from the bridal chamber; it rejoices like an athlete running a course.
19Ps 19:6 It rises from one end of the heavens and circles to their other end; nothing is hidden from its heat.
19Ps 19:7 The instruction of the LORD is perfect, reviving the soul; the testimony of the LORD is trustworthy, making the inexperienced wise.
19Ps 19:8 The precepts of the LORD are right, making the heart glad; the commandment of the LORD is radiant, making the eyes light up.
19Ps 19:9 The fear of the LORD is pure, enduring forever; the ordinances of the LORD are reliable and altogether righteous.
19Ps 19:10 They are more desirable than gold-- than an abundance of pure gold; and sweeter than honey-- than honey dripping from the comb.
19Ps 19:11 In addition, Your servant is warned by them; there is great reward in keeping them.
19Ps 19:12 Who perceives his unintentional sins? Cleanse me from my hidden faults.
19Ps 19:13 Moreover, keep Your servant from willful sins; do not let them rule over me. Then I will be innocent, and cleansed from blatant rebellion.
19Ps 19:14 May the words of my mouth and the meditation of my heart be acceptable to You, LORD, my rock and my Redeemer.
19Ps 20:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic psalm.] May the LORD answer you in a day of trouble; may the name of Jacob's God protect you.
19Ps 20:2 May He send you help from the sanctuary and sustain you from Zion.
19Ps 20:3 May He remember all your offerings and accept your burnt offering. Selah
19Ps 20:4 May He give you what your heart desires and fulfill your whole purpose.
19Ps 20:5 Let us shout for joy at your victory and lift the banner in the name of our God. May the LORD fulfill all your requests.
19Ps 20:6 Now I know that the LORD gives victory to His anointed; He will answer him from His holy heaven with mighty victories from His right hand.
19Ps 20:7 Some take pride in a chariot, and others in horses, but we take pride in the name of the LORD our God.
19Ps 20:8 They collapse and fall, but we rise and stand firm.
19Ps 20:9 LORD, give victory to the king! May He answer us on the day that we call.
19Ps 21:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic psalm.] LORD, the king finds joy in Your strength. How greatly he rejoices in Your victory!
19Ps 21:2 You have given him his heart's desire and have not denied the request of his lips. Selah
19Ps 21:3 For You meet him with rich blessings; You place a crown of pure gold on his head.
19Ps 21:4 He asked You for life, and You gave it to him-- length of days forever and ever.
19Ps 21:5 His glory is great through Your victory; You confer majesty and splendor on him.
19Ps 21:6 You give him blessings forever; You cheer him with joy in Your presence.
19Ps 21:7 For the king relies on the LORD; through the faithful love of the Most High he is not shaken.
19Ps 21:8 Your hand will capture all your enemies; your right hand will seize those who hate you.
19Ps 21:9 You will make them [burn] like a fiery furnace when you appear; the LORD will engulf them in His wrath, and fire will devour them.
19Ps 21:10 You will wipe their descendants from the earth and their offspring from the human race.
19Ps 21:11 Though they intend to harm you and devise a wicked plan, they will not prevail.
19Ps 21:12 Instead, you will put them to flight when you aim your bow at their faces.
19Ps 21:13 Be exalted, LORD, in Your strength; we will sing and praise Your might.
19Ps 22:1 [For the choir director: according to "The Deer of the Dawn." A Davidic psalm.] My God, my God, why have You forsaken me? [Why are You] so far from my deliverance and from my words of groaning?
19Ps 22:2 My God, I cry by day, but You do not answer, by night, yet I have no rest.
19Ps 22:3 But You are holy, enthroned on the praises of Israel.
19Ps 22:4 Our fathers trusted in You; they trusted, and You rescued them.
19Ps 22:5 They cried to You and were set free; they trusted in You and were not disgraced.
19Ps 22:6 But I am a worm and not a man, scorned by men and despised by people.
19Ps 22:7 Everyone who sees me mocks me; they sneer and shake their heads:
19Ps 22:8 "He relies on the LORD; let Him rescue him; let the LORD deliver him, since He takes pleasure in him."
19Ps 22:9 You took me from the womb, making me secure while at my mother's breast.
19Ps 22:10 I was given over to You at birth; You have been my God from my mother's womb.
19Ps 22:11 Do not be far from me, because distress is near and there is no one to help.
19Ps 22:12 Many bulls surround me; strong ones of Bashan encircle me.
19Ps 22:13 They open their mouths against me-- lions, mauling and roaring.
19Ps 22:14 I am poured out like water, and all my bones are disjointed; my heart is like wax, melting within me.
19Ps 22:15 My strength is dried up like baked clay; my tongue sticks to the roof of my mouth. You put me into the dust of death.
19Ps 22:16 For dogs have surrounded me; a gang of evildoers has closed in on me; they pierced my hands and my feet.
19Ps 22:17 I can count all my bones; people look and stare at me.
19Ps 22:18 They divided my garments among themselves, and they cast lots for my clothing.
19Ps 22:19 But You, LORD, don't be far away. My strength, come quickly to help me.
19Ps 22:20 Deliver my life from the sword, my very life from the power of the dog.
19Ps 22:21 Save me from the mouth of the lion! You have rescued me from the horns of the wild oxen.
19Ps 22:22 I will proclaim Your name to my brothers; I will praise You in the congregation.
19Ps 22:23 You who fear the LORD, praise Him! All you descendants of Jacob, honor Him! All you descendants of Israel, revere Him!
19Ps 22:24 For He has not despised or detested the torment of the afflicted. He did not hide His face from him, but listened when he cried to Him for help.
19Ps 22:25 I will give praise in the great congregation because of You; I will fulfill my vows before those who fear You.
19Ps 22:26 The humble will eat and be satisfied; those who seek the LORD will praise Him. May your hearts live forever!
19Ps 22:27 All the ends of the earth will remember and turn to the LORD. All the families of the nations will bow down before You,
19Ps 22:28 for kingship belongs to the LORD; He rules over the nations.
19Ps 22:29 All who prosper on earth will eat and bow down; all those who go down to the dust will kneel before Him-- even the one who cannot preserve his life.
19Ps 22:30 Descendants will serve Him; the next generation will be told about the Lord.
19Ps 22:31 They will come and tell a people yet to be born about His righteousness-- what He has done.
19Ps 23:1 [A Davidic psalm.] The LORD is my shepherd; there is nothing I lack.
19Ps 23:2 He lets me lie down in green pastures; He leads me beside quiet waters.
19Ps 23:3 He renews my life; He leads me along the right paths for His name's sake.
19Ps 23:4 Even when I go through the darkest valley, I fear [no] danger, for You are with me; Your rod and Your staff-- they comfort me.
19Ps 23:5 You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies; You anoint my head with oil; my cup overflows.
19Ps 23:6 Only goodness and faithful love will pursue me all the days of my life, and I will dwell in the house of the LORD as long as I live.
19Ps 24:1 [A Davidic psalm.] The earth and everything in it, the world and its inhabitants, belong to the LORD;
19Ps 24:2 for He laid its foundation on the seas and established it on the rivers.
19Ps 24:3 Who may ascend the mountain of the LORD? Who may stand in His holy place?
19Ps 24:4 The one who has clean hands and a pure heart, who has not set his mind on what is false, and who has not sworn deceitfully.
19Ps 24:5 He will receive blessing from the LORD, and righteousness from the God of his salvation.
19Ps 24:6 Such is the generation of those who seek Him, who seek the face of the God of Jacob. Selah
19Ps 24:7 Lift up your heads, you gates! Rise up, ancient doors! Then the King of glory will come in.
19Ps 24:8 Who is this King of glory? The Lord, strong and mighty, the Lord, mighty in battle.
19Ps 24:9 Lift up your heads, you gates! Rise up, ancient doors! Then the King of glory will come in.
19Ps 24:10 Who is He, this King of glory? The LORD of Hosts, He is the King of glory. Selah
19Ps 25:1 [Davidic.] LORD, I turn my hope to You.
19Ps 25:2 My God, I trust in You. Do not let me be disgraced; do not let my enemies gloat over me.
19Ps 25:3 Not one person who waits for You will be disgraced; those who act treacherously without cause will be disgraced.
19Ps 25:4 Make Your ways known to me, LORD; teach me Your paths.
19Ps 25:5 Guide me in Your truth and teach me, for You are the God of my salvation; I wait for You all day long.
19Ps 25:6 Remember, LORD, Your compassion and Your faithful love, for they [have existed] from antiquity.
19Ps 25:7 Do not remember the sins of my youth or my acts of rebellion; in keeping with Your faithful love, remember me because of Your goodness, LORD.
19Ps 25:8 The LORD is good and upright; therefore He shows sinners the way.
19Ps 25:9 He leads the humble in what is right and teaches them His way.
19Ps 25:10 All the LORD's ways [show] faithful love and truth to those who keep His covenant and decrees.
19Ps 25:11 Because of Your name, LORD, forgive my sin, for it is great.
19Ps 25:12 Who is the person who fears the LORD? He will show him the way he should choose.
19Ps 25:13 He will live a good life, and his descendants will inherit the land.
19Ps 25:14 The secret counsel of the LORD is for those who fear Him, and He reveals His covenant to them.
19Ps 25:15 My eyes are always on the LORD, for He will pull my feet out of the net.
19Ps 25:16 Turn to me and be gracious to me, for I am alone and afflicted.
19Ps 25:17 The distresses of my heart increase; bring me out of my sufferings.
19Ps 25:18 Consider my affliction and trouble, and take away all my sins.
19Ps 25:19 Consider my enemies; they are numerous, and they hate me violently.
19Ps 25:20 Guard me and deliver me; do not let me be put to shame, for I take refuge in You.
19Ps 25:21 May integrity and uprightness keep me, for I wait for You.
19Ps 25:22 God, Redeem Israel, from all its distresses.
19Ps 26:1 [Davidic.] Vindicate me, LORD, because I have lived with integrity and have trusted in the LORD without wavering.
19Ps 26:2 Test me, LORD, and try me; examine my heart and mind.
19Ps 26:3 For Your faithful love is before my eyes, and I live by Your truth.
19Ps 26:4 I do not sit with the worthless or associate with hypocrites.
19Ps 26:5 I hate a crowd of evildoers, and I do not sit with the wicked.
19Ps 26:6 I wash my hands in innocence and go around Your altar, LORD,
19Ps 26:7 raising my voice in thanksgiving and telling about Your wonderful works.
19Ps 26:8 LORD, I love the house where You dwell, the place where Your glory resides.
19Ps 26:9 Do not destroy me along with sinners, or my life along with men of bloodshed
19Ps 26:10 in whose hands are evil schemes, and whose right hands are filled with bribes.
19Ps 26:11 But I live with integrity; redeem me and be gracious to me.
19Ps 26:12 My foot stands on level ground; I will praise the LORD in the assemblies.
19Ps 27:1 [Davidic.] The LORD is my light and my salvation-- whom should I fear? The LORD is the stronghold of my life-- of whom should I be afraid?
19Ps 27:2 When evildoers came against me to devour my flesh, my foes and my enemies stumbled and fell.
19Ps 27:3 Though an army deploy against me, my heart is not afraid; though war break out against me, still I am confident.
19Ps 27:4 I have asked one thing from the LORD; it is what I desire: to dwell in the house of the LORD all the days of my life, gazing on the beauty of the LORD and seeking [Him] in His temple.
19Ps 27:5 For He will conceal me in His shelter in the day of adversity; He will hide me under the cover of His tent; He will set me high on a rock.
19Ps 27:6 Then my head will be high above my enemies around me; I will offer sacrifices in His tent with shouts of joy. I will sing and make music to the LORD.
19Ps 27:7 LORD, hear my voice when I call; be gracious to me and answer me.
19Ps 27:8 In Your behalf my heart says, "Seek My face." LORD, I will seek Your face.
19Ps 27:9 Do not hide Your face from me; do not turn Your servant away in anger. You have been my help; do not leave me or abandon me, God of my salvation.
19Ps 27:10 Even if my father and mother abandon me, the LORD cares for me.
19Ps 27:11 Because of my adversaries, show me Your way, LORD, and lead me on a level path.
19Ps 27:12 Do not give me over to the will of my foes, for false witnesses rise up against me, breathing violence.
19Ps 27:13 I am certain that I will see the LORD's goodness in the land of the living.
19Ps 27:14 Wait for the LORD; be courageous and let your heart be strong. Wait for the LORD.
19Ps 28:1 [Davidic.] LORD, I call to You; my rock, do not be deaf to me. If You remain silent to me, I will be like those going down to the Pit.
19Ps 28:2 Listen to the sound of my pleading when I cry to You for help, when I lift up my hands toward Your holy sanctuary.
19Ps 28:3 Do not drag me away with the wicked, with the evildoers, who speak in friendly ways with their neighbors, while malice is in their hearts.
19Ps 28:4 Repay them according to what they have done-- according to the evil of their deeds. Repay them according to the work of their hands; give them back what they deserve.
19Ps 28:5 Because they do not consider what the LORD has done or the work of His hands, He will tear them down and not rebuild them.
19Ps 28:6 May the LORD be praised, for He has heard the sound of my pleading.
19Ps 28:7 The LORD is my strength and my shield; my heart trusts in Him, and I am helped. Therefore my heart rejoices, and I praise Him with my song.
19Ps 28:8 The LORD is the strength of His people; He is a stronghold of salvation for His anointed.
19Ps 28:9 Save Your people, bless Your possession, shepherd them, and carry them forever.
19Ps 29:1 [A Davidic psalm.] Give the Lord-- you heavenly beings-- give the LORD glory and strength.
19Ps 29:2 Give the LORD the glory due His name; worship the LORD in the splendor of [His] holiness.
19Ps 29:3 The voice of the LORD is above the waters. The God of glory thunders-- the LORD, above vast waters,
19Ps 29:4 the voice of the LORD in power, the voice of the LORD in splendor.
19Ps 29:5 The voice of the LORD breaks the cedars; the LORD shatters the cedars of Lebanon.
19Ps 29:6 He makes Lebanon skip like a calf, and Sirion, like a young wild ox.
19Ps 29:7 The voice of the LORD flashes flames of fire.
19Ps 29:8 The voice of the LORD shakes the wilderness; the LORD shakes the wilderness of Kadesh.
19Ps 29:9 The voice of the LORD makes the deer give birth and strips the woodlands bare. In His temple all cry, "Glory!"
19Ps 29:10 The LORD sat enthroned at the flood; the LORD sits enthroned, King forever.
19Ps 29:11 The LORD gives His people strength; the LORD blesses His people with peace.
19Ps 30:1 [A psalm; a dedication song for the house. Davidic.] I will exalt You, LORD, because You have lifted me up and have not allowed my enemies to triumph over me.
19Ps 30:2 LORD my God, I cried to You for help, and You healed me.
19Ps 30:3 LORD, You brought me up from Sheol; You spared me from among those going down to the Pit.
19Ps 30:4 Sing to the LORD, you His faithful ones, and praise His holy name.
19Ps 30:5 For His anger lasts only a moment, but His favor, a lifetime. Weeping may spend the night, but there is joy in the morning.
19Ps 30:6 When I was secure, I said, "I will never be shaken."
19Ps 30:7 LORD, when You showed Your favor, You made me stand like a strong mountain; when You hid Your face, I was terrified.
19Ps 30:8 LORD, I called to You; I sought favor from my Lord:
19Ps 30:9 "What gain is there in my death, in my descending to the Pit? Will the dust praise You? Will it proclaim Your truth?
19Ps 30:10 LORD, listen and be gracious to me; LORD, be my helper."
19Ps 30:11 You turned my lament into dancing; You removed my sackcloth and clothed me with gladness,
19Ps 30:12 so that I can sing to You and not be silent. LORD my God, I will praise You forever.
19Ps 31:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic psalm.] LORD, I seek refuge in You; let me never be disgraced. Save me by Your righteousness.
19Ps 31:2 Listen closely to me; rescue me quickly. Be a rock of refuge for me, a mountain fortress to save me.
19Ps 31:3 For You are my rock and my fortress; You lead and guide me because of Your name.
19Ps 31:4 You will free me from the net that is secretly set for me, for You are my refuge.
19Ps 31:5 Into Your hand I entrust my spirit; You redeem me, LORD, God of truth.
19Ps 31:6 I hate those who are devoted to worthless idols, but I trust in the LORD.
19Ps 31:7 I will rejoice and be glad in Your faithful love because You have seen my affliction. You have known the troubles of my life
19Ps 31:8 and have not handed me over to the enemy. You have set my feet in a spacious place.
19Ps 31:9 Be gracious to me, LORD, because I am in distress; my eyes are worn out from angry sorrow-- my whole being as well.
19Ps 31:10 Indeed, my life is consumed with grief, and my years with groaning; my strength has failed because of my sinfulness, and my bones waste away.
19Ps 31:11 I am ridiculed by all my adversaries and even by my neighbors. I am an object of dread to my acquaintances; those who see me in the street run from me.
19Ps 31:12 I am forgotten: gone from memory like a dead person-- like broken pottery.
19Ps 31:13 I have heard the gossip of many; terror is on every side. When they conspired against me, they plotted to take my life.
19Ps 31:14 But I trust in You, LORD; I say, "You are my God."
19Ps 31:15 The course of my life is in Your power; deliver me from the power of my enemies and from my persecutors.
19Ps 31:16 Show Your favor to Your servant; save me by Your faithful love.
19Ps 31:17 LORD, do not let me be disgraced when I call on You. Let the wicked be disgraced; let them be silent in Sheol.
19Ps 31:18 Let lying lips be quieted; they speak arrogantly against the righteous with pride and contempt.
19Ps 31:19 How great is Your goodness that You have stored up for those who fear You, and accomplished in the sight of everyone for those who take refuge in You.
19Ps 31:20 You hide them in the protection of Your presence; You conceal them in a shelter from the schemes of men, from quarrelsome tongues.
19Ps 31:21 May the LORD be praised, for He has wonderfully shown His faithful love to me in a city under siege.
19Ps 31:22 In my alarm I had said, "I am cut off from Your sight." But You heard the sound of my pleading when I cried to You for help.
19Ps 31:23 Love the LORD, all His faithful ones. The LORD protects the loyal, but fully repays the arrogant.
19Ps 31:24 Be strong and courageous, all you who put your hope in the LORD.
19Ps 32:1 [Davidic. A Maskil.] How happy is the one whose transgression is forgiven, whose sin is covered!
19Ps 32:2 How happy is the man the LORD does not charge with sin, and in whose spirit is no deceit!
19Ps 32:3 When I kept silent, my bones became brittle from my groaning all day long.
19Ps 32:4 For day and night Your hand was heavy on me; my strength was drained as in the summer's heat. Selah
19Ps 32:5 Then I acknowledged my sin to You and did not conceal my iniquity. I said, "I will confess my transgressions to the LORD," and You took away the guilt of my sin. Selah
19Ps 32:6 Therefore let everyone who is faithful pray to You at a time that You may be found. When great floodwaters come, they will not reach him.
19Ps 32:7 You are my hiding place; You protect me from trouble. You surround me with joyful shouts of deliverance. Selah
19Ps 32:8 I will instruct you and show you the way to go; with My eye on you, I will give counsel.
19Ps 32:9 Do not be like a horse or mule, without understanding, that must be controlled with bit and bridle, or else it will not come near you.
19Ps 32:10 Many pains come to the wicked, but the one who trusts in the LORD will have faithful love surrounding him.
19Ps 32:11 Be glad in the LORD and rejoice, you righteous ones; shout for joy, all you upright in heart.
19Ps 33:1 Rejoice in the LORD, you righteous ones; praise from the upright is beautiful.
19Ps 33:2 Praise the LORD with the lyre; make music to Him with a ten-stringed harp.
19Ps 33:3 Sing a new song to Him; play skillfully on the strings, with a joyful shout.
19Ps 33:4 For the word of the LORD is right, and all His work is trustworthy.
19Ps 33:5 He loves righteousness and justice; the earth is full of the LORD's unfailing love.
19Ps 33:6 The heavens were made by the word of the LORD, and all the stars, by the breath of His mouth.
19Ps 33:7 He gathers the waters of the sea into a heap; He puts the depths into storehouses.
19Ps 33:8 Let the whole earth tremble before the LORD; let all the inhabitants of the world stand in awe of Him.
19Ps 33:9 For He spoke, and it came into being; He commanded, and it came into existence.
19Ps 33:10 The LORD frustrates the counsel of the nations; He thwarts the plans of the peoples.
19Ps 33:11 The counsel of the LORD stands forever, the plans of His heart from generation to generation.
19Ps 33:12 Happy is the nation whose God is the Lord-- the people He has chosen to be His own possession!
19Ps 33:13 The LORD looks down from heaven; He observes everyone.
19Ps 33:14 He gazes on all the inhabitants of the earth from His dwelling place.
19Ps 33:15 He alone crafts their hearts; He considers all their works.
19Ps 33:16 A king is not saved by a large army; a warrior will not be delivered by great strength.
19Ps 33:17 The horse is a false hope for safety; it provides no escape by its great power.
19Ps 33:18 Now the eye of the LORD is on those who fear Him-- those who depend on His faithful love
19Ps 33:19 to deliver them from death and to keep them alive in famine.
19Ps 33:20 We wait for the LORD; He is our help and shield.
19Ps 33:21 For our hearts rejoice in Him, because we trust in His holy name.
19Ps 33:22 May Your faithful love rest on us, LORD, for we put our hope in You.
19Ps 34:1 [Concerning David, when he pretended to be insane in the presence of Abimelech, who drove him out, and he departed.] I will praise the LORD at all times; His praise will always be on my lips.
19Ps 34:2 I will boast in the LORD; the humble will hear and be glad.
19Ps 34:3 Proclaim with me the LORD's greatness; let us exalt His name together.
19Ps 34:4 I sought the LORD, and He answered me and delivered me from all my fears.
19Ps 34:5 Those who look to Him are radiant with joy; their faces will never be ashamed.
19Ps 34:6 This poor man cried, and the LORD heard [him] and saved him from all his troubles.
19Ps 34:7 The angel of the LORD encamps around those who fear Him, and rescues them.
19Ps 34:8 Taste and see that the LORD is good. How happy is the man who takes refuge in Him!
19Ps 34:9 Fear the LORD, you His saints, for those who fear Him lack nothing.
19Ps 34:10 Young lions lack food and go hungry, but those who seek the LORD will not lack any good thing.
19Ps 34:11 Come, children, listen to me; I will teach you the fear of the LORD.
19Ps 34:12 Who is the man who delights in life, loving a long life to enjoy what is good?
19Ps 34:13 Keep your tongue from evil and your lips from deceitful speech.
19Ps 34:14 Turn away from evil and do what is good; seek peace and pursue it.
19Ps 34:15 The eyes of the LORD are on the righteous, and His ears are open to their cry for help.
19Ps 34:16 The face of the LORD is set against those who do what is evil, to erase all memory of them from the earth.
19Ps 34:17 The righteous cry out, and the LORD hears, and delivers them from all their troubles.
19Ps 34:18 The LORD is near the brokenhearted; He saves those crushed in spirit.
19Ps 34:19 Many adversities come to the one who is righteous, but the LORD delivers him from them all.
19Ps 34:20 He protects all his bones; not one of them is broken.
19Ps 34:21 Evil brings death to the sinner, and those who hate the righteous will be punished.
19Ps 34:22 The LORD redeems the life of His servants, and all who take refuge in Him will not be punished.
19Ps 35:1 [Davidic.] Oppose my opponents, LORD; fight those who fight me.
19Ps 35:2 Take Your shields-- large and small-- and come to my aid.
19Ps 35:3 Draw the spear and javelin against my pursuers, and assure me: "I am your deliverance."
19Ps 35:4 Let those who seek to kill me be disgraced and humiliated; let those who plan to harm me be turned back and ashamed.
19Ps 35:5 Let them be like husks in the wind, with the angel of the LORD driving them away.
19Ps 35:6 Let their way be dark and slippery, with the angel of the LORD pursuing them.
19Ps 35:7 They hid their net for me without cause; they dug a pit for me without cause.
19Ps 35:8 Let ruin come on him unexpectedly, and let the net that he hid ensnare him; let him fall into it-- to his ruin.
19Ps 35:9 Then I will rejoice in the LORD; I will delight in His deliverance.
19Ps 35:10 My very bones will say, "LORD, who is like You, rescuing the poor from one too strong for him, the poor or the needy from one who robs him?"
19Ps 35:11 Malicious witnesses come forward; they question me about things I do not know.
19Ps 35:12 They repay me evil for good, making me desolate.
19Ps 35:13 Yet when they were sick, my clothing was sackcloth; I humbled myself with fasting, and my prayer was genuine.
19Ps 35:14 I went about [grieving] as if for my friend or brother; I was bowed down with grief, like one mourning a mother.
19Ps 35:15 But when I stumbled, they gathered in glee; they gathered against me. Assailants I did not know tore at me and did not stop.
19Ps 35:16 With godless mockery they gnashed their teeth at me.
19Ps 35:17 Lord, how long will You look on? Rescue my life from their ravages, my very life from the young lions.
19Ps 35:18 I will praise You in the great congregation; I will exalt You among many people.
19Ps 35:19 Do not let my deceitful enemies rejoice over me; do not let those who hate me without cause look at me maliciously.
19Ps 35:20 For they do not speak in friendly ways, but contrive deceitful schemes against those who live peacefully in the land.
19Ps 35:21 They open their mouths wide against me and say, "Aha, aha! We saw it!"
19Ps 35:22 You saw it, LORD; do not be silent. Lord, do not be far from me.
19Ps 35:23 Wake up and rise to my defense, to my cause, my God and my LORD!
19Ps 35:24 Vindicate me, LORD, my God, in keeping with Your righteousness, and do not let them rejoice over me.
19Ps 35:25 Do not let them say in their hearts, "Aha! Just what we wanted." Do not let them say, "We have swallowed him up!"
19Ps 35:26 Let those who rejoice at my misfortune be disgraced and humiliated; let those who exalt themselves over me be clothed with shame and reproach.
19Ps 35:27 Let those who want my vindication shout for joy and be glad; let them continually say, "The LORD be exalted, who wants His servant's well-being."
19Ps 35:28 And my tongue will proclaim Your righteousness, Your praise all day long.
19Ps 36:1 [For the choir director. [A psalm] of David, the LORD's servant.] An oracle within my heart concerning the transgression of the wicked: There is no dread of God before his eyes,
19Ps 36:2 for in his own eyes he flatters himself [too much] to discover and hate his sin.
19Ps 36:3 The words of his mouth are malicious and deceptive; he has stopped acting wisely and doing good.
19Ps 36:4 Even on his bed he makes malicious plans. He sets himself on a path that is not good and does not reject evil.
19Ps 36:5 LORD, Your faithful love [reaches] to heaven, Your faithfulness to the skies.
19Ps 36:6 Your righteousness is like the highest mountain; Your judgments, like the deepest sea. LORD, You preserve man and beast.
19Ps 36:7 God, Your faithful love is so valuable that people take refuge in the shadow of Your wings.
19Ps 36:8 They are filled from the abundance of Your house; You let them drink from Your refreshing stream,
19Ps 36:9 for with You is life's fountain. In Your light we will see light.
19Ps 36:10 Spread Your faithful love over those who know You, and Your righteousness over the upright in heart.
19Ps 36:11 Do not let the foot of the arrogant come near me or the hand of the wicked drive me away.
19Ps 36:12 There the evildoers fall; they have been thrown down and cannot rise.
19Ps 37:1 [Davidic.] Do not be agitated by evildoers; do not envy those who do wrong.
19Ps 37:2 For they wither quickly like grass and wilt like tender green plants.
19Ps 37:3 Trust in the LORD and do what is good; dwell in the land and live securely.
19Ps 37:4 Take delight in the LORD, and He will give you your heart's desires.
19Ps 37:5 Commit your way to the LORD; trust in Him, and He will act,
19Ps 37:6 making your righteousness shine like the dawn, your justice like the noonday.
19Ps 37:7 Be silent before the LORD and wait expectantly for Him; do not be agitated by one who prospers in his way, by the man who carries out evil plans.
19Ps 37:8 Refrain from anger and give up [your] rage; do not be agitated-- it can only bring harm.
19Ps 37:9 For evildoers will be destroyed, but those who put their hope in the LORD will inherit the land.
19Ps 37:10 A little while, and the wicked will be no more; though you look for him, he will not be there.
19Ps 37:11 But the humble will inherit the land and will enjoy abundant prosperity.
19Ps 37:12 The wicked schemes against the righteous and gnashes his teeth at him.
19Ps 37:13 The Lord laughs at him because He sees that his day is coming.
19Ps 37:14 The wicked have drawn the sword and strung the bow to bring down the afflicted and needy and to slaughter those whose way is upright.
19Ps 37:15 Their swords will enter their own hearts, and their bows will be broken.
19Ps 37:16 Better the little that the righteous man has than the abundance of many wicked people.
19Ps 37:17 For the arms of the wicked will be broken, but the LORD supports the righteous.
19Ps 37:18 The LORD watches over the blameless all their days, and their inheritance will last forever.
19Ps 37:19 They will not be disgraced in times of adversity; they will be satisfied in days of hunger.
19Ps 37:20 But the wicked will perish; the LORD's enemies, like the glory of the pastures, will fade away-- they will fade away like smoke.
19Ps 37:21 The wicked borrows and does not repay, but the righteous is gracious and giving.
19Ps 37:22 Those who are blessed by Him will inherit the land, but those cursed by Him will be destroyed.
19Ps 37:23 A man's steps are established by the LORD, and He takes pleasure in his way.
19Ps 37:24 Though he falls, he will not be overwhelmed, because the LORD holds his hand.
19Ps 37:25 I have been young and now I am old, yet I have not seen the righteous abandoned or his children begging bread.
19Ps 37:26 He is always generous, always lending, and his children are a blessing.
19Ps 37:27 Turn away from evil and do what is good, and dwell there forever.
19Ps 37:28 For the LORD loves justice and will not abandon His faithful ones. They are kept safe forever, but the children of the wicked will be destroyed.
19Ps 37:29 The righteous will inherit the land and dwell in it permanently.
19Ps 37:30 The mouth of the righteous utters wisdom; his tongue speaks what is just.
19Ps 37:31 The instruction of his God is in his heart; his steps do not falter.
19Ps 37:32 The wicked lies in wait for the righteous and seeks to kill him;
19Ps 37:33 the LORD will not leave him in his hand or allow him to be condemned when he is judged.
19Ps 37:34 Wait for the LORD and keep His way, and He will exalt you to inherit the land. You will watch when the wicked are destroyed.
19Ps 37:35 I have seen a wicked, violent man well-rooted like a flourishing native tree.
19Ps 37:36 Then I passed by and noticed he was gone; I searched for him, but he could not be found.
19Ps 37:37 Watch the blameless and observe the upright, for the man of peace will have a future.
19Ps 37:38 But transgressors will all be eliminated; the future of the wicked will be destroyed.
19Ps 37:39 The salvation of the righteous is from the LORD, their refuge in a time of distress.
19Ps 37:40 The LORD helps and delivers them; He will deliver them from the wicked and will save them because they take refuge in Him.
19Ps 38:1 [A Davidic psalm for remembrance.] LORD, do not punish me in Your anger or discipline me in Your wrath.
19Ps 38:2 For Your arrows have sunk into me, and Your hand has pressed down on me.
19Ps 38:3 There is no soundness in my body because of Your indignation; there is no health in my bones because of my sin.
19Ps 38:4 For my sins have flooded over my head; they are a burden too heavy for me to bear.
19Ps 38:5 My wounds are foul and festering because of my foolishness.
19Ps 38:6 I am bent over and brought low; all day long I go around in mourning.
19Ps 38:7 For my loins are full of burning pain, and there is no health in my body.
19Ps 38:8 I am faint and severely crushed; I groan because of the anguish of my heart.
19Ps 38:9 Lord, my every desire is known to You; my sighing is not hidden from You.
19Ps 38:10 My heart races, my strength leaves me, and even the light of my eyes has faded.
19Ps 38:11 My loved ones and friends stand back from my affliction, and my relatives stand at a distance.
19Ps 38:12 Those who seek my life set traps, and those who want to harm me threaten to destroy me; they plot treachery all day long.
19Ps 38:13 I am like a deaf person; I do not hear. I am like a speechless person who does not open his mouth.
19Ps 38:14 I am like a man who does not hear and has no arguments in his mouth.
19Ps 38:15 I put my hope in You, LORD; You will answer, Lord my God.
19Ps 38:16 For I said, "Don't let them rejoice over me-- those who are arrogant toward me when I stumble."
19Ps 38:17 For I am about to fall, and my pain is constantly with me.
19Ps 38:18 So I confess my guilt; I am anxious because of my sin.
19Ps 38:19 But my enemies are vigorous and powerful; many hate me for no reason.
19Ps 38:20 Those who repay evil for good attack me for pursuing good.
19Ps 38:21 LORD, do not abandon me; my God, do not be far from me.
19Ps 38:22 Hurry to help me, Lord, my Savior.
19Ps 39:1 [For the choir director, for Jeduthun. A Davidic psalm.] I said, "I will guard my ways so that I may not sin with my tongue; I will guard my mouth with a muzzle as long as the wicked are in my presence."
19Ps 39:2 I was speechless and quiet; I kept silent, even from [speaking] good, and my pain intensified.
19Ps 39:3 My heart grew hot within me; as I mused, a fire burned. I spoke with my tongue:
19Ps 39:4 "LORD, reveal to me the end of my life and the number of my days. Let me know how transitory I am.
19Ps 39:5 You, indeed, have made my days short in length, and my life span as nothing in Your sight. Yes, every mortal man is only a vapor. Selah
19Ps 39:6 Certainly, man walks about like a mere shadow. Indeed, they frantically rush around in vain, gathering possessions without knowing who will get them.
19Ps 39:7 "Now, Lord, what do I wait for? My hope is in You.
19Ps 39:8 Deliver me from all my transgressions; do not make me the taunt of fools.
19Ps 39:9 I am speechless; I do not open my mouth because of what You have done.
19Ps 39:10 Remove Your torment from me; I fade away because of the force of Your hand.
19Ps 39:11 You discipline a man with punishment for sin, consuming like a moth what is precious to him; every man is a mere vapor. Selah
19Ps 39:12 "Hear my prayer, LORD, and listen to my cry for help; do not be silent at my tears. For I am a foreigner residing with You, a sojourner like all my fathers.
19Ps 39:13 Turn Your angry gaze from me so that I may be cheered up before I die and am gone."
19Ps 40:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic psalm.] I waited patiently for the LORD, and He turned to me and heard my cry for help.
19Ps 40:2 He brought me up from a desolate pit, out of the muddy clay, and set my feet on a rock, making my steps secure.
19Ps 40:3 He put a new song in my mouth, a hymn of praise to our God. Many will see and fear, and put their trust in the LORD.
19Ps 40:4 How happy is the man who has put his trust in the LORD and has not turned to the proud or to those who run after lies!
19Ps 40:5 LORD my God, You have done many things-- Your wonderful works and Your plans for us; none can compare with You. If I were to report and speak [of them], they are more than can be told.
19Ps 40:6 You do not delight in sacrifice and offering; You open my ears to listen. You do not ask for a whole burnt offering or a sin offering.
19Ps 40:7 Then I said, "See, I have come; it is written about me in the volume of the scroll.
19Ps 40:8 I delight to do Your will, my God; Your instruction resides within me."
19Ps 40:9 I proclaim righteousness in the great assembly; see, I do not keep my mouth closed-- as You know, LORD.
19Ps 40:10 I did not hide Your righteousness in my heart; I spoke about Your faithfulness and salvation; I did not conceal Your constant love and truth from the great assembly.
19Ps 40:11 LORD, do not withhold Your compassion from me; Your constant love and truth will always guard me.
19Ps 40:12 For troubles without number have surrounded me; my sins have overtaken me; I am unable to see. They are more than the hairs of my head, and my courage leaves me.
19Ps 40:13 LORD, be pleased to deliver me; hurry to help me, LORD.
19Ps 40:14 Let those who seek to take my life be disgraced and confounded. Let those who wish me harm be driven back and humiliated.
19Ps 40:15 Let those who say to me, "Aha, aha!" be horrified because of their shame.
19Ps 40:16 Let all who seek You rejoice and be glad in You; let those who love Your salvation continually say, The LORD is great!"
19Ps 40:17 I am afflicted and needy; the Lord thinks of me. You are my help and my deliverer; my God, do not delay.
19Ps 41:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic psalm.] Happy is one who cares for the poor; the LORD will save him in a day of adversity.
19Ps 41:2 The LORD will keep him and preserve him; he will be blessed in the land. You will not give him over to the desire of his enemies.
19Ps 41:3 The LORD will sustain him on his sickbed; You will heal him on the bed where he lies.
19Ps 41:4 I said, "LORD, be gracious to me; heal me, for I have sinned against You."
19Ps 41:5 My enemies speak maliciously about me: "When will he die and be forgotten?"
19Ps 41:6 When one [of them] comes to visit, he speaks deceitfully; he stores up evil in his heart; he goes out and talks.
19Ps 41:7 All who hate me whisper together about me; they plan to harm me.
19Ps 41:8 "Lethal poison has been poured into him, and he won't rise again from where he lies!"
19Ps 41:9 Even my friend in whom I trusted, one who ate my bread, has lifted up his heel against me.
19Ps 41:10 But You, LORD, be gracious to me and raise me up; then I will repay them.
19Ps 41:11 By this I know that You delight in me: my enemy does not shout in triumph over me.
19Ps 41:12 You supported me because of my integrity and set me in Your presence forever.
19Ps 41:13 May the LORD, the God of Israel, be praised from everlasting to everlasting. Amen and amen.
19Ps 42:1 [ For the choir director. A Maskil of the sons of Korah.] As a deer longs for streams of water, so I long for You, God.
19Ps 42:2 I thirst for God, the living God. When can I come and appear before God?
19Ps 42:3 My tears have been my food day and night, while all day long people say to me, "Where is your God?"
19Ps 42:4 I remember this as I pour out my heart: how I walked with many, leading the festive procession to the house of God, with joyful and thankful shouts.
19Ps 42:5 Why am I so depressed? Why this turmoil within me? Put your hope in God, for I will still praise Him, my Savior and my God.
19Ps 42:6 I am deeply depressed; therefore I remember You from the land of Jordan and the peaks of Hermon, from Mount Mizar.
19Ps 42:7 Deep calls to deep in the roar of Your waterfalls; all Your breakers and Your billows have swept over me.
19Ps 42:8 The LORD will send His faithful love by day; His song will be with me in the night-- a prayer to the God of my life.
19Ps 42:9 I will say to God, my rock, "Why have You forgotten me? Why must I go about in sorrow because of the enemy's oppression?"
19Ps 42:10 My adversaries taunt me, as if crushing my bones, while all day long they say to me, "Where is your God?"
19Ps 42:11 Why am I so depressed? Why this turmoil within me? Put your hope in God, for I will still praise Him, my Savior and my God.
19Ps 43:1 Vindicate me, God, and defend my cause against an ungodly nation; rescue me from the deceitful and unjust man.
19Ps 43:2 For You are the God of my refuge. Why have You rejected me? Why must I go about in sorrow because of the enemy's oppression?
19Ps 43:3 Send Your light and Your truth; let them lead me. Let them bring me to Your holy mountain, to Your dwelling place.
19Ps 43:4 Then I will come to the altar of God, to God, my greatest joy. I will praise You with the lyre, God, my God.
19Ps 43:5 Why am I so depressed? Why this turmoil within me? Put your hope in God, for I will still praise Him, my Savior and my God.
19Ps 44:1 [For the choir director. A Maskil of the sons of Korah.] God, we have heard with our ears-- our forefathers have told us-- the work You accomplished in their days, in days long ago:
19Ps 44:2 to plant them, You drove out the nations with Your hand; to settle them, You crushed the peoples.
19Ps 44:3 For they did not take the land by their sword-- their arm did not bring them victory-- but by Your right hand, Your arm, and the light of Your face, for You were pleased with them.
19Ps 44:4 You are my King, my God, who ordains victories for Jacob.
19Ps 44:5 Through You we drive back our foes; through Your name we trample our enemies.
19Ps 44:6 For I do not trust in my bow, and my sword does not bring me victory.
19Ps 44:7 But You give us victory over our foes and let those who hate us be disgraced.
19Ps 44:8 We boast in God all day long; we will praise Your name forever. Selah
19Ps 44:9 But You have rejected and humiliated us; You do not march out with our armies.
19Ps 44:10 You make us retreat from the foe, and those who hate us have taken plunder for themselves.
19Ps 44:11 You hand us over to be eaten like sheep and scatter us among the nations.
19Ps 44:12 You sell Your people for nothing; You make no profit from selling them.
19Ps 44:13 You make us an object of reproach to our neighbors, a source of mockery and ridicule to those around us.
19Ps 44:14 You make us a joke among the nations, a laughingstock among the peoples.
19Ps 44:15 My disgrace is before me all day long, and shame has covered my face,
19Ps 44:16 because of the voice of the scorner and reviler, because of the enemy and avenger.
19Ps 44:17 All this has happened to us, but we have not forgotten You or betrayed Your covenant.
19Ps 44:18 Our hearts have not turned back; our steps have not strayed from Your path.
19Ps 44:19 But You have crushed us in a haunt of jackals and have covered us with deepest darkness.
19Ps 44:20 If we had forgotten the name of our God and spread out our hands to a foreign god,
19Ps 44:21 wouldn't God have found this out, since He knows the secrets of the heart?
19Ps 44:22 Because of You we are slain all day long; we are counted as sheep to be slaughtered.
19Ps 44:23 Wake up, LORD! Why are You sleeping? Get up! Don't reject us forever!
19Ps 44:24 Why do You hide Yourself and forget our affliction and oppression?
19Ps 44:25 For we have sunk down to the dust; our bodies cling to the ground.
19Ps 44:26 Rise up! Help us! Redeem us because of Your faithful love.
19Ps 45:1 [For the choir director: according to "The Lilies." A Maskil of the sons of Korah. A love song.] My heart is moved by a noble theme as I recite my verses to the king; my tongue is the pen of a skillful writer.
19Ps 45:2 You are the most handsome of men; grace flows from your lips. Therefore God has blessed you forever.
19Ps 45:3 Mighty warrior, strap your sword at your side. In your majesty and splendor--
19Ps 45:4 in your splendor ride triumphantly in the cause of truth, humility, and justice. May your right hand show your awe-inspiring deeds.
19Ps 45:5 Your arrows pierce the hearts of the king's enemies; the peoples fall under you.
19Ps 45:6 Your throne, God, is forever and ever; the scepter of Your kingdom is a scepter of justice.
19Ps 45:7 You love righteousness and hate wickedness; therefore God, your God, has anointed you, more than your companions, with the oil of joy.
19Ps 45:8 Myrrh, aloes, and cassia [perfume] all your garments; from ivory palaces harps bring you joy.
19Ps 45:9 Kings' daughters are among your honored women; the queen, adorned with gold from Ophir, stands at your right hand.
19Ps 45:10 Listen, daughter, pay attention and consider: forget your people and your father's house,
19Ps 45:11 and the king will desire your beauty. Bow down to him, for he is your lord.
19Ps 45:12 The daughter of Tyre, the wealthy people, will seek your favor with gifts.
19Ps 45:13 In [her chamber], the royal daughter is all glorious, her clothing embroidered with gold.
19Ps 45:14 In colorful garments she is led to the king; after her, the virgins, her companions, are brought to you.
19Ps 45:15 They are led in with gladness and rejoicing; they enter the king's palace.
19Ps 45:16 Your sons will succeed your ancestors; you will make them princes throughout the land.
19Ps 45:17 I will cause your name to be remembered for all generations; therefore the peoples will praise you forever and ever.
19Ps 46:1 [For the choir director. A song of the sons of Korah. According to Alamoth.] God is our refuge and strength, a helper who is always found in times of trouble.
19Ps 46:2 Therefore we will not be afraid, though the earth trembles and the mountains topple into the depths of the seas,
19Ps 46:3 though its waters roar and foam and the mountains quake with its turmoil. Selah
19Ps 46:4 [There is] a river-- its streams delight the city of God, the holy dwelling place of the Most High.
19Ps 46:5 God is within her; she will not be toppled. God will help her when the morning dawns.
19Ps 46:6 Nations rage, kingdoms topple; the earth melts when He lifts His voice.
19Ps 46:7 The LORD of Hosts is with us; the God of Jacob is our stronghold. Selah
19Ps 46:8 Come, see the works of the LORD, who brings devastation on the earth.
19Ps 46:9 He makes wars cease throughout the earth. He shatters bows and cuts spears to pieces; He burns up the chariots.
19Ps 46:10 "Stop [your fighting]-- and know that I am God, exalted among the nations, exalted on the earth."
19Ps 46:11 The LORD of Hosts is with us; the God of Jacob is our stronghold. Selah
19Ps 47:1 [ For the choir director. A psalm of the sons of Korah.] Clap your hands, all you peoples; shout to God with a jubilant cry.
19Ps 47:2 For the LORD Most High is awe-inspiring, a great King over all the earth.
19Ps 47:3 He subdues peoples under us and nations under our feet.
19Ps 47:4 He chooses for us our inheritance-- the pride of Jacob, whom He loves. Selah
19Ps 47:5 God ascends amid shouts of joy, the LORD, amid the sound of trumpets.
19Ps 47:6 Sing praise to God, sing praise; sing praise to our King, sing praise!
19Ps 47:7 Sing a song of instruction, for God is King of all the earth.
19Ps 47:8 God reigns over the nations; God is seated on His holy throne.
19Ps 47:9 The nobles of the peoples have assembled [with] the people of the God of Abraham. For the leaders of the earth belong to God; He is greatly exalted.
19Ps 48:1 [A song. A psalm of the sons of Korah.] The LORD is great and is highly praised in the city of our God. His holy mountain,
19Ps 48:2 rising splendidly, is the joy of the whole earth. Mount Zion on the slopes of the north is the city of the great King.
19Ps 48:3 God is known as a stronghold in its citadels.
19Ps 48:4 Look! The kings assembled; they advanced together.
19Ps 48:5 They looked, and froze with fear; they fled in terror.
19Ps 48:6 Trembling seized them there, agony like that of a woman in labor,
19Ps 48:7 as You wrecked the ships of Tarshish with the east wind.
19Ps 48:8 Just as we heard, so we have seen in the city of the LORD of Hosts, in the city of our God; God will establish it forever. Selah
19Ps 48:9 God, within Your temple, we contemplate Your faithful love.
19Ps 48:10 Your name, God, like Your praise, reaches to the ends of the earth; Your right hand is filled with justice.
19Ps 48:11 Mount Zion is glad. The towns of Judah rejoice because of Your judgments.
19Ps 48:12 Go around Zion, encircle it; count its towers,
19Ps 48:13 note its ramparts; tour its citadels so that you can tell a future generation:
19Ps 48:14 "This God, our God forever and ever-- He will lead us eternally."
19Ps 49:1 [For the choir director. A psalm of the sons of Korah.] Hear this, all you peoples; listen, all who inhabit the world,
19Ps 49:2 both low and high, rich and poor together.
19Ps 49:3 My mouth speaks wisdom; my heart's meditation [brings] understanding.
19Ps 49:4 I turn my ear to a proverb; I explain my riddle with a lyre.
19Ps 49:5 Why should I fear in times of trouble? The iniquity of my foes surrounds me.
19Ps 49:6 They trust in their wealth and boast of their abundant riches.
19Ps 49:7 Yet these cannot redeem a person or pay his ransom to God--
19Ps 49:8 since the price of redeeming him is too costly, one should forever stop trying--
19Ps 49:9 so that he may live forever and not see the Pit.
19Ps 49:10 For one can see that wise men die; the foolish and the senseless also pass away. Then they leave their wealth to others.
19Ps 49:11 Their graves are their eternal homes, their homes from generation to generation, though they have named estates after themselves.
19Ps 49:12 But despite [his] assets, man will not last; he is like the animals that perish.
19Ps 49:13 This is the way of those who are arrogant, and of their followers, who approve of their words. Selah
19Ps 49:14 Like sheep they are headed for Sheol; Death will shepherd them. The upright will rule over them in the morning, and their form will waste away in Sheol, far from their lofty abode.
19Ps 49:15 But God will redeem my life from the power of Sheol, for He will take me. Selah
19Ps 49:16 Do not be afraid when a man gets rich, when the wealth of his house increases.
19Ps 49:17 For when he dies, he will take nothing at all; his wealth will not follow him down.
19Ps 49:18 Though he praises himself during his lifetime-- and people praise you when you do well for yourself--
19Ps 49:19 he will go to the generation of his fathers; they will never see the light.
19Ps 49:20 A man with valuable possessions but without understanding is like the animals that perish.
19Ps 50:1 [A psalm of Asaph.] God, the LORD God speaks; He summons the earth from east to west.
19Ps 50:2 From Zion, the perfection of beauty, God appears in radiance.
19Ps 50:3 Our God is coming; He will not be silent! Devouring fire precedes Him, and a storm rages around Him.
19Ps 50:4 On high, He summons heaven and earth in order to judge His people.
19Ps 50:5 "Gather My faithful ones to Me, those who made a covenant with Me by sacrifice."
19Ps 50:6 The heavens proclaim His righteousness, for God is the judge. Selah
19Ps 50:7 "Listen, My people, and I will speak; I will testify against you, Israel. I am God, your God.
19Ps 50:8 I do not rebuke you for your sacrifices or for your burnt offerings, which are continually before Me.
19Ps 50:9 I will not accept a bull from your household or male goats from your pens,
19Ps 50:10 for every animal of the forest is Mine, the cattle on a thousand hills.
19Ps 50:11 I know every bird of the mountains, and the creatures of the field are Mine.
19Ps 50:12 If I were hungry, I would not tell you, for the world and everything in it is Mine.
19Ps 50:13 Do I eat the flesh of bulls or drink the blood of goats?
19Ps 50:14 Sacrifice a thank offering to God, and pay your vows to the Most High.
19Ps 50:15 Call on Me in a day of trouble; I will rescue you, and you will honor Me."
19Ps 50:16 But God says to the wicked: "What right do you have to recite My statutes and to take My covenant on your lips?
19Ps 50:17 You hate instruction and turn your back on My words.
19Ps 50:18 When you see a thief, you make friends with him, and you associate with adulterers.
19Ps 50:19 You unleash your mouth for evil and harness your tongue for deceit.
19Ps 50:20 You sit, maligning your brother, slandering your mother's son.
19Ps 50:21 You have done these things, and I kept silent; you thought I was just like you. But I will rebuke you and lay out the case before you.
19Ps 50:22 "Understand this, you who forget God, or I will tear you apart, and there will be no rescuer.
19Ps 50:23 Whoever sacrifices a thank offering honors Me, and whoever orders his conduct, I will show him the salvation of God."
19Ps 51:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic psalm, when Nathan the prophet came to him after he had gone to Bathsheba.] Be gracious to me, God, according to Your faithful love; according to Your abundant compassion, blot out my rebellion.
19Ps 51:2 Wash away my guilt, and cleanse me from my sin.
19Ps 51:3 For I am conscious of my rebellion, and my sin is always before me.
19Ps 51:4 Against You-- You alone-- I have sinned and done this evil in Your sight. So You are right when You pass sentence; You are blameless when You judge.
19Ps 51:5 Indeed, I was guilty [when I] was born; I was sinful when my mother conceived me.
19Ps 51:6 Surely You desire integrity in the inner self, and You teach me wisdom deep within.
19Ps 51:7 Purify me with hyssop, and I will be clean; wash me, and I will be whiter than snow.
19Ps 51:8 Let me hear joy and gladness; let the bones You have crushed rejoice.
19Ps 51:9 Turn Your face away from my sins and blot out all my guilt.
19Ps 51:10 God, create a clean heart for me and renew a steadfast spirit within me.
19Ps 51:11 Do not banish me from Your presence or take Your Holy Spirit from me.
19Ps 51:12 Restore the joy of Your salvation to me, and give me a willing spirit.
19Ps 51:13 Then I will teach the rebellious Your ways, and sinners will return to You.
19Ps 51:14 Save me from the guilt of bloodshed, God, the God of my salvation, and my tongue will sing of Your righteousness.
19Ps 51:15 Lord, open my lips, and my mouth will declare Your praise.
19Ps 51:16 You do not want a sacrifice, or I would give it; You are not pleased with a burnt offering.
19Ps 51:17 The sacrifice pleasing to God is a broken spirit. God, You will not despise a broken and humbled heart.
19Ps 51:18 In Your good pleasure, cause Zion to prosper; build the walls of Jerusalem.
19Ps 51:19 Then You will delight in righteous sacrifices, whole burnt offerings; then bulls will be offered on Your altar.
19Ps 52:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic Maskil. When Doeg the Edomite went and reported to Saul, telling him, "David went to Ahimelech's house."] Why brag about evil, you hero! God's faithful love is constant.
19Ps 52:2 Like a sharpened razor, your tongue devises destruction, working treachery.
19Ps 52:3 You love evil instead of good, lying instead of speaking truthfully. Selah
19Ps 52:4 You love any words that destroy, you treacherous tongue!
19Ps 52:5 This is why God will bring you down forever. He will take you, ripping you out of your tent; He will uproot you from the land of the living. Selah
19Ps 52:6 The righteous will look on with awe and will ridicule him:
19Ps 52:7 "Here is the man who would not make God his refuge, but trusted in the abundance of his riches, taking refuge in his destructive behavior."
19Ps 52:8 But I am like a flourishing olive tree in the house of God; I trust in God's faithful love forever and ever.
19Ps 52:9 I will praise You forever for what You have done. In the presence of Your faithful people, I will put my hope in Your name, for it is good.
19Ps 53:1 [For the choir director: on Mahalath. A Davidic Maskil.] The fool says in his heart, "God does not exist." They are corrupt, and they do vile deeds. There is no one who does good.
19Ps 53:2 God looks down from heaven on the human race to see if there is one who is wise and who seeks God.
19Ps 53:3 Everyone has turned aside; they have all become corrupt. There is no one who does good, not even one.
19Ps 53:4 Will evildoers never understand? They consume My people as they consume bread; they do not call on God.
19Ps 53:5 Then they will be filled with terror-- terror like no other-- because God will scatter the bones of those who besiege you. You will put them to shame, for God has rejected them.
19Ps 53:6 Oh, that Israel's deliverance would come from Zion! When God restores His captive people, Jacob will rejoice; Israel will be glad.
19Ps 54:1 [For the choir director: with stringed instruments. A Davidic Maskil. When the Ziphites went and said to Saul, "Is David not hiding among us?"] God, save me by Your name, and vindicate me by Your might!
19Ps 54:2 God, hear my prayer; listen to the words of my mouth.
19Ps 54:3 For strangers rise up against me, and violent men seek my life. They have no regard for God. Selah
19Ps 54:4 God is my helper; the Lord is the sustainer of my life.
19Ps 54:5 He will repay my adversaries for [their] evil. Because of Your faithfulness, annihilate them.
19Ps 54:6 I will sacrifice a freewill offering to You. I will praise Your name, LORD, because it is good.
19Ps 54:7 For He has delivered me from every trouble, and my eye has looked down on my enemies.
19Ps 55:1 [For the choir director: with stringed instruments. A Davidic Maskil.] God, listen to my prayer and do not ignore my plea for help.
19Ps 55:2 Pay attention to me and answer me. I am restless and in turmoil with my complaint,
19Ps 55:3 because of the enemy's voice, because of the pressure of the wicked. For they bring down disaster on me and harass me in anger.
19Ps 55:4 My heart shudders within me; terrors of death sweep over me.
19Ps 55:5 Fear and trembling grip me; horror has overwhelmed me.
19Ps 55:6 I said, "If only I had wings like a dove! I would fly away and find rest.
19Ps 55:7 How far away I would flee; I would stay in the wilderness. Selah
19Ps 55:8 I would hurry to my shelter from the raging wind and the storm."
19Ps 55:9 Lord, confuse and confound their speech, for I see violence and strife in the city;
19Ps 55:10 day and night they make the rounds on its walls. Crime and trouble are within it;
19Ps 55:11 destruction is inside it; oppression and deceit never leave its marketplace.
19Ps 55:12 Now, it is not an enemy who insults me-- otherwise I could bear it; it is not a foe who rises up against me-- otherwise I could hide from him.
19Ps 55:13 But it is you, a man who is my peer, my companion and good friend!
19Ps 55:14 We used to have close fellowship; we walked with the crowd into the house of God.
19Ps 55:15 Let death take them by surprise; let them go down to Sheol alive, because evil is in their homes and within them.
19Ps 55:16 But I call to God, and the LORD will save me.
19Ps 55:17 I complain and groan morning, noon, and night, and He hears my voice.
19Ps 55:18 Though many are against me, He will redeem me from my battle unharmed.
19Ps 55:19 God, the One enthroned from long ago, will hear, and will humiliate them Selah because they do not change and do not fear God.
19Ps 55:20 He acts violently against those at peace with him; he violates his covenant.
19Ps 55:21 His buttery words are smooth, but war is in his heart. His words are softer than oil, but they are drawn swords.
19Ps 55:22 Cast your burden on the LORD, and He will support you; He will never allow the righteous to be shaken.
19Ps 55:23 You, God, will bring them down to the pit of destruction; men of bloodshed and treachery will not live out half their days. But I will trust in You.
19Ps 56:1 [For the choir director: according to "A Silent Dove Far Away." A Davidic Miktam. When the Philistines seized him in Gath.] Be gracious to me, God, for man tramples me; he fights and oppresses me all day long.
19Ps 56:2 My adversaries trample me all day, for many arrogantly fight against me.
19Ps 56:3 When I am afraid, I will trust in You.
19Ps 56:4 In God, whose word I praise, in God I trust; I will not fear. What can man do to me?
19Ps 56:5 They twist my words all day long; all their thoughts are against me for evil.
19Ps 56:6 They stir up strife, they lurk; they watch my steps while they wait to take my life.
19Ps 56:7 Will they escape in spite of such sin? God, bring down the nations in wrath.
19Ps 56:8 You Yourself have recorded my wanderings. Put my tears in Your bottle. Are they not in Your records?
19Ps 56:9 Then my enemies will retreat on the day when I call. This I know: God is for me.
19Ps 56:10 In God, whose word I praise, in the LORD, whose word I praise,
19Ps 56:11 in God I trust; I will not fear. What can man do to me?
19Ps 56:12 I am obligated by vows to You, God; I will make my thank offerings to You.
19Ps 56:13 For You delivered me from death, even my feet from stumbling, to walk before God in the light of life.
19Ps 57:1 [For the choir director: "Do Not Destroy." A Davidic Miktam. When he fled before Saul into the cave.] Be gracious to me, God, be gracious to me, for I take refuge in You. I will seek refuge in the shadow of Your wings until danger passes.
19Ps 57:2 I call to God Most High, to God who fulfills [His purpose] for me.
19Ps 57:3 He reaches down from heaven and saves me, challenging the one who tramples me. Selah God sends His faithful love and truth.
19Ps 57:4 I am in the midst of lions; I lie down with those who devour men. Their teeth are spears and arrows; their tongues are sharp swords.
19Ps 57:5 God, be exalted above the heavens; let Your glory be above the whole earth.
19Ps 57:6 They prepared a net for my steps; I was downcast. They dug a pit ahead of me, but they fell into it! Selah
19Ps 57:7 My heart is confident, God, my heart is confident. I will sing; I will sing praises.
19Ps 57:8 Wake up, my soul! Wake up, harp and lyre! I will wake up the dawn.
19Ps 57:9 I will praise You, Lord, among the peoples; I will sing praises to You among the nations.
19Ps 57:10 For Your faithful love is as high as the heavens; Your faithfulness reaches to the clouds.
19Ps 57:11 God, be exalted above the heavens; let Your glory be over the whole earth.
19Ps 58:1 [For the choir director: "Do Not Destroy." A Davidic Miktam.] Do you really speak righteously, you mighty ones? Do you judge people fairly?
19Ps 58:2 No, you practice injustice in your hearts; with your hands you weigh out violence in the land.
19Ps 58:3 The wicked go astray from the womb; liars err from birth.
19Ps 58:4 They have venom like the venom of a snake, like the deaf cobra that stops up its ears,
19Ps 58:5 that does not listen to the sound of the charmers who skillfully weave spells.
19Ps 58:6 God, knock the teeth out of their mouths; LORD, tear out the young lions' fangs.
19Ps 58:7 They will vanish like water that flows by; they will aim their useless arrows.
19Ps 58:8 Like a slug that moves along in slime, like a woman's miscarried [child], they will not see the sun.
19Ps 58:9 Before your pots can feel the heat of the thorns-- whether green or burning-- He will sweep them away.
19Ps 58:10 The righteous will rejoice when he sees the retribution; he will wash his feet in the blood of the wicked.
19Ps 58:11 Then people will say, "Yes, there is a reward for the righteous! There is a God who judges on earth!"
19Ps 59:1 [For the choir director: "Do Not Destroy." A Davidic Miktam. When Saul sent [agents] to watch the house and kill him.] Deliver me from my enemies, my God; protect me from those who rise up against me.
19Ps 59:2 Deliver me from those who practice sin, and save me from men of bloodshed.
19Ps 59:3 LORD, look! They set an ambush for me. Powerful men attack me, but not because of any sin or rebellion of mine.
19Ps 59:4 For no fault of mine, they run and take up a position. Awake to help me, and take notice.
19Ps 59:5 You, LORD God of Hosts, God of Israel, rise up to punish all the nations; do not show grace to any wicked traitors. Selah
19Ps 59:6 They return at evening, snarling like dogs and prowling around the city.
19Ps 59:7 Look, they spew from their mouths-- sharp words from their lips. "For who," [they say,] "will hear?"
19Ps 59:8 But You laugh at them, LORD; You ridicule all the nations.
19Ps 59:9 I will keep watch for You, my strength, because God is my stronghold.
19Ps 59:10 My faithful God will come to meet me; God will let me look down on my adversaries.
19Ps 59:11 Do not kill them; otherwise, my people will forget. By Your power, make them homeless wanderers and bring them down, Lord, our shield.
19Ps 59:12 The sin of their mouths is the word of their lips, so let them be caught in their pride. They utter curses and lies.
19Ps 59:13 Consume [them] in rage; consume [them] until they are gone. Then they will know to the ends of the earth that God rules over Jacob. Selah
19Ps 59:14 And they return at evening, snarling like dogs and prowling around the city.
19Ps 59:15 They scavenge for food; they growl if they are not satisfied.
19Ps 59:16 But I will sing of Your strength and will joyfully proclaim Your faithful love in the morning. For You have been a stronghold for me, a refuge in my day of trouble.
19Ps 59:17 To You, my strength, I sing praises, because God is my stronghold-- my faithful God.
19Ps 60:1 [For the choir director: according to "The Lily of Testimony." A Davidic Miktam for teaching. When he fought with Aram-naharaim and Aram-zobah, and Joab returned and struck Edom in the Valley of Salt, [killing] 12,000.] God, You have rejected us; You have broken out against us; You have been angry. Restore us!
19Ps 60:2 You have shaken the land and split it open. Heal its fissures, for it shudders.
19Ps 60:3 You have made Your people suffer hardship; You have given us a wine to drink that made us stagger.
19Ps 60:4 You have given a signal flag to those who fear You, so that they can flee before the archers. Selah
19Ps 60:5 Save with Your right hand, and answer me, so that those You love may be rescued.
19Ps 60:6 God has spoken in His sanctuary: "I will triumph! I will divide up Shechem. I will apportion the Valley of Succoth.
19Ps 60:7 Gilead is Mine, Manasseh is Mine, and Ephraim is My helmet; Judah is My scepter.
19Ps 60:8 Moab is My washbasin; on Edom I throw My sandal. Over Philistia I shout in triumph."
19Ps 60:9 Who will bring me to the fortified city? Who will lead me to Edom?
19Ps 60:10 Is it not You, God, who have rejected us? God, You do not march out with our armies.
19Ps 60:11 Give us aid against the foe, for human help is worthless.
19Ps 60:12 With God we will perform valiantly; He will trample our foes.
19Ps 61:1 [For the choir director: on stringed instruments. Davidic.] God, hear my cry; pay attention to my prayer.
19Ps 61:2 I call to You from the ends of the earth when my heart is without strength. Lead me to a rock that is high above me,
19Ps 61:3 for You have been a refuge for me, a strong tower in the face of the enemy.
19Ps 61:4 I will live in Your tent forever and take refuge under the shelter of Your wings. Selah
19Ps 61:5 God, You have heard my vows; You have given a heritage to those who fear Your name.
19Ps 61:6 Add days to the king's life; may his years span many generations.
19Ps 61:7 May he sit enthroned before God forever; appoint faithful love and truth to guard him.
19Ps 61:8 Then I will continually sing of Your name, fulfilling my vows day by day.
19Ps 62:1 [For the choir director: according to Jeduthun. A Davidic psalm.] I am at rest in God alone; my salvation comes from Him.
19Ps 62:2 He alone is my rock and my salvation, my stronghold; I will never be shaken.
19Ps 62:3 How long will you threaten a man? Will all of you attack as if he were a leaning wall or a tottering stone fence?
19Ps 62:4 They only plan to bring him down from his high position. They take pleasure in lying; they bless with their mouths, but they curse inwardly. Selah
19Ps 62:5 Rest in God alone, my soul, for my hope comes from Him.
19Ps 62:6 He alone is my rock and my salvation, my stronghold; I will not be shaken.
19Ps 62:7 My salvation and glory depend on God; my strong rock, my refuge, is in God.
19Ps 62:8 Trust in Him at all times, you people; pour out your hearts before Him. God is our refuge. Selah
19Ps 62:9 Men are only a vapor; exalted men, an illusion. On a balance scale, they go up; together they [weigh] less than a vapor.
19Ps 62:10 Place no trust in oppression, or false hope in robbery. If wealth increases, pay no attention to it.
19Ps 62:11 God has spoken once; I have heard this twice: strength belongs to God,
19Ps 62:12 and faithful love belongs to You, LORD. For You repay each according to his works.
19Ps 63:1 [A Davidic psalm. When he was in the Wilderness of Judah.] God, You are my God; I eagerly seek You. I thirst for You; my body faints for You in a land that is dry, desolate, and without water.
19Ps 63:2 So I gaze on You in the sanctuary to see Your strength and Your glory.
19Ps 63:3 My lips will glorify You because Your faithful love is better than life.
19Ps 63:4 So I will praise You as long as I live; at Your name, I will lift up my hands.
19Ps 63:5 You satisfy me as with rich food; my mouth will praise You with joyful lips.
19Ps 63:6 When, on my bed, I think of You, I meditate on You during the night watches
19Ps 63:7 because You are my help; I will rejoice in the shadow of Your wings.
19Ps 63:8 I follow close to You; Your right hand holds on to me.
19Ps 63:9 But those who seek to destroy my life will go into the depths of the earth.
19Ps 63:10 They will be given over to the power of the sword; they will become the jackals' prey.
19Ps 63:11 But the king will rejoice in God; all who swear by Him will boast, for the mouths of liars will be shut.
19Ps 64:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic psalm.] God, hear my voice when I complain. Protect my life from the terror of the enemy.
19Ps 64:2 Hide me from the scheming of the wicked, from the mob of evildoers,
19Ps 64:3 who sharpen their tongues like swords and aim bitter words like arrows,
19Ps 64:4 shooting from concealed places at the innocent. They shoot at him suddenly and are not afraid.
19Ps 64:5 They encourage each other in an evil plan; they talk about hiding traps and say, "Who will see them?"
19Ps 64:6 They devise crimes [and say,] "We have perfected a secret plan." The inner man and the heart are mysterious.
19Ps 64:7 But God will shoot them with arrows; suddenly, they will be wounded.
19Ps 64:8 They will be made to stumble; their own tongues work against them. All who see them will shake their heads.
19Ps 64:9 Then everyone will fear and will tell about God's work, for they will understand what He has done.
19Ps 64:10 The righteous rejoice in the LORD and take refuge in Him; all the upright in heart offer praise.
19Ps 65:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic psalm. A song.] Praise is rightfully Yours, God, in Zion; vows to You will be fulfilled.
19Ps 65:2 All humanity will come to You, the One who hears prayer.
19Ps 65:3 Iniquities overwhelm me; only You can atone for our rebellions.
19Ps 65:4 How happy is the one You choose and bring near to live in Your courts! We will be satisfied with the goodness of Your house, the holiness of Your temple.
19Ps 65:5 You answer us in righteousness, with awe-inspiring works, God of our salvation, the hope of all the ends of the earth and of the distant seas;
19Ps 65:6 You establish the mountains by Your power, robed with strength;
19Ps 65:7 You silence the roar of the seas, the roar of their waves, and the tumult of the nations.
19Ps 65:8 Those who live far away are awed by Your signs; You make east and west shout for joy.
19Ps 65:9 You visit the earth and water it abundantly, enriching it greatly. God's stream is filled with water, for You prepare the earth in this way, providing [people] with grain.
19Ps 65:10 You soften it with showers and bless its growth, soaking its furrows and leveling its ridges.
19Ps 65:11 You crown the year with Your goodness; Your ways overflow with plenty.
19Ps 65:12 The wilderness pastures overflow, and the hills are robed with joy.
19Ps 65:13 The pastures are clothed with flocks, and the valleys covered with grain. They shout in triumph; indeed, they sing.
19Ps 66:1 [For the choir director. A song. A psalm.] Shout joyfully to God, all the earth!
19Ps 66:2 Sing the glory of His name; make His praise glorious.
19Ps 66:3 Say to God, "How awe-inspiring are Your works! Your enemies will cringe before You because of Your great strength.
19Ps 66:4 All the earth will worship You and sing praise to You. They will sing praise to Your name." Selah
19Ps 66:5 Come and see the works of God; His acts toward mankind are awe-inspiring.
19Ps 66:6 He turned the sea into dry land, and they crossed the river on foot. There we rejoiced in Him.
19Ps 66:7 He rules forever by His might; He keeps His eye on the nations. The rebellious should not exalt themselves. Selah
19Ps 66:8 Praise our God, you peoples; let the sound of His praise be heard.
19Ps 66:9 He keeps us alive and does not allow our feet to slip.
19Ps 66:10 For You, God, tested us; You refined us as silver is refined.
19Ps 66:11 You lured us into a trap; You placed burdens on our backs.
19Ps 66:12 You let men ride over our heads; we went through fire and water, but You brought us out to abundance.
19Ps 66:13 I will enter Your house with burnt offerings; I will pay You my vows
19Ps 66:14 that my lips promised and my mouth spoke during my distress.
19Ps 66:15 I will offer You fattened sheep as burnt offerings, with the fragrant smoke of rams; I will sacrifice oxen with goats. Selah
19Ps 66:16 Come and listen, all who fear God, and I will tell what He has done for me.
19Ps 66:17 I cried out to Him with my mouth, and praise was on my tongue.
19Ps 66:18 If I had been aware of malice in my heart, the Lord would not have listened.
19Ps 66:19 However, God has listened; He has paid attention to the sound of my prayer.
19Ps 66:20 May God be praised! He has not turned away my prayer or turned His faithful love from me.
19Ps 67:1 [For the choir director: with stringed instruments. A psalm. A song.] May God be gracious to us and bless us; look on us with favor Selah
19Ps 67:2 so that Your way may be known on earth, Your salvation among all nations.
19Ps 67:3 Let the peoples praise You, God; let all the peoples praise You.
19Ps 67:4 Let the nations rejoice and shout for joy, for You judge the peoples with fairness and lead the nations on earth. Selah
19Ps 67:5 Let the peoples praise You, God, let all the peoples praise You.
19Ps 67:6 The earth has produced its harvest; God, our God, blesses us.
19Ps 67:7 God will bless us, and all the ends of the earth will fear Him.
19Ps 68:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic psalm. A song.] God arises. His enemies scatter, and those who hate Him flee from His presence.
19Ps 68:2 As smoke is blown away, so You blow [them] away. As wax melts before the fire, so the wicked are destroyed before God.
19Ps 68:3 But the righteous are glad; they rejoice before God and celebrate with joy.
19Ps 68:4 Sing to God! Sing praises to His name. Exalt Him who rides on the clouds-- His name is Yahweh-- and rejoice before Him.
19Ps 68:5 A father of the fatherless and a champion of widows is God in His holy dwelling.
19Ps 68:6 God provides homes for those who are deserted. He leads out the prisoners to prosperity, but the rebellious live in a scorched land.
19Ps 68:7 God, when You went out before Your people, when You marched through the desert, Selah
19Ps 68:8 the earth trembled, and the skies poured down [rain] before God, the God of Sinai, before God, the God of Israel.
19Ps 68:9 You, God, showered abundant rain; You revived Your inheritance when it languished.
19Ps 68:10 Your people settled in it; by Your goodness You provided for the poor, God.
19Ps 68:11 The Lord gave the command; a great company of women brought the good news:
19Ps 68:12 "The kings of the armies flee-- they flee!" She who stays at home divides the spoil.
19Ps 68:13 While you lie among the sheepfolds, the wings of a dove are covered with silver, and its feathers with glistening gold.
19Ps 68:14 When the Almighty scattered kings in the land, it snowed on Zalmon.
19Ps 68:15 Mount Bashan is God's towering mountain; Mount Bashan is a mountain of many peaks.
19Ps 68:16 Why gaze with envy, you mountain peaks, at the mountain God desired for His dwelling? The LORD will live [there] forever!
19Ps 68:17 God's chariots are tens of thousands, thousands and thousands; the Lord is among them in the sanctuary as He was at Sinai.
19Ps 68:18 You ascended to the heights, taking away captives; You received gifts from people, even from the rebellious, so that the LORD God might live [there].
19Ps 68:19 May the Lord be praised! Day after day He bears our burdens; God is our salvation. Selah
19Ps 68:20 Our God is a God of salvation, and escape from death belongs to the Lord God.
19Ps 68:21 Surely God crushes the heads of His enemies, the hairy head of one who goes on in his guilty acts.
19Ps 68:22 The Lord said, "I will bring [them] back from Bashan; I will bring [them] back from the depths of the sea
19Ps 68:23 so that your foot may wade in blood and your dogs' tongues may have their share from the enemies."
19Ps 68:24 People have seen Your procession, God, the procession of my God, my King, in the sanctuary.
19Ps 68:25 Singers lead the way, with musicians following; among them are young women playing tambourines.
19Ps 68:26 Praise God in the assemblies; [praise] the LORD from the fountain of Israel.
19Ps 68:27 There is Benjamin, the youngest, leading them, the rulers of Judah in their assembly, the rulers of Zebulun, the rulers of Naphtali.
19Ps 68:28 Your God has decreed your strength. Show Your strength, God, You who have acted on our behalf.
19Ps 68:29 Because of Your temple at Jerusalem, kings will bring tribute to You.
19Ps 68:30 Rebuke the beast in the reeds, the herd of bulls with the calves of the peoples. Trample underfoot those with bars of silver. Scatter the peoples who take pleasure in war.
19Ps 68:31 Ambassadors will come from Egypt; Cush will stretch out its hands to God.
19Ps 68:32 Sing to God, you kingdoms of the earth; sing praise to the Lord, Selah
19Ps 68:33 to Him who rides in the ancient, highest heavens. Look, He thunders with His powerful voice!
19Ps 68:34 Ascribe power to God. His majesty is over Israel, His power among the clouds.
19Ps 68:35 God, You are awe-inspiring in Your sanctuaries. The God of Israel gives power and strength to His people. May God be praised!
19Ps 69:1 [For the choir director: according to "The Lilies." Davidic.] Save me, God, for the water has risen to my neck.
19Ps 69:2 I have sunk in deep mud, and there is no footing; I have come into deep waters, and a flood sweeps over me.
19Ps 69:3 I am weary from my crying; my throat is parched. My eyes fail, looking for my God.
19Ps 69:4 Those who hate me without cause are more numerous than the hairs of my head; my deceitful enemies, who would destroy me, are powerful. Though I did not steal, I must repay.
19Ps 69:5 God, You know my foolishness, and my guilty acts are not hidden from You.
19Ps 69:6 Do not let those who put their hope in You be disgraced because of me, Lord God of Hosts; do not let those who seek You be humiliated because of me, God of Israel.
19Ps 69:7 For I have endured insults because of You, and shame has covered my face.
19Ps 69:8 I have become a stranger to my brothers and a foreigner to my mother's sons
19Ps 69:9 because zeal for Your house has consumed me, and the insults of those who insult You have fallen on me.
19Ps 69:10 I mourned and fasted, but it brought me insults.
19Ps 69:11 I wore sackcloth as my clothing, and I was a joke to them.
19Ps 69:12 Those who sit at the city gate talk about me, and drunkards make up songs about me.
19Ps 69:13 But as for me, LORD, my prayer to You is for a time of favor. In Your abundant, faithful love, God, answer me with Your sure salvation.
19Ps 69:14 Rescue me from the miry mud; don't let me sink. Let me be rescued from those who hate me, and from the deep waters.
19Ps 69:15 Don't let the floodwaters sweep over me or the deep swallow me up; don't let the Pit close its mouth over me.
19Ps 69:16 Answer me, LORD, for Your faithful love is good; in keeping with Your great compassion, turn to me.
19Ps 69:17 Don't hide Your face from Your servant, for I am in distress. Answer me quickly!
19Ps 69:18 Draw near to me and redeem me; ransom me because of my enemies.
19Ps 69:19 You know the insults I endure-- my shame and disgrace. You are aware of all my adversaries.
19Ps 69:20 Insults have broken my heart, and I am in despair. I waited for sympathy, but there was none; for comforters, but found no one.
19Ps 69:21 Instead, they gave me gall for my food, and for my thirst they gave me vinegar to drink.
19Ps 69:22 Let their table set before them be a snare, and let it be a trap for [their] allies.
19Ps 69:23 Let their eyes grow too dim to see, and let their loins continually shake.
19Ps 69:24 Pour out Your rage on them, and let Your burning anger overtake them.
19Ps 69:25 Make their fortification desolate; may no one live in their tents.
19Ps 69:26 For they persecute the one You struck and talk about the pain of those You wounded.
19Ps 69:27 Add guilt to their guilt; do not let them share in Your righteousness.
19Ps 69:28 Let them be erased from the book of life and not be recorded with the righteous.
19Ps 69:29 But as for me-- poor and in pain-- let Your salvation protect me, God.
19Ps 69:30 I will praise God's name with song and exalt Him with thanksgiving.
19Ps 69:31 That will please the LORD more than an ox, more than a bull with horns and hooves.
19Ps 69:32 The humble will see it and rejoice. You who seek God, take heart!
19Ps 69:33 For the LORD listens to the needy and does not despise His own who are prisoners.
19Ps 69:34 Let heaven and earth praise Him, the seas and everything that moves in them,
19Ps 69:35 for God will save Zion and build up the cities of Judah. They will live there and possess it.
19Ps 69:36 The descendants of His servants will inherit it, and those who love His name will live in it.
19Ps 70:1 [For the choir director. Davidic. To bring remembrance.] God, deliver me. Hurry to help me, LORD!
19Ps 70:2 Let those who seek my life be disgraced and confounded; let those who wish me harm be driven back and humiliated.
19Ps 70:3 Let those who say, "Aha, aha!" retreat because of their shame.
19Ps 70:4 Let all who seek You rejoice and be glad in You; let those who love Your salvation continually say, "God is great!"
19Ps 70:5 I am afflicted and needy; hurry to me, God. You are my help and my deliverer; LORD, do not delay.
19Ps 71:1 LORD, I seek refuge in You; never let me be disgraced.
19Ps 71:2 In Your justice, rescue and deliver me; listen closely to me and save me.
19Ps 71:3 Be a rock of refuge for me, where I can always go. Give the command to save me, for You are my rock and fortress.
19Ps 71:4 Deliver me, my God, from the hand of the wicked, from the grasp of the unjust and oppressive.
19Ps 71:5 For You are my hope, Lord God, my confidence from my youth.
19Ps 71:6 I have leaned on You from birth; You took me from my mother's womb. My praise is always about You.
19Ps 71:7 I have become an ominous sign to many, but You are my strong refuge.
19Ps 71:8 My mouth is full of praise and honor to You all day long.
19Ps 71:9 Don't discard me in my old age: as my strength fails, do not abandon me.
19Ps 71:10 For my enemies talk about me, and those who spy on me plot together,
19Ps 71:11 saying, "God has abandoned him; chase him and catch him, for there is no one to rescue [him]."
19Ps 71:12 God, do not be far from me; my God, hurry to help me.
19Ps 71:13 May my adversaries be disgraced and confounded; may those who seek my harm be covered with disgrace and humiliation.
19Ps 71:14 But I will hope continually and will praise You more and more.
19Ps 71:15 My mouth will tell about Your righteousness and Your salvation all day long, though I cannot sum them up.
19Ps 71:16 I come because of the mighty acts of the Lord God; I will proclaim Your righteousness, Yours alone.
19Ps 71:17 God, You have taught me from my youth, and I still proclaim Your wonderful works.
19Ps 71:18 Even when I am old and gray, God, do not abandon me. Then I will proclaim Your power to [another] generation, Your strength to all who are to come.
19Ps 71:19 Your righteousness reaches heaven, God, You who have done great things; God, who is like You?
19Ps 71:20 You caused me to experience many troubles and misfortunes, but You will revive me again. You will bring me up again, even from the depths of the earth.
19Ps 71:21 You will increase my honor and comfort me once again.
19Ps 71:22 Therefore, with a lute I will praise You for Your faithfulness, my God; I will sing to You with a harp, Holy One of Israel.
19Ps 71:23 My lips will shout for joy when I sing praise to You, because You have redeemed me.
19Ps 71:24 Therefore, my tongue will proclaim Your righteousness all day long, for those who seek my harm will be disgraced and confounded.
19Ps 72:1 [Solomonic.] God, give Your justice to the king and Your righteousness to the king's son.
19Ps 72:2 He will judge Your people with righteousness and Your afflicted ones with justice.
19Ps 72:3 May the mountains bring prosperity to the people, and the hills, righteousness.
19Ps 72:4 May he vindicate the afflicted among the people, help the poor, and crush the oppressor.
19Ps 72:5 May he continue while the sun endures, and as long as the moon, throughout all generations.
19Ps 72:6 May he be like rain that falls on the cut grass, like spring showers that water the earth.
19Ps 72:7 May the righteous flourish in his days, and prosperity abound until the moon is no more.
19Ps 72:8 And may he rule from sea to sea and from the Euphrates to the ends of the earth.
19Ps 72:9 May desert tribes kneel before him and his enemies lick the dust.
19Ps 72:10 May the kings of Tarshish and the coasts and islands bring tribute, the kings of Sheba and Seba offer gifts.
19Ps 72:11 And let all kings bow down to him, all nations serve him.
19Ps 72:12 For he will rescue the poor who cry out and the afflicted who have no helper.
19Ps 72:13 He will have pity on the poor and helpless and save the lives of the poor.
19Ps 72:14 He will redeem them from oppression and violence, for their lives are precious in his sight.
19Ps 72:15 May he live long! May gold from Sheba be given to him. May prayer be offered for him continually, and may he be blessed all day long.
19Ps 72:16 May there be plenty of grain in the land; may it wave on the tops of the mountains. May its crops be like Lebanon. May people flourish in the cities like the grass of the field.
19Ps 72:17 May his name endure forever; as long as the sun shines, may his fame increase. May all nations be blessed by him and call him blessed.
19Ps 72:18 May the LORD God, the God of Israel, be praised, who alone does wonders.
19Ps 72:19 May His glorious name be praised forever; the whole earth is filled with His glory. Amen and amen.
19Ps 72:20 The prayers of David son of Jesse are concluded.
19Ps 73:1 [A psalm of Asaph.] God is indeed good to Israel, to the pure in heart.
19Ps 73:2 But as for me, my feet almost slipped; my steps nearly went astray.
19Ps 73:3 For I envied the arrogant; I saw the prosperity of the wicked.
19Ps 73:4 They have an easy time until they die, and their bodies are well-fed.
19Ps 73:5 They are not in trouble like others; they are not afflicted like most people.
19Ps 73:6 Therefore, pride is their necklace, and violence covers them like a garment.
19Ps 73:7 Their eyes bulge out from fatness; the imaginations of their hearts run wild.
19Ps 73:8 They mock, and they speak maliciously; they arrogantly threaten oppression.
19Ps 73:9 They set their mouths against heaven, and their tongues strut across the earth.
19Ps 73:10 Therefore His people turn to them and drink in their overflowing waters.
19Ps 73:11 They say, "How can God know? Does the Most High know everything?"
19Ps 73:12 Look at them-- the wicked! They are always at ease, and they increase their wealth.
19Ps 73:13 Did I purify my heart and wash my hands in innocence for nothing?
19Ps 73:14 For I am afflicted all day long, and punished every morning.
19Ps 73:15 If I had decided to say these things [aloud], I would have betrayed Your people.
19Ps 73:16 When I tried to understand all this, it seemed hopeless
19Ps 73:17 until I entered God's sanctuary. Then I understood their destiny.
19Ps 73:18 Indeed You put them in slippery places; You make them fall into ruin.
19Ps 73:19 How suddenly they become a desolation! They come to an end, swept away by terrors.
19Ps 73:20 Like one waking from a dream, Lord, when arising, You will despise their image.
19Ps 73:21 When I became embittered and my innermost being was wounded,
19Ps 73:22 I was a fool and didn't understand; I was an unthinking animal toward You.
19Ps 73:23 Yet I am always with You; You hold my right hand.
19Ps 73:24 You guide me with Your counsel, and afterwards You will take me up in glory.
19Ps 73:25 Whom do I have in heaven but You? And I desire nothing on earth but You.
19Ps 73:26 My flesh and my heart may fail, but God is the strength of my heart, my portion forever.
19Ps 73:27 Those far from You will certainly perish; You destroy all who are unfaithful to You.
19Ps 73:28 But as for me, God's presence is my good. I have made the Lord God my refuge, so I can tell about all You do.
19Ps 74:1 [A Maskil of Asaph.] Why have You rejected [us] forever, God? Why does Your anger burn against the sheep of Your pasture?
19Ps 74:2 Remember Your congregation, which You purchased long ago and redeemed as the tribe for Your own possession. [Remember] Mount Zion where You dwell.
19Ps 74:3 Make Your way to the everlasting ruins, to all that the enemy has destroyed in the sanctuary.
19Ps 74:4 Your adversaries roared in the meeting place where You met with us. They set up their emblems as signs.
19Ps 74:5 It was like men in a thicket of trees, wielding axes,
19Ps 74:6 then smashing all the carvings with hatchets and picks.
19Ps 74:7 They set Your sanctuary on fire; they utterly desecrated the dwelling place of Your name.
19Ps 74:8 They said in their hearts, "Let us oppress them relentlessly." They burned down every place throughout the land where God met with us.
19Ps 74:9 We don't see any signs for us. There is no longer a prophet. And none of us knows how long this will last.
19Ps 74:10 God, how long will the foe mock? Will the enemy insult Your name forever?
19Ps 74:11 Why do You hold back Your hand? Stretch out Your right hand and destroy [them]!
19Ps 74:12 God my king is from ancient times, performing saving acts on the earth.
19Ps 74:13 You divided the sea with Your strength; You smashed the heads of the sea monsters in the waters;
19Ps 74:14 You crushed the heads of Leviathan; You fed him to the creatures of the desert.
19Ps 74:15 You opened up springs and streams; You dried up ever-flowing rivers.
19Ps 74:16 The day is Yours, also the night; You established the moon and the sun.
19Ps 74:17 You set all the boundaries of the earth; You made summer and winter.
19Ps 74:18 Remember this: the enemy has mocked the LORD, and a foolish people has insulted Your name.
19Ps 74:19 Do not give the life of Your dove to beasts; do not forget the lives of Your poor people forever.
19Ps 74:20 Consider the covenant, for the dark places of the land are full of violence.
19Ps 74:21 Do not let the oppressed turn away in shame; let the poor and needy praise Your name.
19Ps 74:22 Arise, God, defend Your cause! Remember the insults that fools bring against You all day long.
19Ps 74:23 Do not forget the clamor of Your adversaries, the tumult of Your opponents that goes up constantly.
19Ps 75:1 [For the choir director: "Do Not Destroy." A psalm of Asaph. A song.] We give thanks to You, God; we give thanks to You, for Your name is near. People tell about Your wonderful works.
19Ps 75:2 "When I choose a time, I will judge fairly.
19Ps 75:3 When the earth and all its inhabitants shake, I am the One who steadies its pillars. Selah
19Ps 75:4 I say to the boastful, 'Do not boast,' and to the wicked, 'Do not lift up your horn.
19Ps 75:5 Do not lift up your horn against heaven or speak arrogantly.'"
19Ps 75:6 Exaltation does not come from the east, the west, or the desert,
19Ps 75:7 for God is the judge: He brings down one and exalts another.
19Ps 75:8 For there is a cup in the LORD's hand, full of wine blended with spices, and He pours from it. All the wicked of the earth will drink, draining it to the dregs.
19Ps 75:9 As for me, I will tell about Him forever; I will sing praise to the God of Jacob.
19Ps 75:10 "I will cut off all the horns of the wicked, but the horns of the righteous will be lifted up."
19Ps 76:1 [For the choir director: with stringed instruments. A psalm of Asaph. A song.] God is known in Judah; His name is great in Israel.
19Ps 76:2 His tent is in Salem, His dwelling place in Zion.
19Ps 76:3 There He shatters the bow's flaming arrows, the shield, the sword, and the weapons of war. Selah
19Ps 76:4 You are resplendent and majestic [coming down] from the mountains of prey.
19Ps 76:5 The brave-hearted have been plundered; they have slipped into their [final] sleep. None of the warriors was able to lift a hand.
19Ps 76:6 At Your rebuke, God of Jacob, both chariot and horse lay still.
19Ps 76:7 And You-- You are to be feared. When You are angry, who can stand before You?
19Ps 76:8 From heaven You pronounced judgment. The earth feared and grew quiet
19Ps 76:9 when God rose up to judge and to save all the lowly of the earth. Selah
19Ps 76:10 Even human wrath will praise You; You will clothe Yourself with their remaining wrath.
19Ps 76:11 Make and keep your vows to the LORD your God; let all who are around Him bring tribute to the awe-inspiring One.
19Ps 76:12 He humbles the spirit of leaders; He is feared by the kings of the earth.
19Ps 77:1 [For the choir director: according to Jeduthun. Of Asaph. A psalm.] I cry aloud to God, aloud to God, and He will hear me.
19Ps 77:2 In my day of trouble I sought the Lord. My hands were lifted up all night long; I refused to be comforted.
19Ps 77:3 I think of God; I groan; I meditate; my spirit becomes weak. Selah
19Ps 77:4 You have kept me from closing my eyes; I am troubled and cannot speak.
19Ps 77:5 I consider days of old, years long past.
19Ps 77:6 At night I remember my music; I meditate in my heart, and my spirit ponders.
19Ps 77:7 "Will the Lord reject forever and never again show favor?
19Ps 77:8 Has His faithful love ceased forever? Is [His] promise at an end for all generations?
19Ps 77:9 Has God forgotten to be gracious? Has He in anger withheld His compassion?" Selah
19Ps 77:10 So I say, "It is my sorrow that the right hand of the Most High has changed."
19Ps 77:11 I will remember the LORD's works; yes, I will remember Your ancient wonders.
19Ps 77:12 I will reflect on all You have done and meditate on Your actions.
19Ps 77:13 God, Your way is holy. What god is great like God?
19Ps 77:14 You are the God who works wonders; You revealed Your strength among the peoples.
19Ps 77:15 With power You redeemed Your people, the descendants of Jacob and Joseph. Selah
19Ps 77:16 The waters saw You, God. The waters saw You; they trembled. Even the depths shook.
19Ps 77:17 The clouds poured down water. The storm clouds thundered; Your arrows flashed back and forth.
19Ps 77:18 The sound of Your thunder was in the whirlwind; lightning lit up the world. The earth shook and quaked.
19Ps 77:19 Your way went through the sea, and Your path through the great waters, but Your footprints were unseen.
19Ps 77:20 You led Your people like a flock by the hand of Moses and Aaron.
19Ps 78:1 [A Maskil of Asaph.] My people, hear my instruction; listen to what I say.
19Ps 78:2 I will declare wise sayings; I will speak mysteries from the past--
19Ps 78:3 things we have heard and known and that our fathers have passed down to us.
19Ps 78:4 We must not hide them from their children, but must tell a future generation the praises of the LORD, His might, and the wonderful works He has performed.
19Ps 78:5 He established a testimony in Jacob and set up a law in Israel, which He commanded our fathers to teach to their children
19Ps 78:6 so that a future generation-- children yet to be born-- might know. They were to rise and tell their children
19Ps 78:7 so that they might put their confidence in God and not forget God's works, but keep His commandments.
19Ps 78:8 Then they would not be like their fathers, a stubborn and rebellious generation, a generation whose heart was not loyal and whose spirit was not faithful to God.
19Ps 78:9 The Ephraimite archers turned back on the day of battle.
19Ps 78:10 They did not keep God's covenant and refused to live by His law.
19Ps 78:11 They forgot what He had done, the wonderful works He had shown them.
19Ps 78:12 He worked wonders in the sight of their fathers, in the land of Egypt, the region of Zoan.
19Ps 78:13 He split the sea and brought them across; the water stood firm like a wall.
19Ps 78:14 He led them with a cloud by day and with a fiery light throughout the night.
19Ps 78:15 He split rocks in the wilderness and gave them drink as abundant as the depths.
19Ps 78:16 He brought streams out of the stone and made water flow down like rivers.
19Ps 78:17 But they continued to sin against Him, rebelling in the desert against the Most High.
19Ps 78:18 They deliberately tested God, demanding the food they craved.
19Ps 78:19 They spoke against God, saying, "Is God able to provide food in the wilderness?
19Ps 78:20 Look! He struck the rock and water gushed out; torrents overflowed. But can He also provide bread or furnish meat for His people?"
19Ps 78:21 Therefore, the LORD heard and became furious; then fire broke out against Jacob, and anger flared up against Israel
19Ps 78:22 because they did not believe God or rely on His salvation.
19Ps 78:23 He gave a command to the clouds above and opened the doors of heaven.
19Ps 78:24 He rained manna for them to eat; He gave them grain from heaven.
19Ps 78:25 People ate the bread of angels. He sent them an abundant supply of food.
19Ps 78:26 He made the east wind blow in the skies and drove the south wind by His might.
19Ps 78:27 He rained meat on them like dust, and winged birds like the sand of the seas.
19Ps 78:28 He made [them] fall in His camp, all around His tent.
19Ps 78:29 They ate and were completely satisfied, for He gave them what they craved.
19Ps 78:30 Before they had satisfied their desire, while the food was still in their mouths,
19Ps 78:31 God's anger flared up against them, and He killed some of their best men. He struck down Israel's choice young men.
19Ps 78:32 Despite all this, they kept sinning and did not believe His wonderful works.
19Ps 78:33 He made their days end in futility, their years in sudden disaster.
19Ps 78:34 When He killed [some of] them, [the rest] began to seek Him; they repented and searched for God.
19Ps 78:35 They remembered that God was their rock, the Most High God, their Redeemer.
19Ps 78:36 But they deceived Him with their mouths, they lied to Him with their tongues,
19Ps 78:37 their hearts were insincere toward Him, and they were unfaithful to His covenant.
19Ps 78:38 Yet He was compassionate; He atoned for [their] guilt and did not destroy [them]. He often turned His anger aside and did not unleash all His wrath.
19Ps 78:39 He remembered that they were [only] flesh, a wind that passes and does not return.
19Ps 78:40 How often they rebelled against Him in the wilderness and grieved Him in the desert.
19Ps 78:41 They constantly tested God and provoked the Holy One of Israel.
19Ps 78:42 They did not remember His power [shown] on the day He redeemed them from the foe,
19Ps 78:43 when He performed His miraculous signs in Egypt and His marvels in the region of Zoan.
19Ps 78:44 He turned their rivers into blood, and they could not drink from their streams.
19Ps 78:45 He sent among them swarms of flies, which fed on them, and frogs, which devastated them.
19Ps 78:46 He gave their crops to the caterpillar and the fruit of their labor to the locust.
19Ps 78:47 He killed their vines with hail and their sycamore-fig trees with a flood.
19Ps 78:48 He handed over their livestock to hail and their cattle to lightning bolts.
19Ps 78:49 He sent His burning anger against them: fury, indignation, and calamity-- a band of deadly messengers.
19Ps 78:50 He cleared a path for His anger. He did not spare them from death, but delivered their lives to the plague.
19Ps 78:51 He struck all the firstborn in Egypt, the first progeny of the tents of Ham.
19Ps 78:52 He led His people out like sheep and guided them like a flock in the wilderness.
19Ps 78:53 He led them safely, and they were not afraid; but the sea covered their enemies.
19Ps 78:54 He brought them to His holy land, to the mountain His right hand acquired.
19Ps 78:55 He drove out nations before them. He apportioned their inheritance by lot and settled the tribes of Israel in their tents.
19Ps 78:56 But they rebelliously tested the Most High God, for they did not keep His decrees.
19Ps 78:57 They treacherously turned away like their fathers; they became warped like a faulty bow.
19Ps 78:58 They enraged Him with their high places and provoked His jealousy with their carved images.
19Ps 78:59 God heard and became furious; He completely rejected Israel.
19Ps 78:60 He abandoned the tabernacle at Shiloh, the tent where He resided among men.
19Ps 78:61 He gave up His strength to captivity and His splendor to the hand of a foe.
19Ps 78:62 He surrendered His people to the sword because He was enraged with His heritage.
19Ps 78:63 Fire consumed His chosen young men, and His young women had no wedding songs.
19Ps 78:64 His priests fell by the sword, but the widows could not lament.
19Ps 78:65 Then the Lord awoke as if from sleep, like a warrior from the effects of wine.
19Ps 78:66 He beat back His foes; He gave them lasting shame.
19Ps 78:67 He rejected the tent of Joseph and did not choose the tribe of Ephraim.
19Ps 78:68 He chose instead the tribe of Judah, Mount Zion, which He loved.
19Ps 78:69 He built His sanctuary like the heights, like the earth that He established forever.
19Ps 78:70 He chose David His servant and took him from the sheepfolds;
19Ps 78:71 He brought him from tending ewes to be shepherd over His people Jacob-- over Israel, His inheritance.
19Ps 78:72 He shepherded them with a pure heart and guided them with his skillful hands.
19Ps 79:1 [A psalm of Asaph.] God, the nations have invaded Your inheritance, desecrated Your holy temple, and turned Jerusalem into ruins.
19Ps 79:2 They gave the corpses of Your servants to the birds of the sky for food, the flesh of Your godly ones to the beasts of the earth.
19Ps 79:3 They poured out their blood like water all around Jerusalem, and there was no one to bury [them].
19Ps 79:4 We have become an object of reproach to our neighbors, a source of mockery and ridicule to those around us.
19Ps 79:5 How long, LORD? Will You be angry forever? Will Your jealousy keep burning like fire?
19Ps 79:6 Pour out Your wrath on the nations that don't acknowledge You, on the kingdoms that don't call on Your name,
19Ps 79:7 for they have devoured Jacob and devastated his homeland.
19Ps 79:8 Do not hold past sins against us; let Your compassion come to us quickly, for we have become weak.
19Ps 79:9 God of our salvation, help us-- for the glory of Your name. Deliver us and atone for our sins, because of Your name.
19Ps 79:10 Why should the nations ask, "Where is their God?" Before our eyes, let vengeance for the shed blood of Your servants be known among the nations.
19Ps 79:11 Let the groans of the prisoners reach You; according to Your great power, preserve those condemned to die.
19Ps 79:12 Pay back sevenfold to our neighbors the reproach they have hurled at You, Lord.
19Ps 79:13 Then we, Your people, the sheep of Your pasture, will thank You forever; we will declare Your praise to generation after generation.
19Ps 80:1 [For the choir director: according to "The Lilies." A testimony of Asaph. A psalm.] Listen, Shepherd of Israel, who guides Joseph like a flock; You who sit enthroned [on] the cherubim, rise up
19Ps 80:2 at the head of Ephraim, Benjamin, and Manasseh. Rally Your power and come to save us.
19Ps 80:3 Restore us, God; look [on us] with favor, and we will be saved.
19Ps 80:4 LORD God of Hosts, how long will You be angry with Your people's prayers?
19Ps 80:5 You fed them the bread of tears and gave them a full measure of tears to drink.
19Ps 80:6 You set us at strife with our neighbors; our enemies make fun of us.
19Ps 80:7 Restore us, God of Hosts; look [on us] with favor, and we will be saved.
19Ps 80:8 You uprooted a vine from Egypt; You drove out the nations and planted it.
19Ps 80:9 You cleared [a place] for it; it took root and filled the land.
19Ps 80:10 The mountains were covered by its shade, and the mighty cedars with its branches.
19Ps 80:11 It sent out sprouts toward the Sea and shoots toward the River.
19Ps 80:12 Why have You broken down its walls so that all who pass by pick its fruit?
19Ps 80:13 The boar from the forest gnaws at it, and creatures of the field feed on it.
19Ps 80:14 Return, God of Hosts. Look down from heaven and see; take care of this vine,
19Ps 80:15 the root Your right hand has planted, the shoot that You made strong for Yourself.
19Ps 80:16 It was cut down and burned up; they perish at the rebuke of Your countenance.
19Ps 80:17 Let Your hand be with the man at Your right hand, with the son of man You have made strong for Yourself.
19Ps 80:18 Then we will not turn away from You; revive us, and we will call on Your name.
19Ps 80:19 Restore us, LORD God of Hosts; look [on us] with favor, and we will be saved.
19Ps 81:1 [For the choir director: on the Gittith. Of Asaph.] Sing for joy to God our strength; shout in triumph to the God of Jacob.
19Ps 81:2 Lift up a song-- play the tambourine, the melodious lyre, and the harp.
19Ps 81:3 Blow the horn during the new moon and during the full moon, on the day of our feast.
19Ps 81:4 For this is a statute for Israel, a judgment of the God of Jacob.
19Ps 81:5 He set it up as an ordinance for Joseph when He went throughout the land of Egypt. I heard an unfamiliar language:
19Ps 81:6 "I relieved his shoulder from the burden; his hands were freed from [carrying] the basket.
19Ps 81:7 You called out in distress, and I rescued you; I answered you from the thundercloud. I tested you at the waters of Meribah. Selah
19Ps 81:8 Listen, My people, and I will admonish you. Israel, if you would only listen to Me!
19Ps 81:9 There must not be a strange god among you; you must not bow down to a foreign god.
19Ps 81:10 I am Yahweh your God, who brought you up from the land of Egypt. Open your mouth wide, and I will fill it.
19Ps 81:11 "But My people did not listen to Me; Israel did not obey Me.
19Ps 81:12 So I gave them over to their stubborn hearts to follow their own plans.
19Ps 81:13 If only My people would listen to Me and Israel would follow My ways,
19Ps 81:14 I would quickly subdue their enemies and turn My hand against their foes."
19Ps 81:15 Those who hate the LORD would pretend submission to Him; their doom would last forever.
19Ps 81:16 But He would feed Israel with the best wheat. "I would satisfy you with honey from the rock."
19Ps 82:1 [A psalm of Asaph.] God has taken His place in the divine assembly; He judges among the gods:
19Ps 82:2 "How long will you judge unjustly and show partiality to the wicked? Selah
19Ps 82:3 Provide justice for the needy and the fatherless; uphold the rights of the oppressed and the destitute.
19Ps 82:4 Rescue the poor and needy; save them from the hand of the wicked."
19Ps 82:5 They do not know or understand; they wander in darkness. All the foundations of the earth are shaken.
19Ps 82:6 I said, "You are gods; you are all sons of the Most High.
19Ps 82:7 However, you will die like men and fall like any other ruler."
19Ps 82:8 Rise up, God, judge the earth, for all the nations belong to You.
19Ps 83:1 [A song. A psalm of Asaph.] God, do not keep silent. Do not be deaf, God; do not be idle.
19Ps 83:2 See how Your enemies make an uproar; those who hate You have acted arrogantly.
19Ps 83:3 They devise clever schemes against Your people; they conspire against Your treasured ones.
19Ps 83:4 They say, "Come, let us wipe them out as a nation so that Israel's name will no longer be remembered."
19Ps 83:5 For they have conspired with one mind; they form an alliance against You--
19Ps 83:6 the tents of Edom and the Ishmaelites, Moab and the Hagrites,
19Ps 83:7 Gebal, Ammon, and Amalek, Philistia with the inhabitants of Tyre.
19Ps 83:8 Even Assyria has joined them; they lend support to the sons of Lot. Selah
19Ps 83:9 Deal with them as [You did] with Midian, as [You did] with Sisera and Jabin at the Kishon River.
19Ps 83:10 They were destroyed at En-dor; they became manure for the ground.
19Ps 83:11 Make their nobles like Oreb and Zeeb, and all their tribal leaders like Zebah and Zalmunna,
19Ps 83:12 who said, "Let us seize God's pastures for ourselves."
19Ps 83:13 Make them like tumbleweed, my God, like straw before the wind.
19Ps 83:14 As fire burns a forest, as a flame blazes through mountains,
19Ps 83:15 so pursue them with Your tempest and terrify them with Your storm.
19Ps 83:16 Cover their faces with shame so that they will seek Your name, LORD.
19Ps 83:17 Let them be put to shame and terrified forever; let them perish in disgrace.
19Ps 83:18 May they know that You alone-- whose name is Yahweh-- are the Most High over all the earth.
19Ps 84:1 [For the choir director: on the Gittith. A psalm of the sons of Korah.] How lovely is Your dwelling place, LORD of Hosts.
19Ps 84:2 I long and yearn for the courts of the LORD; my heart and flesh cry out for the living God.
19Ps 84:3 Even a sparrow finds a home, and a swallow, a nest for herself where she places her young-- near Your altars, LORD of Hosts, my King and my God.
19Ps 84:4 How happy are those who reside in Your house, who praise You continually. Selah
19Ps 84:5 Happy are the people whose strength is in You, whose hearts are set on pilgrimage.
19Ps 84:6 As they pass through the Valley of Baca, they make it a source of springwater; even the autumn rain will cover it with blessings.
19Ps 84:7 They go from strength to strength; each appears before God in Zion.
19Ps 84:8 LORD God of Hosts, hear my prayer; listen, God of Jacob. Selah
19Ps 84:9 Consider our shield, God; look on the face of Your anointed one.
19Ps 84:10 Better a day in Your courts than a thousand [anywhere else]. I would rather be at the door of the house of my God than to live in the tents of the wicked.
19Ps 84:11 For the LORD God is a sun and shield. The LORD gives grace and glory; He does not withhold the good from those who live with integrity.
19Ps 84:12 LORD of Hosts, happy is the person who trusts in You!
19Ps 85:1 [For the choir director. A psalm of the sons of Korah.] LORD, You showed favor to Your land; You restored Jacob's prosperity.
19Ps 85:2 You took away Your people's guilt; You covered all their sin. Selah
19Ps 85:3 You withdrew all Your fury; You turned from Your burning anger.
19Ps 85:4 Return to us, God of our salvation, and abandon Your displeasure with us.
19Ps 85:5 Will You be angry with us forever? Will You prolong Your anger for all generations?
19Ps 85:6 Will You not revive us again so that Your people may rejoice in You?
19Ps 85:7 Show us Your faithful love, LORD, and give us Your salvation.
19Ps 85:8 I will listen to what God will say; surely the LORD will declare peace to His people, His godly ones, and not let them go back to foolish ways.
19Ps 85:9 His salvation is very near those who fear Him, so that glory may dwell in our land.
19Ps 85:10 Faithful love and truth will join together; righteousness and peace will embrace.
19Ps 85:11 Truth will spring up from the earth, and righteousness will look down from heaven.
19Ps 85:12 Also, the LORD will provide what is good, and our land will yield its crops.
19Ps 85:13 Righteousness will go before Him to prepare the way for His steps.
19Ps 86:1 [A Davidic prayer.] Listen, LORD, and answer me, for I am poor and needy.
19Ps 86:2 Protect my life, for I am faithful. You are my God; save Your servant who trusts in You.
19Ps 86:3 Be gracious to me, Lord, for I call to You all day long.
19Ps 86:4 Bring joy to Your servant's life, since I set my hope on You, Lord.
19Ps 86:5 For You, Lord, are kind and ready to forgive, abundant in faithful love to all who call on You.
19Ps 86:6 LORD, hear my prayer; listen to my plea for mercy.
19Ps 86:7 I call on You in the day of my distress, for You will answer me.
19Ps 86:8 Lord, there is no one like You among the gods, and there are no works like Yours.
19Ps 86:9 All the nations You have made will come and bow down before You, Lord, and will honor Your name.
19Ps 86:10 For You are great and perform wonders; You alone are God.
19Ps 86:11 Teach me Your way, LORD, and I will live by Your truth. Give me an undivided mind to fear Your name.
19Ps 86:12 I will praise You with all my heart, Lord my God, and will honor Your name forever.
19Ps 86:13 For Your faithful love for me is great, and You deliver my life from the depths of Sheol.
19Ps 86:14 God, arrogant people have attacked me; a gang of ruthless men seeks my life. They have no regard for You.
19Ps 86:15 But You, Lord, are a compassionate and gracious God, slow to anger and abundant in faithful love and truth.
19Ps 86:16 Turn to me and be gracious to me. Give Your strength to Your servant; save the son of Your female servant.
19Ps 86:17 Show me a sign of Your goodness; my enemies will see and be put to shame because You, LORD, have helped and comforted me.
19Ps 87:1 [A psalm of the sons of Korah. A song.] His foundation is on the holy mountains.
19Ps 87:2 The LORD loves the gates of Zion more than all the dwellings of Jacob.
19Ps 87:3 Glorious things are said about you, city of God. Selah
19Ps 87:4 "I will mention those who know Me: Rahab, Babylon, Philistia, Tyre, and Cush-- each one was born there."
19Ps 87:5 And it will be said of Zion, "This one and that one were born in her." The Most High Himself will establish her.
19Ps 87:6 When He registers the peoples, the LORD will record, "This one was born there." Selah
19Ps 87:7 Singers and dancers alike [will say], "All my springs are in you."
19Ps 88:1 [A song. A psalm of the sons of Korah. For the choir director: according to Mahalath Leannoth. A Maskil of Heman the Ezrahite.] LORD, God of my salvation, I cry out before You day and night.
19Ps 88:2 May my prayer reach Your presence; listen to my cry.
19Ps 88:3 For I have had enough troubles, and my life is near Sheol.
19Ps 88:4 I am counted among those going down to the Pit. I am like a man without strength,
19Ps 88:5 abandoned among the dead. I am like the slain lying in the grave, whom You no longer remember, and who are cut off from Your care.
19Ps 88:6 You have put me in the lowest part of the Pit, in the darkest places, in the depths.
19Ps 88:7 Your wrath weighs heavily on me; You have overwhelmed me with all Your waves. Selah
19Ps 88:8 You have distanced my friends from me; You have made me repulsive to them. I am shut in and cannot go out.
19Ps 88:9 My eyes are worn out from crying. LORD, I cry out to You all day long; I spread out my hands to You.
19Ps 88:10 Do You work wonders for the dead? Do departed spirits rise up to praise You? Selah
19Ps 88:11 Will Your faithful love be declared in the grave, Your faithfulness in Abaddon?
19Ps 88:12 Will Your wonders be known in the darkness, or Your righteousness in the land of oblivion?
19Ps 88:13 But I call to You for help, LORD; in the morning my prayer meets You.
19Ps 88:14 LORD, why do You reject me? Why do You hide Your face from me?
19Ps 88:15 From my youth, I have been afflicted and near death. I suffer Your horrors; I am desperate.
19Ps 88:16 Your wrath sweeps over me; Your terrors destroy me.
19Ps 88:17 They surround me like water all day long; they close in on me from every side.
19Ps 88:18 You have distanced loved one and neighbor from me; darkness is my [only] friend.
19Ps 89:1 [A Maskil of Ethan the Ezrahite.] I will sing about the LORD's faithful love forever; with my mouth I will proclaim Your faithfulness to all generations.
19Ps 89:2 For I will declare, "Faithful love is built up forever; You establish Your faithfulness in the heavens."
19Ps 89:3 [The LORD said,] "I have made a covenant with My chosen one; I have sworn an oath to David My servant:
19Ps 89:4 'I will establish your offspring forever and build up your throne for all generations.' " Selah
19Ps 89:5 LORD, the heavens praise Your wonders-- Your faithfulness also-- in the assembly of the holy ones.
19Ps 89:6 For who in the skies can compare with the LORD? Who among the heavenly beings is like the LORD?
19Ps 89:7 God is greatly feared in the council of the holy ones, more awe-inspiring than all who surround Him.
19Ps 89:8 LORD God of Hosts, who is strong like You, LORD? Your faithfulness surrounds You.
19Ps 89:9 You rule the raging sea; when its waves surge, You still them.
19Ps 89:10 You crushed Rahab like one who is slain; You scattered Your enemies with Your powerful arm.
19Ps 89:11 The heavens are Yours; the earth also is Yours. The world and everything in it-- You founded them.
19Ps 89:12 North and south-- You created them. Tabor and Hermon shout for joy at Your name.
19Ps 89:13 You have a mighty arm; Your hand is powerful; Your right hand is lifted high.
19Ps 89:14 Righteousness and justice are the foundation of Your throne; faithful love and truth go before You.
19Ps 89:15 Happy are the people who know the joyful shout; LORD, they walk in the light of Your presence.
19Ps 89:16 They rejoice in Your name all day long, and they are exalted by Your righteousness.
19Ps 89:17 For You are their magnificent strength; by Your favor our horn is exalted.
19Ps 89:18 Surely our shield belongs to the LORD, our king to the Holy One of Israel.
19Ps 89:19 You once spoke in a vision to Your loyal ones and said: "I have granted help to a warrior; I have exalted one chosen from the people.
19Ps 89:20 I have found David My servant; I have anointed him with My sacred oil.
19Ps 89:21 My hand will always be with him, and My arm will strengthen him.
19Ps 89:22 The enemy will not afflict him; no wicked man will oppress him.
19Ps 89:23 I will crush his foes before him and strike those who hate him.
19Ps 89:24 My faithfulness and love will be with him, and through My name his horn will be exalted.
19Ps 89:25 I will extend his power to the sea and his right hand to the rivers.
19Ps 89:26 He will call to Me, 'You are my Father, my God, the rock of my salvation.'
19Ps 89:27 I will also make him My firstborn, greatest of the kings of the earth.
19Ps 89:28 I will always preserve My faithful love for him, and My covenant with him will endure.
19Ps 89:29 I will establish his line forever, his throne as long as heaven lasts.
19Ps 89:30 If his sons forsake My instruction and do not live by My ordinances,
19Ps 89:31 if they dishonor My statutes and do not keep My commandments,
19Ps 89:32 then I will call their rebellion to account with the rod, their sin with blows.
19Ps 89:33 But I will not withdraw My faithful love from him or betray My faithfulness.
19Ps 89:34 I will not violate My covenant or change what My lips have said.
19Ps 89:35 Once and for all I have sworn an oath by My holiness; I will not lie to David.
19Ps 89:36 His offspring will continue forever, his throne like the sun before Me,
19Ps 89:37 like the moon, established forever, a faithful witness in the sky." Selah
19Ps 89:38 But You have spurned and rejected him; You have become enraged with Your anointed.
19Ps 89:39 You have repudiated the covenant with Your servant; You have completely dishonored his crown.
19Ps 89:40 You have broken down all his walls; You have reduced his fortified cities to ruins.
19Ps 89:41 All who pass by plunder him; he has become a joke to his neighbors.
19Ps 89:42 You have lifted high the right hand of his foes; You have made all his enemies rejoice.
19Ps 89:43 You have also turned back his sharp sword and have not let him stand in battle.
19Ps 89:44 You have made his splendor cease and have overturned his throne.
19Ps 89:45 You have shortened the days of his youth; You have covered him with shame. Selah
19Ps 89:46 How long, LORD? Will You hide Yourself forever? Will Your anger keep burning like fire?
19Ps 89:47 Remember how short my life is. Have You created everyone for nothing?
19Ps 89:48 What man can live and never see death? Who can save himself from the power of Sheol? Selah
19Ps 89:49 Lord, where are the former acts of Your faithful love that You swore to David in Your faithfulness?
19Ps 89:50 Remember, Lord, the ridicule against Your servants-- in my heart I carry [abuse] from all the peoples--
19Ps 89:51 how Your enemies have ridiculed, LORD, how they have ridiculed every step of Your anointed.
19Ps 89:52 May the LORD be praised forever. Amen and amen.
19Ps 90:1 [A prayer of Moses the man of God.] Lord, You have been our refuge in every generation.
19Ps 90:2 Before the mountains were born, before You gave birth to the earth and the world, from eternity to eternity, You are God.
19Ps 90:3 You return mankind to the dust, saying, "Return, descendants of Adam."
19Ps 90:4 For in Your sight a thousand years are like yesterday that passes by, like a few hours of the night.
19Ps 90:5 You end their life; they sleep. They are like grass that grows in the morning--
19Ps 90:6 in the morning it sprouts and grows; by evening it withers and dries up.
19Ps 90:7 For we are consumed by Your anger; we are terrified by Your wrath.
19Ps 90:8 You have set our unjust ways before You, our secret sins in the light of Your presence.
19Ps 90:9 For all our days ebb away under Your wrath; we end our years like a sigh.
19Ps 90:10 Our lives last seventy years or, if we are strong, eighty years. Even the best of them are struggle and sorrow; indeed, they pass quickly and we fly away.
19Ps 90:11 Who understands the power of Your anger? Your wrath matches the fear that is due You.
19Ps 90:12 Teach us to number our days carefully so that we may develop wisdom in our hearts.
19Ps 90:13 Lord-- how long? Turn and have compassion on Your servants.
19Ps 90:14 Satisfy us in the morning with Your faithful love so that we may shout with joy and be glad all our days.
19Ps 90:15 Make us rejoice for as many days as You have humbled us, for as many years as we have seen adversity.
19Ps 90:16 Let Your work be seen by Your servants, and Your splendor by their children.
19Ps 90:17 Let the favor of the Lord our God be on us; establish for us the work of our hands-- establish the work of our hands!
19Ps 91:1 The one who lives under the protection of the Most High dwells in the shadow of the Almighty.
19Ps 91:2 I will say to the LORD, "My refuge and my fortress, my God, in whom I trust."
19Ps 91:3 He Himself will deliver you from the hunter's net, from the destructive plague.
19Ps 91:4 He will cover you with His feathers; you will take refuge under His wings. His faithfulness will be a protective shield.
19Ps 91:5 You will not fear the terror of the night, the arrow that flies by day,
19Ps 91:6 the plague that stalks in darkness, or the pestilence that ravages at noon.
19Ps 91:7 Though a thousand fall at your side and ten thousand at your right hand, the pestilence will not reach you.
19Ps 91:8 You will only see it with your eyes and witness the punishment of the wicked.
19Ps 91:9 Because you have made the Lord-- my refuge, the Most High-- your dwelling place,
19Ps 91:10 no harm will come to you; no plague will come near your tent.
19Ps 91:11 For He will give His angels orders concerning you, to protect you in all your ways.
19Ps 91:12 They will support you with their hands so that you will not strike your foot against a stone.
19Ps 91:13 You will tread on the lion and the cobra; you will trample the young lion and the serpent.
19Ps 91:14 Because he is lovingly devoted to Me, I will deliver him; I will exalt him because he knows My name.
19Ps 91:15 When he calls out to Me, I will answer him; I will be with him in trouble. I will rescue him and give him honor.
19Ps 91:16 I will satisfy him with a long life and show him My salvation.
19Ps 92:1 [A psalm. A song for the Sabbath day.] It is good to praise the LORD, to sing praise to Your name, Most High,
19Ps 92:2 to declare Your faithful love in the morning and Your faithfulness at night,
19Ps 92:3 with a ten-stringed harp and the music of a lyre.
19Ps 92:4 For You have made me rejoice, LORD, by what You have done; I will shout for joy because of the works of Your hands.
19Ps 92:5 How magnificent are Your works, LORD, how profound Your thoughts!
19Ps 92:6 A stupid person does not know, a fool does not understand this:
19Ps 92:7 though the wicked sprout like grass and all evildoers flourish, they will be eternally destroyed.
19Ps 92:8 But You, LORD, are exalted forever.
19Ps 92:9 For indeed, LORD, Your enemies-- indeed, Your enemies will perish; all evildoers will be scattered.
19Ps 92:10 You have lifted up my horn like that of a wild ox; I have been anointed with oil.
19Ps 92:11 My eyes look down on my enemies; my ears hear evildoers when they attack me.
19Ps 92:12 The righteous thrive like a palm tree and grow like a cedar tree in Lebanon.
19Ps 92:13 Planted in the house of the LORD, they thrive in the courtyards of our God.
19Ps 92:14 They will still bear fruit in old age, healthy and green,
19Ps 92:15 to declare: "The LORD is just; He is my rock, and there is no unrighteousness in Him."
19Ps 93:1 The LORD reigns! He is robed in majesty; The LORD is robed, enveloped in strength. The world is firmly established; it cannot be shaken.
19Ps 93:2 Your throne has been established from the beginning; You are from eternity.
19Ps 93:3 The floods have lifted up, LORD, the floods have lifted up their voice; the floods lift up their pounding waves.
19Ps 93:4 Greater than the roar of many waters-- the mighty breakers of the sea-- the LORD on high is majestic.
19Ps 93:5 LORD, Your testimonies are completely reliable; holiness is the beauty of Your house for all the days to come.
19Ps 94:1 LORD, God of vengeance-- God of vengeance, appear.
19Ps 94:2 Rise up, Judge of the earth; repay the proud what they deserve.
19Ps 94:3 LORD, how long will the wicked-- how long will the wicked gloat?
19Ps 94:4 They pour out arrogant words; all the evildoers boast.
19Ps 94:5 LORD, they crush Your people; they afflict Your heritage.
19Ps 94:6 They kill the widow and the foreigner and murder the fatherless.
19Ps 94:7 They say, "The LORD doesn't see it. The God of Jacob doesn't pay attention."
19Ps 94:8 Pay attention, you stupid people! Fools, when will you be wise?
19Ps 94:9 Can the One who shaped the ear not hear, the One who formed the eye not see?
19Ps 94:10 The One who instructs nations, the One who teaches man knowledge-- does He not discipline?
19Ps 94:11 The LORD knows man's thoughts; they are meaningless.
19Ps 94:12 LORD, happy is the man You discipline and teach from Your law
19Ps 94:13 to give him relief from troubled times until a pit is dug for the wicked.
19Ps 94:14 The LORD will not forsake His people or abandon His heritage,
19Ps 94:15 for justice will again be righteous, and all the upright in heart will follow it.
19Ps 94:16 Who stands up for me against the wicked? Who takes a stand for me against evildoers?
19Ps 94:17 If the LORD had not been my help, I would soon rest in the silence [of death].
19Ps 94:18 If I say, "My foot is slipping," Your faithful love will support me, LORD.
19Ps 94:19 When I am filled with cares, Your comfort brings me joy.
19Ps 94:20 Can a corrupt throne-- one that creates trouble by law-- become Your ally?
19Ps 94:21 They band together against the life of the righteous and condemn the innocent to death.
19Ps 94:22 But the LORD is my refuge; my God is the rock of my protection.
19Ps 94:23 He will pay them back for their sins and destroy them for their evil. The LORD our God will destroy them.
19Ps 95:1 Come, let us shout joyfully to the LORD, shout triumphantly to the rock of our salvation!
19Ps 95:2 Let us enter His presence with thanksgiving; let us shout triumphantly to Him in song.
19Ps 95:3 For the LORD is a great God, a great King above all gods.
19Ps 95:4 The depths of the earth are in His hand, and the mountain peaks are His.
19Ps 95:5 The sea is His; He made it. His hands formed the dry land.
19Ps 95:6 Come, let us worship and bow down; let us kneel before the LORD our Maker.
19Ps 95:7 For He is our God, and we are the people of His pasture, the sheep under His care. Today, if you hear His voice:
19Ps 95:8 "Do not harden your hearts as at Meribah, as on that day at Massah in the wilderness
19Ps 95:9 where your fathers tested Me; they tried Me, though they had seen what I did.
19Ps 95:10 For 40 years I was disgusted with that generation; I said, 'They are a people whose hearts go astray; they do not know My ways.'
19Ps 95:11 So I swore in My anger, 'They will not enter My rest.'"
19Ps 96:1 Sing a new song to the LORD; sing to the Lord, all the earth.
19Ps 96:2 Sing to the LORD, praise His name; proclaim His salvation from day to day.
19Ps 96:3 Declare His glory among the nations, His wonderful works among all peoples.
19Ps 96:4 For the LORD is great and is highly praised; He is feared above all gods.
19Ps 96:5 For all the gods of the peoples are idols, but the LORD made the heavens.
19Ps 96:6 Splendor and majesty are before Him; strength and beauty are in His sanctuary.
19Ps 96:7 Ascribe to the LORD, you families of the peoples, ascribe to the LORD glory and strength.
19Ps 96:8 Ascribe to the LORD the glory of His name; bring an offering and enter His courts.
19Ps 96:9 Worship the LORD in the splendor of [His] holiness; tremble before Him, all the earth.
19Ps 96:10 Say among the nations: "The LORD reigns. The world is firmly established; it cannot be shaken. He judges the peoples fairly."
19Ps 96:11 Let the heavens be glad and the earth rejoice; let the sea and all that fills it resound.
19Ps 96:12 Let the fields and everything in them exult. Then all the trees of the forest will shout for joy
19Ps 96:13 before the LORD, for He is coming-- for He is coming to judge the earth. He will judge the world with righteousness and the peoples with His faithfulness.
19Ps 97:1 The LORD reigns! Let the earth rejoice; let the many coasts and islands be glad.
19Ps 97:2 Clouds and thick darkness surround Him; righteousness and justice are the foundation of His throne.
19Ps 97:3 Fire goes before Him and burns up His foes on every side.
19Ps 97:4 His lightning lights up the world; the earth sees and trembles.
19Ps 97:5 The mountains melt like wax at the presence of the LORD-- at the presence of the Lord of all the earth.
19Ps 97:6 The heavens proclaim His righteousness; all the peoples see His glory.
19Ps 97:7 All who serve carved images, those who boast in idols, will be put to shame. All the gods must worship Him.
19Ps 97:8 Zion hears and is glad, and the towns of Judah rejoice because of Your judgments, LORD.
19Ps 97:9 For You, LORD, are the Most High over all the earth; You are exalted above all the gods.
19Ps 97:10 You who love the Lord, hate evil! He protects the lives of His godly ones; He rescues them from the hand of the wicked.
19Ps 97:11 Light dawns for the righteous, gladness for the upright in heart.
19Ps 97:12 Be glad in the LORD, you righteous ones, and praise His holy name.
19Ps 98:1 [A psalm.] Sing a new song to the LORD, for He has performed wonders; His right hand and holy arm have won Him victory.
19Ps 98:2 The LORD has made His victory known; He has revealed His righteousness in the sight of the nations.
19Ps 98:3 He has remembered His love and faithfulness to the house of Israel; all the ends of the earth have seen our God's victory.
19Ps 98:4 Shout to the LORD, all the earth; be jubilant, shout for joy, and sing.
19Ps 98:5 Sing to the LORD with the lyre, with the lyre and melodious song.
19Ps 98:6 With trumpets and the blast of the ram's horn shout triumphantly in the presence of the LORD, our King.
19Ps 98:7 Let the sea and all that fills it, the world and those who live in it, resound.
19Ps 98:8 Let the rivers clap their hands; let the mountains shout together for joy
19Ps 98:9 before the LORD, for He is coming to judge the earth. He will judge the world righteously and the peoples fairly.
19Ps 99:1 The LORD reigns! Let the peoples tremble. He is enthroned above the cherubim. Let the earth quake.
19Ps 99:2 The LORD is great in Zion; He is exalted above all the peoples.
19Ps 99:3 Let them praise Your great and awe-inspiring name. He is holy.
19Ps 99:4 The mighty King loves justice. You have established fairness; You have administered justice and righteousness in Jacob.
19Ps 99:5 Exalt the LORD our God; bow in worship at His footstool. He is holy.
19Ps 99:6 Moses and Aaron were among His priests; Samuel also was among those calling on His name. They called to the Lord, and He answered them.
19Ps 99:7 He spoke to them in a pillar of cloud; they kept His decrees and the statutes He gave them.
19Ps 99:8 LORD our God, You answered them. You were a God who forgave them, but punished their misdeeds.
19Ps 99:9 Exalt the LORD our God; bow in worship at His holy mountain, for the LORD our God is holy.
19Ps 100:1 [A psalm of thanksgiving.] Shout triumphantly to the LORD, all the earth.
19Ps 100:2 Serve the LORD with gladness; come before Him with joyful songs.
19Ps 100:3 Acknowledge that the LORD is God. He made us, and we are His-- His people, the sheep of His pasture.
19Ps 100:4 Enter His gates with thanksgiving and His courts with praise. Give thanks to Him and praise His name.
19Ps 100:5 For the LORD is good, and His love is eternal; His faithfulness endures through all generations.
19Ps 101:1 [A Davidic psalm.] I will sing of faithful love and justice; I will sing praise to You, LORD.
19Ps 101:2 I will pay attention to the way of integrity. When will You come to me? I will live with integrity of heart in my house.
19Ps 101:3 I will not set anything godless before my eyes. I hate the doing of transgression; it will not cling to me.
19Ps 101:4 A devious heart will be far from me; I will not be involved with evil.
19Ps 101:5 I will destroy anyone who secretly slanders his neighbor; I cannot tolerate anyone with haughty eyes or an arrogant heart.
19Ps 101:6 My eyes [favor] the faithful of the land so that they may sit down with me. The one who follows the way of integrity may serve me.
19Ps 101:7 No one who acts deceitfully will live in my palace; no one who tells lies will remain in my presence.
19Ps 101:8 Every morning I will destroy all the wicked of the land, eliminating all evildoers from the LORD's city.
19Ps 102:1 [A prayer of an afflicted person who is weak and pours out his lament before the Lord.] LORD, hear my prayer; let my cry for help come before You.
19Ps 102:2 Do not hide Your face from me in my day of trouble. Listen closely to me; answer me quickly when I call.
19Ps 102:3 For my days vanish like smoke, and my bones burn like a furnace.
19Ps 102:4 My heart is afflicted, withered like grass; I even forget to eat my food.
19Ps 102:5 Because of the sound of my groaning, my flesh sticks to my bones.
19Ps 102:6 I am like a desert owl, like an owl among the ruins.
19Ps 102:7 I stay awake; I am like a solitary bird on a roof.
19Ps 102:8 My enemies taunt me all day long; they ridicule and curse me.
19Ps 102:9 I eat ashes like bread and mingle my drinks with tears
19Ps 102:10 because of Your indignation and wrath; for You have picked me up and thrown me aside.
19Ps 102:11 My days are like a lengthening shadow, and I wither away like grass.
19Ps 102:12 But You, LORD, are enthroned forever; Your fame [endures] to all generations.
19Ps 102:13 You will arise and have compassion on Zion, for it is time to show favor to her-- the appointed time has come.
19Ps 102:14 For Your servants take delight in its stones and favor its dust.
19Ps 102:15 Then the nations will fear the name of the LORD, and all the kings of the earth Your glory,
19Ps 102:16 for the LORD will rebuild Zion; He will appear in His glory.
19Ps 102:17 He will pay attention to the prayer of the destitute and will not despise their prayer.
19Ps 102:18 This will be written for a later generation, and a newly created people will praise the LORD:
19Ps 102:19 He looked down from His holy heights-- the LORD gazed out from heaven to earth--
19Ps 102:20 to hear a prisoner's groaning, to set free those condemned to die,
19Ps 102:21 so that they might declare the name of the LORD in Zion and His praise in Jerusalem,
19Ps 102:22 when peoples and kingdoms are assembled to serve the LORD.
19Ps 102:23 He has broken my strength in midcourse; He has shortened my days.
19Ps 102:24 I say: "My God, do not take me in the middle of my life! Your years continue through all generations.
19Ps 102:25 Long ago You established the earth, and the heavens are the work of Your hands.
19Ps 102:26 They will perish, but You will endure; all of them will wear out like clothing. You will change them like a garment, and they will pass away.
19Ps 102:27 But You are the same, and Your years will never end.
19Ps 102:28 Your servants' children will dwell [securely], and their offspring will be established before You."
19Ps 103:1 [Davidic.] My soul, praise the LORD, and all that is within me, praise His holy name.
19Ps 103:2 My soul, praise the LORD, and do not forget all His benefits.
19Ps 103:3 He forgives all your sin; He heals all your diseases.
19Ps 103:4 He redeems your life from the Pit; He crowns you with faithful love and compassion.
19Ps 103:5 He satisfies you with goodness; your youth is renewed like the eagle.
19Ps 103:6 The LORD executes acts of righteousness and justice for all the oppressed.
19Ps 103:7 He revealed His ways to Moses, His deeds to the people of Israel.
19Ps 103:8 The LORD is compassionate and gracious, slow to anger and full of faithful love.
19Ps 103:9 He will not always accuse [us] or be angry forever.
19Ps 103:10 He has not dealt with us as our sins deserve or repaid us according to our offenses.
19Ps 103:11 For as high as the heavens are above the earth, so great is His faithful love toward those who fear Him.
19Ps 103:12 As far as the east is from the west, so far has He removed our transgressions from us.
19Ps 103:13 As a father has compassion on his children, so the LORD has compassion on those who fear Him.
19Ps 103:14 For He knows what we are made of, remembering that we are dust.
19Ps 103:15 As for man, his days are like grass-- he blooms like a flower of the field;
19Ps 103:16 when the wind passes over it, it vanishes, and its place is no longer known.
19Ps 103:17 But from eternity to eternity the LORD's faithful love is toward those who fear Him, and His righteousness toward the grandchildren
19Ps 103:18 of those who keep His covenant, who remember to observe His instructions.
19Ps 103:19 The LORD has established His throne in heaven, and His kingdom rules over all.
19Ps 103:20 Praise the LORD, [all] His angels of great strength, who do His word, obedient to His command.
19Ps 103:21 Praise the LORD, all His armies, His servants who do His will.
19Ps 103:22 Praise the LORD, all His works in all the places where He rules. My soul, praise the LORD!
19Ps 104:1 My soul, praise the LORD! LORD my God, You are very great; You are clothed with majesty and splendor.
19Ps 104:2 He wraps Himself in light as if it were a robe, spreading out the sky like a canopy,
19Ps 104:3 laying the beams of His palace on the waters [above], making the clouds His chariot, walking on the wings of the wind,
19Ps 104:4 and making the winds His messengers, flames of fire His servants.
19Ps 104:5 He established the earth on its foundations; it will never be shaken.
19Ps 104:6 You covered it with the deep as if it were a garment; the waters stood above the mountains.
19Ps 104:7 At Your rebuke the waters fled; at the sound of Your thunder they hurried away--
19Ps 104:8 mountains rose and valleys sank-- to the place You established for them.
19Ps 104:9 You set a boundary they cannot cross; they will never cover the earth again.
19Ps 104:10 He causes the springs to gush into the valleys; they flow between the mountains.
19Ps 104:11 They supply water for every wild beast; the wild donkeys quench their thirst.
19Ps 104:12 The birds of the sky live beside [the springs]; they sing among the foliage.
19Ps 104:13 He waters the mountains from His palace; the earth is satisfied by the fruit of Your labor.
19Ps 104:14 He causes grass to grow for the livestock and [provides] crops for man to cultivate, producing food from the earth,
19Ps 104:15 wine that makes man's heart glad-- making his face shine with oil-- and bread that sustains man's heart.
19Ps 104:16 The trees of the LORD flourish, the cedars of Lebanon that He planted.
19Ps 104:17 There the birds make their nests; the stork makes its home in the pine trees.
19Ps 104:18 The high mountains are for the wild goats; the cliffs are a refuge for hyraxes.
19Ps 104:19 He made the moon to mark the seasons; the sun knows when to set.
19Ps 104:20 You bring darkness, and it becomes night, when all the forest animals stir.
19Ps 104:21 The young lions roar for their prey and seek their food from God.
19Ps 104:22 The sun rises; they go back and lie down in their dens.
19Ps 104:23 Man goes out to his work and to his labor until evening.
19Ps 104:24 How countless are Your works, LORD! In wisdom You have made them all; the earth is full of Your creatures.
19Ps 104:25 Here is the sea, vast and wide, teeming with creatures beyond number-- living things both large and small.
19Ps 104:26 There the ships move about, and Leviathan, which You formed to play there.
19Ps 104:27 All of them wait for You to give them their food at the right time.
19Ps 104:28 When You give it to them, they gather it; when You open Your hand, they are satisfied with good things.
19Ps 104:29 When You hide Your face, they are terrified; when You take away their breath, they die and return to the dust.
19Ps 104:30 When You send Your breath, they are created, and You renew the face of the earth.
19Ps 104:31 May the glory of the LORD endure forever; may the LORD rejoice in His works.
19Ps 104:32 He looks at the earth, and it trembles; He touches the mountains, and they pour out smoke.
19Ps 104:33 I will sing to the LORD all my life; I will sing praise to my God while I live.
19Ps 104:34 May my meditation be pleasing to Him; I will rejoice in the LORD.
19Ps 104:35 May sinners vanish from the earth and the wicked be no more. My soul, praise the LORD! Hallelujah!
19Ps 105:1 Give thanks to the LORD, call on His name; proclaim His deeds among the peoples.
19Ps 105:2 Sing to Him, sing praise to Him; tell about all His wonderful works!
19Ps 105:3 Honor His holy name; let the hearts of those who seek the LORD rejoice.
19Ps 105:4 Search for the LORD and for His strength; seek His face always.
19Ps 105:5 Remember the wonderful works He has done, His wonders, and the judgments He has pronounced,
19Ps 105:6 You offspring of Abraham His servant, Jacob's descendants-- His chosen ones.
19Ps 105:7 He is the LORD our God; His judgments [govern] the whole earth.
19Ps 105:8 He forever remembers His covenant, the promise He ordained for a thousand generations--
19Ps 105:9 [the covenant] He made with Abraham, swore to Isaac,
19Ps 105:10 and confirmed to Jacob as a decree and to Israel as an everlasting covenant:
19Ps 105:11 "I will give the land of Canaan to you as your inherited portion."
19Ps 105:12 When they were few in number, very few indeed, and temporary residents in Canaan,
19Ps 105:13 wandering from nation to nation and from one kingdom to another,
19Ps 105:14 He allowed no one to oppress them; He rebuked kings on their behalf:
19Ps 105:15 "Do not touch My anointed ones, or harm My prophets."
19Ps 105:16 He called down famine against the land and destroyed the entire food supply.
19Ps 105:17 He had sent a man ahead of them-- Joseph, who was sold as a slave.
19Ps 105:18 They hurt his feet with shackles; his neck was put in an iron collar.
19Ps 105:19 Until the time his prediction came true, the word of the LORD tested him.
19Ps 105:20 The king sent [for him] and released him; the ruler of peoples set him free.
19Ps 105:21 He made him master of his household, ruler over all his possessions--
19Ps 105:22 binding his officials at will and instructing his elders.
19Ps 105:23 Then Israel went to Egypt; Jacob lived as a foreigner in the land of Ham.
19Ps 105:24 The LORD made His people very fruitful; He made them more numerous than their foes,
19Ps 105:25 whose hearts He turned to hate His people and to deal deceptively with His servants.
19Ps 105:26 He sent Moses His servant, and Aaron, whom He had chosen.
19Ps 105:27 They performed His miraculous signs among them, and wonders in the land of Ham.
19Ps 105:28 He sent darkness, and it became dark-- for did they not defy His commands?
19Ps 105:29 He turned their waters into blood and caused their fish to die.
19Ps 105:30 Their land was overrun with frogs, even in their kings' chambers.
19Ps 105:31 He spoke, and insects came-- gnats throughout their country.
19Ps 105:32 He gave them hail for rain, and lightning throughout their land.
19Ps 105:33 He struck their vines and fig trees and shattered the trees of their territory.
19Ps 105:34 He spoke and locusts came-- young locusts without number.
19Ps 105:35 They devoured all the vegetation in their land and consumed the produce of their soil.
19Ps 105:36 He struck all the firstborn in their land, all their first progeny.
19Ps 105:37 Then He brought Israel out with silver and gold, and no one among His tribes stumbled.
19Ps 105:38 Egypt was glad when they left, for dread of Israel had fallen on them.
19Ps 105:39 He spread a cloud as a covering and [gave] a fire to light up the night.
19Ps 105:40 They asked, and He brought quail and satisfied them with bread from heaven.
19Ps 105:41 He opened a rock, and water gushed out; it flowed like a stream in the desert.
19Ps 105:42 For He remembered His holy promise to Abraham His servant.
19Ps 105:43 He brought His people out with rejoicing, His chosen ones with shouts of joy.
19Ps 105:44 He gave them the lands of the nations, and they inherited what other peoples had worked for.
19Ps 105:45 [All this happened] so that they might keep His statutes and obey His laws. Hallelujah!
19Ps 106:1 Hallelujah! Give thanks to the LORD, for He is good; His faithful love endures forever.
19Ps 106:2 Who can declare the LORD's mighty acts or proclaim all the praise due Him?
19Ps 106:3 How happy are those who uphold justice, who practice righteousness at all times.
19Ps 106:4 Remember me, LORD, when You show favor to Your people. Come to me with Your salvation
19Ps 106:5 so that I may enjoy the prosperity of Your chosen ones, rejoice in the joy of Your nation, and boast about Your heritage.
19Ps 106:6 Both we and our fathers have sinned; we have gone astray and have acted wickedly.
19Ps 106:7 Our fathers in Egypt did not grasp [the significance of] Your wonderful works or remember Your many acts of faithful love; instead, they rebelled by the sea-- the Red Sea.
19Ps 106:8 Yet He saved them because of His name, to make His power known.
19Ps 106:9 He rebuked the Red Sea, and it dried up; He led them through the depths as through a desert.
19Ps 106:10 He saved them from the hand of the adversary; He redeemed them from the hand of the enemy.
19Ps 106:11 Water covered their foes; not one of them remained.
19Ps 106:12 Then they believed His promises and sang His praise.
19Ps 106:13 They soon forgot His works and would not wait for His counsel.
19Ps 106:14 They were seized with craving in the wilderness and tested God in the desert.
19Ps 106:15 He gave them what they asked for, but sent a wasting disease among them.
19Ps 106:16 In the camp they were envious of Moses and of Aaron, the LORD's holy one.
19Ps 106:17 The earth opened up and swallowed Dathan; it covered the assembly of Abiram.
19Ps 106:18 Fire blazed throughout their assembly; flames consumed the wicked.
19Ps 106:19 At Horeb they made a calf and worshiped the cast metal image.
19Ps 106:20 They exchanged their glory for the image of a grass-eating ox.
19Ps 106:21 They forgot God their Savior, who did great things in Egypt,
19Ps 106:22 wonderful works in the land of Ham, awe-inspiring deeds at the Red Sea.
19Ps 106:23 So He said He would have destroyed them-- if Moses His chosen one had not stood before Him in the breach to turn His wrath away from destroying [them].
19Ps 106:24 They despised the pleasant land and did not believe His promise.
19Ps 106:25 They grumbled in their tents and did not listen to the LORD's voice.
19Ps 106:26 So He raised His hand against them [with an oath] that He would make them fall in the desert
19Ps 106:27 and would disperse their descendants among the nations, scattering them throughout the lands.
19Ps 106:28 They aligned themselves with Baal of Peor and ate sacrifices offered to lifeless gods.
19Ps 106:29 They provoked the LORD with their deeds, and a plague broke out against them.
19Ps 106:30 But Phinehas stood up and intervened, and the plague was stopped.
19Ps 106:31 It was credited to him as righteousness throughout all generations to come.
19Ps 106:32 They angered [the LORD] at the waters of Meribah, and Moses suffered because of them;
19Ps 106:33 for they embittered his spirit, and he spoke rashly with his lips.
19Ps 106:34 They did not destroy the peoples as the LORD had commanded them,
19Ps 106:35 but mingled with the nations and adopted their ways.
19Ps 106:36 They served their idols, which became a snare to them.
19Ps 106:37 They sacrificed their sons and daughters to demons.
19Ps 106:38 They shed innocent blood-- the blood of their sons and daughters whom they sacrificed to the idols of Canaan; so the land became polluted with blood.
19Ps 106:39 They defiled themselves by their actions and prostituted themselves by their deeds.
19Ps 106:40 Therefore the LORD's anger burned against His people, and He abhorred His own inheritance.
19Ps 106:41 He handed them over to the nations; those who hated them ruled them.
19Ps 106:42 Their enemies oppressed them, and they were subdued under their power.
19Ps 106:43 He rescued them many times, but they continued to rebel deliberately and were beaten down by their sin.
19Ps 106:44 When He heard their cry, He took note of their distress,
19Ps 106:45 remembered His covenant with them, and relented according to the abundance of His faithful love.
19Ps 106:46 He caused them to be pitied before all their captors.
19Ps 106:47 Save us, LORD our God, and gather us from the nations, so that we may give thanks to Your holy name and rejoice in Your praise.
19Ps 106:48 May the LORD, the God of Israel, be praised from everlasting to everlasting. Let all the people say, "Amen!" Hallelujah!
19Ps 107:1 Give thanks to the LORD, for He is good; His faithful love endures forever.
19Ps 107:2 Let the redeemed of the LORD proclaim that He has redeemed them from the hand of the foe
19Ps 107:3 and has gathered them from the lands-- from the east and the west, from the north and the south.
19Ps 107:4 Some wandered in the desolate wilderness, finding no way to a city where they could live.
19Ps 107:5 They were hungry and thirsty; their spirits failed within them.
19Ps 107:6 Then they cried out to the LORD in their trouble; He rescued them from their distress.
19Ps 107:7 He led them by the right path to go to a city where they could live.
19Ps 107:8 Let them give thanks to the LORD for His faithful love and His wonderful works for the human race.
19Ps 107:9 For He has satisfied the thirsty and filled the hungry with good things.
19Ps 107:10 Others sat in darkness and gloom-- prisoners in cruel chains--
19Ps 107:11 because they rebelled against God's commands and despised the counsel of the Most High.
19Ps 107:12 He broke their spirits with hard labor; they stumbled, and there was no one to help.
19Ps 107:13 Then they cried out to the LORD in their trouble; He saved them from their distress.
19Ps 107:14 He brought them out of darkness and gloom and broke their chains apart.
19Ps 107:15 Let them give thanks to the LORD for His faithful love and His wonderful works for the human race.
19Ps 107:16 For He has broken down the bronze gates and cut through the iron bars.
19Ps 107:17 Fools suffered affliction because of their rebellious ways and their sins.
19Ps 107:18 They loathed all food and came near the gates of death.
19Ps 107:19 Then they cried out to the LORD in their trouble; He saved them from their distress.
19Ps 107:20 He sent His word and healed them; He rescued them from the Pit.
19Ps 107:21 Let them give thanks to the LORD for His faithful love and His wonderful works for the human race.
19Ps 107:22 Let them offer sacrifices of thanksgiving and announce His works with shouts of joy.
19Ps 107:23 Others went to sea in ships, conducting trade on the vast waters.
19Ps 107:24 They saw the LORD's works, His wonderful works in the deep.
19Ps 107:25 He spoke and raised a tempest that stirred up the waves of the sea.
19Ps 107:26 Rising up to the sky, sinking down to the depths, their courage melting away in anguish,
19Ps 107:27 they reeled and staggered like drunken men, and all their skill was useless.
19Ps 107:28 Then they cried out to the LORD in their trouble, and He brought them out of their distress.
19Ps 107:29 He stilled the storm to a murmur, and the waves of the sea were hushed.
19Ps 107:30 They rejoiced when the waves grew quiet. Then He guided them to the harbor they longed for.
19Ps 107:31 Let them give thanks to the LORD for His faithful love and His wonderful works for the human race.
19Ps 107:32 Let them exalt Him in the assembly of the people and praise Him in the council of the elders.
19Ps 107:33 He turns rivers into desert, springs of water into thirsty ground,
19Ps 107:34 and fruitful land into salty wasteland, because of the wickedness of its inhabitants.
19Ps 107:35 He turns a desert into a pool of water, dry land into springs of water.
19Ps 107:36 He causes the hungry to settle there, and they establish a city where they can live.
19Ps 107:37 They sow fields and plant vineyards that yield a fruitful harvest.
19Ps 107:38 He blesses them, and they multiply greatly; He does not let their livestock decrease.
19Ps 107:39 When they are diminished and are humbled by cruel oppression and sorrow,
19Ps 107:40 He pours contempt on nobles and makes them wander in trackless wastelands.
19Ps 107:41 But He lifts the needy out of their suffering and makes their families [multiply] like flocks.
19Ps 107:42 The upright see it and rejoice, and all injustice shuts its mouth.
19Ps 107:43 Let whoever is wise pay attention to these things and consider the LORD's acts of faithful love.
19Ps 108:1 [A song. A Davidic psalm.] My heart is confident, God; I will sing; I will sing praises with the whole of my being.
19Ps 108:2 Wake up, harp and lyre! I will wake up the dawn.
19Ps 108:3 I will praise You, LORD, among the peoples; I will sing praises to You among the nations.
19Ps 108:4 For Your faithful love is higher than the heavens; Your faithfulness reaches the clouds.
19Ps 108:5 God, be exalted above the heavens; let Your glory be over the whole earth.
19Ps 108:6 Save with Your right hand and answer me so that those You love may be rescued.
19Ps 108:7 God has spoken in His sanctuary: "I will triumph! I will divide up Shechem. I will apportion the Valley of Succoth.
19Ps 108:8 Gilead is Mine, Manasseh is Mine, and Ephraim is My helmet; Judah is My scepter.
19Ps 108:9 Moab is My washbasin; on Edom I throw My sandal. Over Philistia I shout in triumph."
19Ps 108:10 Who will bring me to the fortified city? Who will lead me to Edom?
19Ps 108:11 Have You not rejected us, God? God, You do not march out with our armies.
19Ps 108:12 Give us aid against the foe, for human help is worthless.
19Ps 108:13 With God we will perform valiantly; He will trample our foes.
19Ps 109:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic psalm.] God of my praise, do not be silent.
19Ps 109:2 For wicked and deceitful mouths open against me; they speak against me with lying tongues.
19Ps 109:3 They surround me with hateful words and attack me without cause.
19Ps 109:4 In return for my love they accuse me, but I continue to pray.
19Ps 109:5 They repay me evil for good, and hatred for my love.
19Ps 109:6 Set a wicked person over him; let an accuser stand at his right hand.
19Ps 109:7 When he is judged, let him be found guilty, and let his prayer be counted as sin.
19Ps 109:8 Let his days be few; let another take over his position.
19Ps 109:9 Let his children be fatherless and his wife a widow.
19Ps 109:10 Let his children wander as beggars, searching [for food] far from their demolished homes.
19Ps 109:11 Let a creditor seize all he has; let strangers plunder what he has worked for.
19Ps 109:12 Let no one show him kindness, and let no one be gracious to his fatherless children.
19Ps 109:13 Let the line of his descendants be cut off; let their name be blotted out in the next generation.
19Ps 109:14 Let his forefathers' guilt be remembered before the LORD, and do not let his mother's sin be blotted out.
19Ps 109:15 Let their sins always remain before the LORD, and let Him cut off [all] memory of them from the earth.
19Ps 109:16 For he did not think to show kindness, but pursued the wretched poor and the brokenhearted in order to put them to death.
19Ps 109:17 He loved cursing-- let it fall on him; he took no delight in blessing-- let it be far from him.
19Ps 109:18 He wore cursing like his coat-- let it enter his body like water and go into his bones like oil.
19Ps 109:19 Let it be like a robe he wraps around himself, like a belt he always wears.
19Ps 109:20 Let this be the LORD's payment to my accusers, to those who speak evil against me.
19Ps 109:21 But You, God my Lord, deal [kindly] with me because of Your name; deliver me because of the goodness of Your faithful love.
19Ps 109:22 For I am poor and needy; my heart is wounded within me.
19Ps 109:23 I fade away like a lengthening shadow; I am shaken off like a locust.
19Ps 109:24 My knees are weak from fasting, and my body is emaciated.
19Ps 109:25 I have become an object of ridicule to my accusers; when they see me, they shake their heads [in scorn].
19Ps 109:26 Help me, LORD my God; save me according to Your faithful love
19Ps 109:27 so they may know that this is Your hand and that You, LORD, have done it.
19Ps 109:28 Though they curse, You will bless. When they rise up, they will be put to shame, but Your servant will rejoice.
19Ps 109:29 My accusers will be clothed with disgrace; they will wear their shame like a cloak.
19Ps 109:30 I will fervently thank the LORD with my mouth; I will praise Him in the presence of many.
19Ps 109:31 For He stands at the right hand of the needy, to save him from those who would condemn him.
19Ps 110:1 [A Davidic psalm.] The LORD declared to my Lord: "Sit at My right hand until I make Your enemies Your footstool."
19Ps 110:2 The LORD will extend Your mighty scepter from Zion. Rule over Your surrounding enemies.
19Ps 110:3 Your people will volunteer on Your day of battle. In holy splendor, from the womb of the dawn, the dew of Your youth belongs to You.
19Ps 110:4 The LORD has sworn an oath and will not take it back: "Forever, You are a priest like Melchizedek."
19Ps 110:5 The Lord is at Your right hand; He will crush kings on the day of His anger.
19Ps 110:6 He will judge the nations, heaping up corpses; He will crush leaders over the entire world.
19Ps 110:7 He will drink from the brook by the road; therefore, He will lift up His head.
19Ps 111:1 Hallelujah! I will praise the LORD with all my heart in the assembly of the upright and in the congregation.
19Ps 111:2 The LORD's works are great, studied by all who delight in them.
19Ps 111:3 All that He does is splendid and majestic; His righteousness endures forever.
19Ps 111:4 He has caused His wonderful works to be remembered. The LORD is gracious and compassionate.
19Ps 111:5 He has provided food for those who fear Him; He remembers His covenant forever.
19Ps 111:6 He has shown His people the power of His works by giving them the inheritance of the nations.
19Ps 111:7 The works of His hands are truth and justice; all His instructions are trustworthy.
19Ps 111:8 They are established forever and ever, enacted in truth and uprightness.
19Ps 111:9 He has sent redemption to His people. He has ordained His covenant forever. His name is holy and awe-inspiring.
19Ps 111:10 The fear of the LORD is the beginning of wisdom; all who follow His instructions have good insight. His praise endures forever.
19Ps 112:1 Hallelujah! Happy is the man who fears the Lord, taking great delight in His commandments.
19Ps 112:2 His descendants will be powerful in the land; the generation of the upright will be blessed.
19Ps 112:3 Wealth and riches are in his house, and his righteousness endures forever.
19Ps 112:4 Light shines in the darkness for the upright. He is gracious, compassionate, and righteous.
19Ps 112:5 Good will come to a man who lends generously and conducts his business fairly.
19Ps 112:6 He will never be shaken. The righteous will be remembered forever.
19Ps 112:7 He will not fear bad news; his heart is confident, trusting in the LORD.
19Ps 112:8 His heart is assured; he will not fear. In the end he will look in triumph on his foes.
19Ps 112:9 He distributes freely to the poor; his righteousness endures forever. His horn will be exalted in honor.
19Ps 112:10 The wicked man will see [it] and be angry; he will gnash his teeth in despair. The desire of the wicked will come to nothing.
19Ps 113:1 Hallelujah! Give praise, servants of the LORD; praise the name of the LORD.
19Ps 113:2 Let the name of the LORD be praised both now and forever.
19Ps 113:3 From the rising of the sun to its setting, let the name of the LORD be praised.
19Ps 113:4 The LORD is exalted above all the nations, His glory above the heavens.
19Ps 113:5 Who is like the LORD our God-- the One enthroned on high,
19Ps 113:6 who stoops down to look on the heavens and the earth?
19Ps 113:7 He raises the poor from the dust and lifts the needy from the garbage pile
19Ps 113:8 in order to seat them with nobles-- with the nobles of His people.
19Ps 113:9 He gives the childless woman a household, [making her] the joyful mother of children. Hallelujah!
19Ps 114:1 When Israel came out of Egypt-- the house of Jacob from a people who spoke a foreign language--
19Ps 114:2 Judah became His sanctuary, Israel, His dominion.
19Ps 114:3 The sea looked and fled; the Jordan turned back.
19Ps 114:4 The mountains skipped like rams, the hills, like lambs.
19Ps 114:5 Why was it, sea, that you fled? Jordan, that you turned back?
19Ps 114:6 Mountains, that you skipped like rams? Hills, like lambs?
19Ps 114:7 Tremble, earth, at the presence of the Lord, at the presence of the God of Jacob,
19Ps 114:8 who turned the rock into a pool of water, the flint into a spring of water.
19Ps 115:1 Not to us, LORD, not to us, but to Your name give glory because of Your faithful love, because of Your truth.
19Ps 115:2 Why should the nations say, "Where is their God?"
19Ps 115:3 Our God is in heaven and does whatever He pleases.
19Ps 115:4 Their idols are silver and gold, made by human hands.
19Ps 115:5 They have mouths, but cannot speak, eyes, but cannot see.
19Ps 115:6 They have ears, but cannot hear, noses, but cannot smell.
19Ps 115:7 They have hands, but cannot feel, feet, but cannot walk. They cannot make a sound with their throats.
19Ps 115:8 Those who make them are just like them, as are all who trust in them.
19Ps 115:9 Israel, trust in the LORD! He is their help and shield.
19Ps 115:10 House of Aaron, trust in the LORD! He is their help and shield.
19Ps 115:11 You who fear the LORD, trust in the LORD! He is their help and shield.
19Ps 115:12 The LORD remembers us and will bless [us]. He will bless the house of Israel; He will bless the house of Aaron;
19Ps 115:13 He will bless those who fear the Lord-- small and great alike.
19Ps 115:14 May the LORD add to [your numbers], both yours and your children's.
19Ps 115:15 May you be blessed by the LORD, the Maker of heaven and earth.
19Ps 115:16 The heavens are the LORD's, but the earth He has given to the human race.
19Ps 115:17 It is not the dead who praise the LORD, nor any of those descending into the silence [of death].
19Ps 115:18 But we will praise the LORD, both now and forever. Hallelujah!
19Ps 116:1 I love the LORD because He has heard my appeal for mercy.
19Ps 116:2 Because He has turned His ear to me, I will call [out to Him] as long as I live.
19Ps 116:3 The ropes of death were wrapped around me, and the torments of Sheol overcame me; I encountered trouble and sorrow.
19Ps 116:4 Then I called on the name of the LORD: "LORD, save me!"
19Ps 116:5 The LORD is gracious and righteous; our God is compassionate.
19Ps 116:6 The LORD guards the inexperienced; I was helpless, and He saved me.
19Ps 116:7 Return to your rest, my soul, for the LORD has been good to you.
19Ps 116:8 For You, [LORD,] rescued me from death, my eyes from tears, my feet from stumbling.
19Ps 116:9 I will walk before the LORD in the land of the living.
19Ps 116:10 I believed, even when I said, "I am severely afflicted."
19Ps 116:11 In my alarm I said, "Everyone is a liar."
19Ps 116:12 How can I repay the LORD all the good He has done for me?
19Ps 116:13 I will take the cup of salvation and worship the LORD.
19Ps 116:14 I will fulfill my vows to the LORD in the presence of all His people.
19Ps 116:15 The death of His faithful ones is valuable in the LORD's sight.
19Ps 116:16 LORD, I am indeed Your servant; I am Your servant, the son of Your female servant. You have loosened my bonds.
19Ps 116:17 I will offer You a sacrifice of thanksgiving and will worship the LORD.
19Ps 116:18 I will fulfill my vows to the LORD, in the very presence of all His people,
19Ps 116:19 in the courts of the LORD's house-- within you, Jerusalem. Hallelujah!
19Ps 117:1 Praise the LORD, all nations! Glorify Him, all peoples!
19Ps 117:2 For great is His faithful love to us; the LORD's faithfulness endures forever. Hallelujah!
19Ps 118:1 Give thanks to the LORD, for He is good; His faithful love endures forever.
19Ps 118:2 Let Israel say, "His faithful love endures forever."
19Ps 118:3 Let the house of Aaron say, "His faithful love endures forever."
19Ps 118:4 Let those who fear the LORD say, "His faithful love endures forever."
19Ps 118:5 I called to the LORD in distress; the LORD answered me [and put me] in a spacious place.
19Ps 118:6 The LORD is for me; I will not be afraid. What can man do to me?
19Ps 118:7 With the LORD for me as my helper, I will look in triumph on those who hate me.
19Ps 118:8 It is better to take refuge in the LORD than to trust in man.
19Ps 118:9 It is better to take refuge in the LORD than to trust in nobles.
19Ps 118:10 All the nations surrounded me; in the name of the LORD I destroyed them.
19Ps 118:11 They surrounded me, yes, they surrounded me; in the name of the LORD I destroyed them.
19Ps 118:12 They surrounded me like bees; they were extinguished like a fire among thorns; in the name of the LORD I destroyed them.
19Ps 118:13 You pushed me hard to make me fall, but the LORD helped me.
19Ps 118:14 The LORD is my strength and my song; He has become my salvation.
19Ps 118:15 There are shouts of joy and victory in the tents of the righteous: "The LORD's right hand strikes with power!
19Ps 118:16 The LORD's right hand is raised! The LORD's right hand strikes with power!"
19Ps 118:17 I will not die, but I will live and proclaim what the LORD has done.
19Ps 118:18 The LORD disciplined me severely but did not give me over to death.
19Ps 118:19 Open the gates of righteousness for me; I will enter through them and give thanks to the LORD.
19Ps 118:20 This is the gate of the LORD; the righteous will enter through it.
19Ps 118:21 I will give thanks to You because You have answered me and have become my salvation.
19Ps 118:22 The stone that the builders rejected has become the cornerstone.
19Ps 118:23 This came from the LORD; it is wonderful in our eyes.
19Ps 118:24 This is the day the LORD has made; let us rejoice and be glad in it.
19Ps 118:25 LORD, save us! LORD, please grant us success!
19Ps 118:26 Blessed is he who comes in the name of the LORD. From the house of the LORD we bless you.
19Ps 118:27 The LORD is God and has given us light. Bind the festival sacrifice with cords to the horns of the altar.
19Ps 118:28 You are my God, and I will give You thanks. [You are] my God; I will exalt You.
19Ps 118:29 Give thanks to the LORD, for He is good; His faithful love endures forever.
19Ps 119:1 How happy are those whose way is blameless, who live according to the law of the LORD!
19Ps 119:2 Happy are those who keep His decrees and seek Him with all their heart.
19Ps 119:3 They do nothing wrong; they follow His ways.
19Ps 119:4 You have commanded that Your precepts be diligently kept.
19Ps 119:5 If only my ways were committed to keeping Your statutes!
19Ps 119:6 Then I would not be ashamed when I think about all Your commands.
19Ps 119:7 I will praise You with a sincere heart when I learn Your righteous judgments.
19Ps 119:8 I will keep Your statutes; never abandon me.
19Ps 119:9 How can a young man keep his way pure? By keeping Your word.
19Ps 119:10 I have sought You with all my heart; don't let me wander from Your commands.
19Ps 119:11 I have treasured Your word in my heart so that I may not sin against You.
19Ps 119:12 LORD, may You be praised; teach me Your statutes.
19Ps 119:13 With my lips I proclaim all the judgments from Your mouth.
19Ps 119:14 I rejoice in the way [revealed by] Your decrees as much as in all riches.
19Ps 119:15 I will meditate on Your precepts and think about Your ways.
19Ps 119:16 I will delight in Your statutes; I will not forget Your word.
19Ps 119:17 Deal generously with Your servant so that I might live; then I will keep Your word.
19Ps 119:18 Open my eyes so that I may see wonderful things in Your law.
19Ps 119:19 I am a stranger on earth; do not hide Your commands from me.
19Ps 119:20 I am continually overcome by longing for Your judgments.
19Ps 119:21 You rebuke the proud, the accursed, who wander from Your commands.
19Ps 119:22 Take insult and contempt away from me, for I have kept Your decrees.
19Ps 119:23 Though princes sit together speaking against me, Your servant will think about Your statutes;
19Ps 119:24 Your decrees are my delight and my counselors.
19Ps 119:25 My life is down in the dust; give me life through Your word.
19Ps 119:26 I told You about my life, and You listened to me; teach me Your statutes.
19Ps 119:27 Help me understand the meaning of Your precepts so that I can meditate on Your wonders.
19Ps 119:28 I am weary from grief; strengthen me through Your word.
19Ps 119:29 Keep me from the way of deceit, and graciously give me Your instruction.
19Ps 119:30 I have chosen the way of truth; I have set Your ordinances [before me].
19Ps 119:31 I cling to Your decrees; LORD, do not put me to shame.
19Ps 119:32 I pursue the way of Your commands, for You broaden my understanding.
19Ps 119:33 Teach me, LORD, the meaning of Your statutes, and I will always keep them.
19Ps 119:34 Help me understand Your instruction, and I will obey it and follow it with all my heart.
19Ps 119:35 Help me stay on the path of Your commands, for I take pleasure in it.
19Ps 119:36 Turn my heart to Your decrees and not to material gain.
19Ps 119:37 Turn my eyes from looking at what is worthless; give me life in Your ways.
19Ps 119:38 Confirm what You said to Your servant, for it produces reverence for You.
19Ps 119:39 Turn away the disgrace I dread; indeed, Your judgments are good.
19Ps 119:40 How I long for Your precepts! Give me life through Your righteousness.
19Ps 119:41 Let Your faithful love come to me, LORD, Your salvation, as You promised.
19Ps 119:42 Then I can answer the one who taunts me, for I trust in Your word.
19Ps 119:43 Never take the word of truth from my mouth, for I hope in Your judgments.
19Ps 119:44 I will always keep Your law, forever and ever.
19Ps 119:45 I will walk freely in an open place because I seek Your precepts.
19Ps 119:46 I will speak of Your decrees before kings and not be ashamed.
19Ps 119:47 I delight in Your commands, which I love.
19Ps 119:48 I will lift up my hands to Your commands, which I love, and will meditate on Your statutes.
19Ps 119:49 Remember [Your] word to Your servant; You have given me hope through it.
19Ps 119:50 This is my comfort in my affliction: Your promise has given me life.
19Ps 119:51 The arrogant constantly ridicule me, but I do not turn away from Your instruction.
19Ps 119:52 LORD, I remember Your judgments from long ago and find comfort.
19Ps 119:53 Rage seizes me because of the wicked who reject Your instruction.
19Ps 119:54 Your statutes are [the theme of] my song during my earthly life.
19Ps 119:55 I remember Your name in the night, LORD, and I keep Your law.
19Ps 119:56 This is my [practice]: I obey Your precepts.
19Ps 119:57 The LORD is my portion; I have promised to keep Your words.
19Ps 119:58 I have sought Your favor with all my heart; be gracious to me according to Your promise.
19Ps 119:59 I thought about my ways and turned my steps back to Your decrees.
19Ps 119:60 I hurried, not hesitating to keep Your commands.
19Ps 119:61 Though the ropes of the wicked were wrapped around me, I did not forget Your law.
19Ps 119:62 I rise at midnight to thank You for Your righteous judgments.
19Ps 119:63 I am a friend to all who fear You, to those who keep Your precepts.
19Ps 119:64 LORD, the earth is filled with Your faithful love; teach me Your statutes.
19Ps 119:65 LORD, You have treated Your servant well, just as You promised.
19Ps 119:66 Teach me good judgment and discernment, for I rely on Your commands.
19Ps 119:67 Before I was afflicted I went astray, but now I keep Your word.
19Ps 119:68 You are good, and You do what is good; teach me Your statutes.
19Ps 119:69 The arrogant have smeared me with lies, but I obey Your precepts with all my heart.
19Ps 119:70 Their hearts are hard and insensitive, but I delight in Your instruction.
19Ps 119:71 It was good for me to be afflicted so that I could learn Your statutes.
19Ps 119:72 Instruction from Your lips is better for me than thousands of gold and silver pieces.
19Ps 119:73 Your hands made me and formed me; give me understanding so that I can learn Your commands.
19Ps 119:74 Those who fear You will see me and rejoice, for I put my hope in Your word.
19Ps 119:75 I know, LORD, that Your judgments are just and that You have afflicted me fairly.
19Ps 119:76 May Your faithful love comfort me, as You promised Your servant.
19Ps 119:77 May Your compassion come to me so that I may live, for Your instruction is my delight.
19Ps 119:78 Let the arrogant be put to shame for slandering me with lies; I will meditate on Your precepts.
19Ps 119:79 Let those who fear You, those who know Your decrees, turn to me.
19Ps 119:80 May my heart be blameless regarding Your statutes so that I will not be put to shame.
19Ps 119:81 I long for Your salvation; I put my hope in Your word.
19Ps 119:82 My eyes grow weary [looking] for what You have promised; I ask, "When will You comfort me?"
19Ps 119:83 Though I have become like a wineskin [dried] by smoke, I do not forget Your statutes.
19Ps 119:84 How many days [must] Your servant [wait]? When will You execute judgment on my persecutors?
19Ps 119:85 The arrogant have dug pits for me; they violate Your instruction.
19Ps 119:86 All Your commands are true; people persecute me with lies-- help me!
19Ps 119:87 They almost ended my life on earth, but I did not abandon Your precepts.
19Ps 119:88 Give me life in accordance with Your faithful love, and I will obey the decree You have spoken.
19Ps 119:89 LORD, Your word is forever; it is firmly fixed in heaven.
19Ps 119:90 Your faithfulness is for all generations; You established the earth, and it stands firm.
19Ps 119:91 They stand today in accordance with Your judgments, for all things are Your servants.
19Ps 119:92 If Your instruction had not been my delight, I would have died in my affliction.
19Ps 119:93 I will never forget Your precepts, for You have given me life through them.
19Ps 119:94 I am Yours; save me, for I have sought Your precepts.
19Ps 119:95 The wicked hope to destroy me, but I contemplate Your decrees.
19Ps 119:96 I have seen a limit to all perfection, but Your command is without limit.
19Ps 119:97 How I love Your teaching! It is my meditation all day long.
19Ps 119:98 Your command makes me wiser than my enemies, for it is always with me.
19Ps 119:99 I have more insight than all my teachers because Your decrees are my meditation.
19Ps 119:100 I understand more than the elders because I obey Your precepts.
19Ps 119:101 I have kept my feet from every evil path to follow Your word.
19Ps 119:102 I have not turned from Your judgments, for You Yourself have instructed me.
19Ps 119:103 How sweet Your word is to my taste-- [sweeter] than honey to my mouth.
19Ps 119:104 I gain understanding from Your precepts; therefore I hate every false way.
19Ps 119:105 Your word is a lamp for my feet and a light on my path.
19Ps 119:106 I have solemnly sworn to keep Your righteous judgments.
19Ps 119:107 I am severely afflicted; LORD, give me life through Your word.
19Ps 119:108 LORD, please accept my willing offerings of praise, and teach me Your judgments.
19Ps 119:109 My life is constantly in danger, yet I do not forget Your instruction.
19Ps 119:110 The wicked have set a trap for me, but I have not wandered from Your precepts.
19Ps 119:111 I have Your decrees as a heritage forever; indeed, they are the joy of my heart.
19Ps 119:112 I am resolved to obey Your statutes to the very end.
19Ps 119:113 I hate the double-minded, but I love Your instruction.
19Ps 119:114 You are my shelter and my shield; I put my hope in Your word.
19Ps 119:115 Depart from me, you evil ones, so that I may obey my God's commands.
19Ps 119:116 Sustain me as You promised, and I will live; do not let me be ashamed of my hope.
19Ps 119:117 Sustain me so that I can be safe and be concerned with Your statutes continually.
19Ps 119:118 You reject all who stray from Your statutes, for their deceit is a lie.
19Ps 119:119 You remove all the wicked on earth as if they were dross; therefore, I love Your decrees.
19Ps 119:120 I tremble in awe of You; I fear Your judgments.
19Ps 119:121 I have done what is just and right; do not leave me to my oppressors.
19Ps 119:122 Guarantee Your servant's well-being; do not let the arrogant oppress me.
19Ps 119:123 My eyes grow weary [looking for] Your salvation and for Your righteous promise.
19Ps 119:124 Deal with Your servant based on Your faithful love; teach me Your statutes.
19Ps 119:125 I am Your servant; give me understanding so that I may know Your decrees.
19Ps 119:126 It is time for the LORD to act, [for] they have broken Your law.
19Ps 119:127 Since I love Your commandments more than gold, even the purest gold,
19Ps 119:128 I carefully follow all Your precepts and hate every false way.
19Ps 119:129 Your decrees are wonderful; therefore I obey them.
19Ps 119:130 The revelation of Your words brings light and gives understanding to the inexperienced.
19Ps 119:131 I pant with open mouth because I long for Your commands.
19Ps 119:132 Turn to me and be gracious to me, as is [Your] practice toward those who love Your name.
19Ps 119:133 Make my steps steady through Your promise; don't let sin dominate me.
19Ps 119:134 Redeem me from human oppression, and I will keep Your precepts.
19Ps 119:135 Show favor to Your servant, and teach me Your statutes.
19Ps 119:136 My eyes pour out streams of tears because people do not follow Your instruction.
19Ps 119:137 You are righteous, LORD, and Your judgments are just.
19Ps 119:138 The decrees You issue are righteous and altogether trustworthy.
19Ps 119:139 My anger overwhelms me because my foes forget Your words.
19Ps 119:140 Your word is completely pure, and Your servant loves it.
19Ps 119:141 I am insignificant and despised, but I do not forget Your precepts.
19Ps 119:142 Your righteousness is an everlasting righteousness, and Your instruction is true.
19Ps 119:143 Trouble and distress have overtaken me, but Your commands are my delight.
19Ps 119:144 Your decrees are righteous forever. Give me understanding, and I will live.
19Ps 119:145 I call with all my heart; answer me, LORD. I will obey Your statutes.
19Ps 119:146 I call to You; save me, and I will keep Your decrees.
19Ps 119:147 I rise before dawn and cry out for help; I put my hope in Your word.
19Ps 119:148 I am awake through each watch of the night to meditate on Your promise.
19Ps 119:149 In keeping with Your faithful love, hear my voice. LORD, give me life, in keeping with Your justice.
19Ps 119:150 Those who pursue evil plans come near; they are far from Your instruction.
19Ps 119:151 You are near, LORD, and all Your commands are true.
19Ps 119:152 Long ago I learned from Your decrees that You have established them forever.
19Ps 119:153 Consider my affliction and rescue me, for I have not forgotten Your instruction.
19Ps 119:154 Defend my cause, and redeem me; give me life, as You promised.
19Ps 119:155 Salvation is far from the wicked because they do not seek Your statutes.
19Ps 119:156 Your compassions are many, LORD; give me life, according to Your judgments.
19Ps 119:157 My persecutors and foes are many. I have not turned from Your decrees.
19Ps 119:158 I have seen the disloyal and feel disgust because they do not keep Your word.
19Ps 119:159 Consider how I love Your precepts; LORD, give me life, according to Your faithful love.
19Ps 119:160 The entirety of Your word is truth, and all Your righteous judgments endure forever.
19Ps 119:161 Princes have persecuted me without cause, but my heart fears [only] Your word.
19Ps 119:162 I rejoice over Your promise like one who finds vast treasure.
19Ps 119:163 I hate and abhor falsehood, [but] I love Your instruction.
19Ps 119:164 I praise You seven times a day for Your righteous judgments.
19Ps 119:165 Abundant peace belongs to those who love Your instruction; nothing makes them stumble.
19Ps 119:166 LORD, I hope for Your salvation and carry out Your commands.
19Ps 119:167 I obey Your decrees and love them greatly.
19Ps 119:168 I obey Your precepts and decrees, for all my ways are before You.
19Ps 119:169 Let my cry reach You, LORD; give me understanding according to Your word.
19Ps 119:170 Let my plea reach You; rescue me according to Your promise.
19Ps 119:171 My lips pour out praise, for You teach me Your statutes.
19Ps 119:172 My tongue sings about Your promise, for all Your commandments are righteous.
19Ps 119:173 May Your hand be ready to help me, for I have chosen Your precepts.
19Ps 119:174 I long for Your salvation, LORD, and Your instruction is my delight.
19Ps 119:175 Let me live, and I will praise You; may Your judgments help me.
19Ps 119:176 I wander like a lost sheep; seek Your servant, for I do not forget Your commands.
19Ps 120:1 [A song of ascents.] In my distress I called to the LORD, and He answered me:
19Ps 120:2 "LORD, deliver me from lying lips and a deceitful tongue."
19Ps 120:3 What will He give you, and what will He do to you, you deceitful tongue?
19Ps 120:4 A warrior's sharp arrows, with burning charcoal!
19Ps 120:5 What misery that I have stayed in Meshech, that I have lived among the tents of Kedar!
19Ps 120:6 I have lived too long with those who hate peace.
19Ps 120:7 I am for peace; but when I speak, they are for war.
19Ps 121:1 [A song of ascents.] I raise my eyes toward the mountains. Where will my help come from?
19Ps 121:2 My help comes from the LORD, the Maker of heaven and earth.
19Ps 121:3 He will not allow your foot to slip; your Protector will not slumber.
19Ps 121:4 Indeed, the Protector of Israel does not slumber or sleep.
19Ps 121:5 The LORD protects you; the LORD is a shelter right by your side.
19Ps 121:6 The sun will not strike you by day, or the moon by night.
19Ps 121:7 The LORD will protect you from all harm; He will protect your life.
19Ps 121:8 The LORD will protect your coming and going both now and forever.
19Ps 122:1 [A Davidic song of ascents.] I rejoiced with those who said to me, "Let us go to the house of the LORD."
19Ps 122:2 Our feet are standing within your gates, Jerusalem--
19Ps 122:3 Jerusalem, built as a city [should be], solidly joined together,
19Ps 122:4 where the tribes, the tribes of the LORD, go up to give thanks to the name of the LORD. (This is an ordinance for Israel.)
19Ps 122:5 There, thrones for judgment are placed, thrones of the house of David.
19Ps 122:6 Pray for the peace of Jerusalem: "May those who love you prosper;
19Ps 122:7 may there be peace within your walls, prosperity within your fortresses."
19Ps 122:8 Because of my brothers and friends, I will say, "Peace be with you."
19Ps 122:9 Because of the house of the LORD our God, I will seek your good.
19Ps 123:1 [A song of ascents.] I lift my eyes to You, the One enthroned in heaven.
19Ps 123:2 Like a servant's eyes on His master's hand, like a servant girl's eyes on her mistress's hand, so our eyes are on the LORD our God until He shows us favor.
19Ps 123:3 Show us favor, LORD, show us favor, for we've had more than enough contempt.
19Ps 123:4 We've had more than enough scorn from the arrogant [and] contempt from the proud.
19Ps 124:1 [A Davidic song of ascents.] If the LORD had not been on our side-- let Israel say--
19Ps 124:2 If the LORD had not been on our side when men attacked us,
19Ps 124:3 then they would have swallowed us alive in their burning anger against us.
19Ps 124:4 Then the waters would have engulfed us; the torrent would have swept over us;
19Ps 124:5 the raging waters would have swept over us.
19Ps 124:6 Praise the LORD, who has not let us be ripped apart by their teeth.
19Ps 124:7 We have escaped like a bird from the hunter's net; the net is torn, and we have escaped.
19Ps 124:8 Our help is in the name of the LORD, the Maker of heaven and earth.
19Ps 125:1 [A song of ascents.] Those who trust in the LORD are like Mount Zion. It cannot be shaken; it remains forever.
19Ps 125:2 Jerusalem-- the mountains surround her. And the LORD surrounds His people, both now and forever.
19Ps 125:3 The scepter of the wicked will not remain over the land allotted to the righteous, so that the righteous will not apply their hands to injustice.
19Ps 125:4 Do what is good, LORD, to the good, to those whose hearts are upright.
19Ps 125:5 But as for those who turn aside to crooked ways, the LORD will banish them with the evildoers. Peace be with Israel.
19Ps 126:1 [A song of ascents.] When the LORD restored the fortunes of Zion, we were like those who dream.
19Ps 126:2 Our mouths were filled with laughter then, and our tongues with shouts of joy. Then they said among the nations, "The LORD has done great things for them."
19Ps 126:3 The LORD had done great things for us; we were joyful.
19Ps 126:4 Restore our fortunes, LORD, like watercourses in the Negev.
19Ps 126:5 Those who sow in tears will reap with shouts of joy.
19Ps 126:6 Though one goes along weeping, carrying the bag of seed, he will surely come back with shouts of joy, carrying his sheaves.
19Ps 127:1 [A Solomonic song of ascents.] Unless the LORD builds a house, its builders labor over it in vain; unless the LORD watches over a city, the watchman stays alert in vain.
19Ps 127:2 In vain you get up early and stay up late, eating food earned by hard work; certainly He gives sleep to the one He loves.
19Ps 127:3 Sons are indeed a heritage from the LORD, children, a reward.
19Ps 127:4 Like arrows in the hand of a warrior are the sons born in one's youth.
19Ps 127:5 Happy is the man who has filled his quiver with them. Such men will never be put to shame when they speak with [their] enemies at the city gate.
19Ps 128:1 [A song of ascents.] How happy is everyone who fears the LORD, who walks in His ways!
19Ps 128:2 You will surely eat what your hands have worked for. You will be happy, and it will go well for you.
19Ps 128:3 Your wife will be like a fruitful vine within your house, your sons, like young olive trees around your table.
19Ps 128:4 In this very way the man who fears the LORD will be blessed.
19Ps 128:5 May the LORD bless you from Zion, so that you will see the prosperity of Jerusalem all the days of your life,
19Ps 128:6 and will see your children's children! Peace be with Israel.
19Ps 129:1 [A song of ascents.] Since my youth they have often attacked me-- let Israel say--
19Ps 129:2 Since my youth they have often attacked me, but they have not prevailed against me.
19Ps 129:3 Plowmen plowed over my back; they made their furrows long.
19Ps 129:4 The LORD is righteous; He has cut the ropes of the wicked.
19Ps 129:5 Let all who hate Zion be driven back in disgrace.
19Ps 129:6 Let them be like grass on the rooftops, which withers before it grows up
19Ps 129:7 and can't even fill the hands of the reaper or the arms of the one who binds sheaves.
19Ps 129:8 Then none who pass by will say, "May the LORD's blessing be on you." We bless you in the name of the LORD.
19Ps 130:1 [A song of ascents.] Out of the depths I call to You, LORD!
19Ps 130:2 Lord, listen to my voice; let Your ears be attentive to my cry for help.
19Ps 130:3 LORD, if You considered sins, Lord, who could stand?
19Ps 130:4 But with You there is forgiveness, so that You may be revered.
19Ps 130:5 I wait for the LORD; I wait, and put my hope in His word.
19Ps 130:6 I [wait] for the Lord more than watchmen for the morning-- more than watchmen for the morning.
19Ps 130:7 Israel, put your hope in the LORD. For there is faithful love with the Lord, and with Him is redemption in abundance.
19Ps 130:8 And He will redeem Israel from all its sins.
19Ps 131:1 [A Davidic song of ascents.] LORD, my heart is not proud; my eyes are not haughty. I do not get involved with things too great or too difficult for me.
19Ps 131:2 Instead, I have calmed and quieted myself like a little weaned child with its mother; I am like a little child.
19Ps 131:3 Israel, put your hope in the LORD, both now and forever.
19Ps 132:1 [A song of ascents.] LORD, remember David and all the hardships he endured,
19Ps 132:2 and how he swore an oath to the LORD, making a vow to the Mighty One of Jacob:
19Ps 132:3 "I will not enter my house or get into my bed,
19Ps 132:4 I will not allow my eyes to sleep or my eyelids to slumber
19Ps 132:5 until I find a place for the LORD, a dwelling for the Mighty One of Jacob."
19Ps 132:6 We heard of [the ark] in Ephrathah; we found it in the fields of Jaar.
19Ps 132:7 Let us go to His dwelling place; let us worship at His footstool.
19Ps 132:8 Arise, LORD, come to Your resting place, You and the ark [that shows] Your strength.
19Ps 132:9 May Your priests be clothed with righteousness, and may Your godly people shout for joy.
19Ps 132:10 Because of Your servant David, do not reject Your anointed one.
19Ps 132:11 The LORD swore an oath to David, a promise He will not abandon: "I will set one of your descendants on your throne.
19Ps 132:12 If your sons keep My covenant and My decrees that I will teach them, their sons will also sit on your throne, forever."
19Ps 132:13 For the LORD has chosen Zion; He has desired it for His home:
19Ps 132:14 "This is My resting place forever; I will make My home here because I have desired it.
19Ps 132:15 I will abundantly bless its food; I will satisfy its needy with bread.
19Ps 132:16 I will clothe its priests with salvation, and its godly people will shout for joy.
19Ps 132:17 There I will make a horn grow for David; I have prepared a lamp for My anointed one.
19Ps 132:18 I will clothe his enemies with shame, but the crown he wears will be glorious."
19Ps 133:1 [A Davidic song of ascents.] How good and pleasant it is when brothers can live together!
19Ps 133:2 It is like fine oil on the head, running down on the beard, running down Aaron's beard, on his robes.
19Ps 133:3 It is like the dew of Hermon falling on the mountains of Zion. For there the LORD has appointed the blessing-- life forevermore.
19Ps 134:1 [A song of ascents.] Now praise the LORD, all you servants of the LORD who stand in the LORD's house at night!
19Ps 134:2 Lift up your hands in the holy place, and praise the LORD!
19Ps 134:3 May the LORD, Maker of heaven and earth, bless you from Zion.
19Ps 135:1 Hallelujah! Praise the name of the LORD. Give praise, you servants of the LORD
19Ps 135:2 who stand in the house of the LORD, in the courts of the house of our God.
19Ps 135:3 Praise the LORD, for the LORD is good; sing praise to His name, for it is delightful.
19Ps 135:4 For the LORD has chosen Jacob for Himself, Israel as His treasured possession.
19Ps 135:5 For I know that the LORD is great; our Lord is greater than all gods.
19Ps 135:6 The LORD does whatever He pleases in heaven and on earth, in the seas and all the depths.
19Ps 135:7 He causes the clouds to rise from the ends of the earth. He makes lightning for the rain and brings the wind from His storehouses.
19Ps 135:8 He struck down the firstborn of Egypt, both people and animals.
19Ps 135:9 He sent signs and wonders against you, Egypt, against Pharaoh and all his officials.
19Ps 135:10 He struck down many nations and slaughtered mighty kings:
19Ps 135:11 Sihon king of the Amorites, Og king of Bashan, and all the kings of Canaan.
19Ps 135:12 He gave their land as an inheritance, an inheritance to His people Israel.
19Ps 135:13 LORD, Your name [endures] forever, Your reputation, LORD, through all generations.
19Ps 135:14 For the LORD will judge His people and have compassion on His servants.
19Ps 135:15 The idols of the nations are of silver and gold, made by human hands.
19Ps 135:16 They have mouths, but cannot speak, eyes, but cannot see.
19Ps 135:17 They have ears, but cannot hear; indeed, there is no breath in their mouths.
19Ps 135:18 Those who make them are just like them, as are all who trust in them.
19Ps 135:19 House of Israel, praise the LORD! House of Aaron, praise the LORD!
19Ps 135:20 House of Levi, praise the LORD! You who revere the LORD, praise the LORD!
19Ps 135:21 May the LORD be praised from Zion; He dwells in Jerusalem. Hallelujah!
19Ps 136:1 Give thanks to the LORD, for He is good. His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:2 Give thanks to the God of gods. His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:3 Give thanks to the Lord of lords. His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:4 He alone does great wonders. His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:5 He made the heavens skillfully. His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:6 He spread the land on the waters. His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:7 He made the great lights: His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:8 the sun to rule by day, His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:9 the moon and stars to rule by night. His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:10 He struck the firstborn of the Egyptians His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:11 and brought Israel out from among them His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:12 with a strong hand and outstretched arm. His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:13 He divided the Red Sea His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:14 and led Israel through, His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:15 but hurled Pharaoh and his army into the Red Sea. His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:16 He led His people in the wilderness. His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:17 He struck down great kings His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:18 and slaughtered famous kings-- His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:19 Sihon king of the Amorites His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:20 and Og king of Bashan-- His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:21 and gave their land as an inheritance, His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:22 an inheritance to Israel His servant. His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:23 He remembered us in our humiliation His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:24 and rescued us from our foes. His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:25 He gives food to every creature. His love is eternal.
19Ps 136:26 Give thanks to the God of heaven! His love is eternal.
19Ps 137:1 By the rivers of Babylon-- there we sat down and wept when we remembered Zion.
19Ps 137:2 There we hung up our lyres on the poplar trees,
19Ps 137:3 for our captors there asked us for songs, and our tormentors, for rejoicing: "Sing us one of the songs of Zion."
19Ps 137:4 How can we sing the LORD's song on foreign soil?
19Ps 137:5 If I forget you, Jerusalem, may my right hand forget [its skill].
19Ps 137:6 May my tongue stick to the roof of my mouth if I do not remember you, if I do not exalt Jerusalem as my greatest joy!
19Ps 137:7 Remember, LORD, [what] the Edomites said that day at Jerusalem: "Destroy it! Destroy it down to its foundations!"
19Ps 137:8 Daughter Babylon, doomed to destruction, happy is the one who pays you back what you have done to us.
19Ps 137:9 Happy is he who takes your little ones and dashes them against the rocks.
19Ps 138:1 [Davidic.] I will give You thanks with all my heart; I will sing Your praise before the heavenly beings.
19Ps 138:2 I will bow down toward Your holy temple and give thanks to Your name for Your constant love and faithfulness. You have exalted Your name and Your promise above everything else.
19Ps 138:3 On the day I called, You answered me; You increased strength within me.
19Ps 138:4 All the kings on earth will give You thanks, LORD, when they hear what You have promised.
19Ps 138:5 They will sing of the LORD's ways, for the LORD's glory is great.
19Ps 138:6 Though the LORD is exalted, He takes note of the humble; but He knows the haughty from afar.
19Ps 138:7 If I walk in the thick of danger, You will preserve my life from the anger of my enemies. You will extend Your hand; Your right hand will save me.
19Ps 138:8 The LORD will fulfill [His purpose] for me. LORD, Your love is eternal; do not abandon the work of Your hands.
19Ps 139:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic psalm.] LORD, You have searched me and known me.
19Ps 139:2 You know when I sit down and when I stand up; You understand my thoughts from far away.
19Ps 139:3 You observe my travels and my rest; You are aware of all my ways.
19Ps 139:4 Before a word is on my tongue, You know all about it, LORD.
19Ps 139:5 You have encircled me; You have placed Your hand on me.
19Ps 139:6 [This] extraordinary knowledge is beyond me. It is lofty; I am unable to [reach] it.
19Ps 139:7 Where can I go to escape Your Spirit? Where can I flee from Your presence?
19Ps 139:8 If I go up to heaven, You are there; if I make my bed in Sheol, You are there.
19Ps 139:9 If I live at the eastern horizon [or] settle at the western limits,
19Ps 139:10 even there Your hand will lead me; Your right hand will hold on to me.
19Ps 139:11 If I say, "Surely the darkness will hide me, and the light around me will become night"--
19Ps 139:12 even the darkness is not dark to You. The night shines like the day; darkness and light are alike to You.
19Ps 139:13 For it was You who created my inward parts; You knit me together in my mother's womb.
19Ps 139:14 I will praise You, because I have been remarkably and wonderfully made. Your works are wonderful, and I know [this] very well.
19Ps 139:15 My bones were not hidden from You when I was made in secret, when I was formed in the depths of the earth.
19Ps 139:16 Your eyes saw me when I was formless; all [my] days were written in Your book and planned before a single one of them began.
19Ps 139:17 God, how difficult Your thoughts are for me [to comprehend]; how vast their sum is!
19Ps 139:18 If I counted them, they would outnumber the grains of sand; when I wake up, I am still with You.
19Ps 139:19 God, if only You would kill the wicked-- you bloodthirsty men, stay away from me--
19Ps 139:20 who invoke You deceitfully. Your enemies swear [by You] falsely.
19Ps 139:21 LORD, don't I hate those who hate You, and detest those who rebel against You?
19Ps 139:22 I hate them with extreme hatred; I consider them my enemies.
19Ps 139:23 Search me, God, and know my heart; test me and know my concerns.
19Ps 139:24 See if there is any offensive way in me; lead me in the everlasting way.
19Ps 140:1 [For the choir director. A Davidic psalm.] Rescue me, LORD, from evil men. Keep me safe from violent men
19Ps 140:2 who plan evil in their hearts. They stir up wars all day long.
19Ps 140:3 They make their tongues as sharp as a snake's bite; viper's venom is under their lips. Selah
19Ps 140:4 Protect me, LORD, from the clutches of the wicked. Keep me safe from violent men who plan to make me stumble.
19Ps 140:5 The proud hide a trap with ropes for me; they spread a net along the path and set snares for me. Selah
19Ps 140:6 I say to the LORD, "You are my God." Listen, LORD, to my cry for help.
19Ps 140:7 Lord God, my strong Savior, You shield my head on the day of battle.
19Ps 140:8 LORD, do not grant the desires of the wicked; do not let them achieve their goals. [Otherwise,] they will become proud. Selah
19Ps 140:9 As for the heads of those who surround me, let the trouble their lips cause overwhelm [them].
19Ps 140:10 Let hot coals fall on them. Let them be thrown into the fire, into the abyss, never again to rise.
19Ps 140:11 Do not let a slanderer stay in the land. Let evil relentlessly hunt down a violent man.
19Ps 140:12 I know that the LORD upholds the just cause of the poor, justice for the needy.
19Ps 140:13 Surely the righteous will praise Your name; the upright will live in Your presence.
19Ps 141:1 [A Davidic psalm.] LORD, I call on You; hurry to [help] me. Listen to my voice when I call on You.
19Ps 141:2 May my prayer be set before You as incense, the raising of my hands as the evening offering.
19Ps 141:3 LORD, set up a guard for my mouth; keep watch at the door of my lips.
19Ps 141:4 Do not let my heart turn to any evil thing or wickedly perform reckless acts with men who commit sin. Do not let me feast on their delicacies.
19Ps 141:5 Let the righteous one strike me-- it is [an act of] faithful love; let him rebuke me-- it is oil for my head; let me not refuse it. Even now my prayer is against the evil acts of the wicked.
19Ps 141:6 When their rulers will be thrown off the sides of a cliff, the people will listen to my words, for they are pleasing.
19Ps 141:7 As when one plows and breaks up the soil, [turning up rocks], so our bones have been scattered at the mouth of Sheol.
19Ps 141:8 But my eyes [look] to You, Lord God. I seek refuge in You; do not let me die.
19Ps 141:9 Protect me from the trap they have set for me, and from the snares of evildoers.
19Ps 141:10 Let the wicked fall into their own nets, while I pass [safely] by.
19Ps 142:1 [A Davidic Maskil. When he was in the cave. A prayer.] I cry aloud to the LORD; I plead aloud to the LORD for mercy.
19Ps 142:2 I pour out my complaint before Him; I reveal my trouble to Him.
19Ps 142:3 Although my spirit is weak within me, You know my way. Along this path I travel they have hidden a trap for me.
19Ps 142:4 Look to the right and see: no one stands up for me; there is no refuge for me; no one cares about me.
19Ps 142:5 I cry to You, LORD; I say, "You are my shelter, my portion in the land of the living."
19Ps 142:6 Listen to my cry, for I am very weak. Rescue me from those who pursue me, for they are too strong for me.
19Ps 142:7 Free me from prison so that I can praise Your name. The righteous will gather around me because You deal generously with me.
19Ps 143:1 [A Davidic psalm.] LORD, hear my prayer. In Your faithfulness listen to my plea, and in Your righteousness answer me.
19Ps 143:2 Do not bring Your servant into judgment, for no one alive is righteous in Your sight.
19Ps 143:3 For the enemy has pursued me, crushing me to the ground, making me live in darkness like those long dead.
19Ps 143:4 My spirit is weak within me; my heart is overcome with dismay.
19Ps 143:5 I remember the days of old; I meditate on all You have done; I reflect on the work of Your hands.
19Ps 143:6 I spread out my hands to You; I am like parched land before You. Selah
19Ps 143:7 Answer me quickly, LORD; my spirit fails. Don't hide Your face from me, or I will be like those going down to the Pit.
19Ps 143:8 Let me experience Your faithful love in the morning, for I trust in You. Reveal to me the way I should go, because I long for You.
19Ps 143:9 Rescue me from my enemies, LORD; I come to You for protection.
19Ps 143:10 Teach me to do Your will, for You are my God. May Your gracious Spirit lead me on level ground.
19Ps 143:11 Because of Your name, Yahweh, let me live. In Your righteousness deliver me from trouble,
19Ps 143:12 and in Your faithful love destroy my enemies. Wipe out all those who attack me, for I am Your servant.
19Ps 144:1 [Davidic.] May the LORD my rock be praised, who trains my hands for battle and my fingers for warfare.
19Ps 144:2 He is my faithful love and my fortress, my stronghold and my deliverer. He is my shield, and I take refuge in Him; He subdues my people under me.
19Ps 144:3 LORD, what is man, that You care for him, the son of man, that You think of him?
19Ps 144:4 Man is like a breath; his days are like a passing shadow.
19Ps 144:5 LORD, part Your heavens and come down. Touch the mountains, and they will smoke.
19Ps 144:6 Flash [Your] lightning and scatter the foe; shoot Your arrows and rout them.
19Ps 144:7 Reach down from on high; rescue me from deep water, and set me free from the grasp of foreigners
19Ps 144:8 whose mouths speak lies, whose right hands are deceptive.
19Ps 144:9 God, I will sing a new song to You; I will play on a ten-stringed harp for You--
19Ps 144:10 the One who gives victory to kings, who frees His servant David from the deadly sword.
19Ps 144:11 Set me free and rescue me from the grasp of foreigners whose mouths speak lies, whose right hands are deceptive.
19Ps 144:12 Then our sons will be like plants nurtured in their youth, our daughters, like corner pillars that are carved in the palace style.
19Ps 144:13 Our storehouses will be full, supplying all kinds of produce; our flocks will increase by thousands and tens of thousands in our open fields.
19Ps 144:14 Our cattle will be well fed. There will be no breach [in the walls], no going [into captivity], and no cry of lament in our public squares.
19Ps 144:15 Happy are the people with such [blessings]. Happy are the people whose God is the LORD.
19Ps 145:1 [A Davidic hymn.] I exalt You, my God the King, and praise Your name forever and ever.
19Ps 145:2 I will praise You every day; I will honor Your name forever and ever.
19Ps 145:3 Yahweh is great and is highly praised; His greatness is unsearchable.
19Ps 145:4 One generation will declare Your works to the next and will proclaim Your mighty acts.
19Ps 145:5 I will speak of Your glorious splendor and Your wonderful works.
19Ps 145:6 They will proclaim the power of Your awe-inspiring works, and I will declare Your greatness.
19Ps 145:7 They will give a testimony of Your great goodness and will joyfully sing of Your righteousness.
19Ps 145:8 The LORD is gracious and compassionate, slow to anger and great in faithful love.
19Ps 145:9 The LORD is good to everyone; His compassion [rests] on all He has made.
19Ps 145:10 All You have made will praise You, LORD; the godly will bless You.
19Ps 145:11 They will speak of the glory of Your kingdom and will declare Your might,
19Ps 145:12 informing [all] people of Your mighty acts and of the glorious splendor of Your kingdom.
19Ps 145:13 Your kingdom is an everlasting kingdom; Your rule is for all generations. The LORD is faithful in all His words and gracious in all His actions.
19Ps 145:14 The LORD helps all who fall; He raises up all who are oppressed.
19Ps 145:15 All eyes look to You, and You give them their food in due time.
19Ps 145:16 You open Your hand and satisfy the desire of every living thing.
19Ps 145:17 The LORD is righteous in all His ways and gracious in all His acts.
19Ps 145:18 The LORD is near all who call out to Him, all who call out to Him with integrity.
19Ps 145:19 He fulfills the desires of those who fear Him; He hears their cry for help and saves them.
19Ps 145:20 The LORD guards all those who love Him, but He destroys all the wicked.
19Ps 145:21 My mouth will declare the LORD's praise; let every living thing praise His holy name forever and ever.
19Ps 146:1 Hallelujah! My soul, praise the LORD.
19Ps 146:2 I will praise the LORD all my life; I will sing to the LORD as long as I live.
19Ps 146:3 Do not trust in nobles, in man, who cannot save.
19Ps 146:4 When his breath leaves him, he returns to the ground; on that day his plans die.
19Ps 146:5 Happy is the one whose help is the God of Jacob, whose hope is in the LORD his God,
19Ps 146:6 the Maker of heaven and earth, the sea and everything in them. He remains faithful forever,
19Ps 146:7 executing justice for the exploited and giving food to the hungry. The LORD frees prisoners.
19Ps 146:8 The LORD opens [the eyes of] the blind. The LORD raises up those who are oppressed. The LORD loves the righteous.
19Ps 146:9 The LORD protects foreigners and helps the fatherless and the widow, but He frustrates the ways of the wicked.
19Ps 146:10 The LORD reigns forever; Zion, your God [reigns] for all generations. Hallelujah!
19Ps 147:1 Hallelujah! How good it is to sing to our God, for praise is pleasant and lovely.
19Ps 147:2 The LORD rebuilds Jerusalem; He gathers Israel's exiled people.
19Ps 147:3 He heals the brokenhearted and binds up their wounds.
19Ps 147:4 He counts the number of the stars; He gives names to all of them.
19Ps 147:5 Our Lord is great, vast in power; His understanding is infinite.
19Ps 147:6 The LORD helps the afflicted but brings the wicked to the ground.
19Ps 147:7 Sing to the LORD with thanksgiving; play the lyre to our God,
19Ps 147:8 who covers the sky with clouds, prepares rain for the earth, and causes grass to grow on the hills.
19Ps 147:9 He provides the animals with their food, and the young ravens, what they cry for.
19Ps 147:10 He is not impressed by the strength of a horse; He does not value the power of a man.
19Ps 147:11 The LORD values those who fear Him, those who put their hope in His faithful love.
19Ps 147:12 Exalt the LORD, Jerusalem; praise your God, Zion!
19Ps 147:13 For He strengthens the bars of your gates and blesses your children within you.
19Ps 147:14 He endows your territory with prosperity; He satisfies you with the finest wheat.
19Ps 147:15 He sends His command throughout the earth; His word runs swiftly.
19Ps 147:16 He spreads snow like wool; He scatters frost like ashes;
19Ps 147:17 He throws His hailstones like crumbs. Who can withstand His cold?
19Ps 147:18 He sends His word and melts them; He unleashes His winds, and the waters flow.
19Ps 147:19 He declares His word to Jacob, His statutes and judgments to Israel.
19Ps 147:20 He has not done this for any nation; they do not know [His] judgments. Hallelujah!
19Ps 148:1 Hallelujah! Praise the LORD from the heavens; praise Him in the heights.
19Ps 148:2 Praise Him, all His angels; praise Him, all His hosts.
19Ps 148:3 Praise Him, sun and moon; praise Him, all you shining stars.
19Ps 148:4 Praise Him, highest heavens, and you waters above the heavens.
19Ps 148:5 Let them praise the name of the LORD, for He commanded, and they were created.
19Ps 148:6 He set them in position forever and ever; He gave an order that will never pass away.
19Ps 148:7 Praise the LORD from the earth, all sea monsters and ocean depths,
19Ps 148:8 lightning and hail, snow and cloud, powerful wind that executes His command,
19Ps 148:9 mountains and all hills, fruit trees and all cedars,
19Ps 148:10 wild animals and all cattle, creatures that crawl and flying birds,
19Ps 148:11 kings of the earth and all peoples, princes and all judges of the earth,
19Ps 148:12 young men as well as young women, old and young together.
19Ps 148:13 Let them praise the name of the LORD, for His name alone is exalted. His majesty covers heaven and earth.
19Ps 148:14 He has raised up a horn for His people, praise from all His godly ones, from the Israelites, the people close to Him. Hallelujah!
19Ps 149:1 Hallelujah! Sing to the LORD a new song, His praise in the assembly of the godly.
19Ps 149:2 Let Israel celebrate its Maker; let the children of Zion rejoice in their King.
19Ps 149:3 Let them praise His name with dancing and make music to Him with tambourine and lyre.
19Ps 149:4 For the LORD takes pleasure in His people; He adorns the humble with salvation.
19Ps 149:5 Let the godly celebrate in triumphal glory; let them shout for joy on their beds.
19Ps 149:6 Let the exaltation of God be in their mouths and a two-edged sword in their hands,
19Ps 149:7 inflicting vengeance on the nations and punishment on the peoples,
19Ps 149:8 binding their kings with chains and their dignitaries with iron shackles,
19Ps 149:9 carrying out the judgment decreed against them. This honor is for all His godly people. Hallelujah!
19Ps 150:1 Hallelujah! Praise God in His sanctuary. Praise Him in His mighty heavens.
19Ps 150:2 Praise Him for His powerful acts; praise Him for His abundant greatness.
19Ps 150:3 Praise Him with trumpet blast; praise Him with harp and lyre.
19Ps 150:4 Praise Him with tambourine and dance; praise Him with flute and strings.
19Ps 150:5 Praise Him with resounding cymbals; praise Him with clashing cymbals.
19Ps 150:6 Let everything that breathes praise the LORD. Hallelujah!
