23Is 1:1 The vision concerning Judah and Jerusalem that Isaiah son of Amoz saw during the reignsof Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah.
23Is 1:2 Listen, heavens, and pay attention, earth, for the LORD has spoken: "I have raised children and brought them up, but they have rebelled against Me.
23Is 1:3 The ox knows its owner, and the donkey its master's feeding-trough, [but] Israel does not know; My people do not understand."
23Is 1:4 Oh-- sinful nation, people weighed down with iniquity, brood of evildoers, depraved children! They have abandoned the LORD; they have despised the Holy One of Israel; they have turned their backs [on Him].
23Is 1:5 Why do you want more beatings? Why do you keep on rebelling? The whole head is hurt, and the whole heart is sick.
23Is 1:6 From the sole of the foot even to the head, no spot is uninjured-- wounds, welts, and festering sores not cleansed, bandaged, or soothed with oil.
23Is 1:7 Your land is desolate, your cities burned with fire; before your very eyes foreigners devour your fields-- a desolation overthrown by foreigners.
23Is 1:8 Daughter Zion is abandoned like a shelter in a vineyard, like a shack in a cucumber field, like a besieged city.
23Is 1:9 If the LORD of Hosts had not left us a few survivors, we would be like Sodom, we would resemble Gomorrah.
23Is 1:10 Hear the word of the LORD, you rulers of Sodom! Listen to the instruction of our God, you people of Gomorrah!
23Is 1:11 "What are all your sacrifices to Me?" asks the LORD. "I have had enough of burnt offerings and rams and the fat of well-fed cattle; I have no desire for the blood of bulls, lambs, or male goats.
23Is 1:12 When you come to appear before Me, who requires this from you-- [this] trampling of My courts?
23Is 1:13 Stop bringing useless offerings. I despise [your] incense. New Moons and Sabbaths, and the calling of solemn assemblies-- I cannot stand iniquity with a festival.
23Is 1:14 I hate your New Moons and prescribed festivals. They have become a burden to Me; I am tired of putting up with [them].
23Is 1:15 When you lift up your hands [in prayer], I will refuse to look at you; even if you offer countless prayers, I will not listen. Your hands are covered with blood.
23Is 1:16 "Wash yourselves. Cleanse yourselves. Remove your evil deeds from My sight. Stop doing evil.
23Is 1:17 Learn to do what is good. Seek justice. Correct the oppressor. Defend the rights of the fatherless. Plead the widow's cause.
23Is 1:18 "Come, let us discuss this," says the LORD. "Though your sins are like scarlet, they will be as white as snow; though they are as red as crimson, they will be like wool.
23Is 1:19 If you are willing and obedient, you will eat the good things of the land.
23Is 1:20 But if you refuse and rebel, you will be devoured by the sword." For the mouth of the LORD has spoken.
23Is 1:21 The faithful city-- what an adulteress she has become! She was once full of justice. Righteousness once dwelt in her-- but now, murderers!
23Is 1:22 Your silver has become dross, your beer is diluted with water.
23Is 1:23 Your rulers are rebels, friends of thieves. They all love graft and chase after bribes. They do not defend the rights of the fatherless, and the widow's case never comes before them."
23Is 1:24 Therefore the Lord God of Hosts, the Mighty One of Israel, declares: "Ah, I will gain satisfaction against My foes; I will take revenge against My enemies.
23Is 1:25 I will turn My hand against you and will burn away your dross completely; I will remove all your impurities.
23Is 1:26 I will restore your judges to what they once were, and your advisers to their former state. Afterwards you will be called the Righteous City, a Faithful City."
23Is 1:27 Zion will be redeemed by justice, her repentant ones by righteousness.
23Is 1:28 But both rebels and sinners will be destroyed, and those who abandon the LORD will perish.
23Is 1:29 Indeed, they will be ashamed of the sacred trees you desired, and you will be embarrassed because of the gardens you have chosen.
23Is 1:30 For you will become like an oak whose leaves are withered, and like a garden without water.
23Is 1:31 The strong one will become tinder, and his work a spark; both will burn together, with no one to quench [the flames].
23Is 2:1 The vision that Isaiah son of Amoz saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem:
23Is 2:2 In the last days the mountain of the LORD's house will be established at the top of the mountains and will be raised above the hills. All nations will stream to it,
23Is 2:3 and many peoples will come and say, "Come, let us go up to the mountain of the LORD, to the house of the God of Jacob. He will teach us about His ways so that we may walk in His paths." For instruction will go out of Zion and the word of the LORD from Jerusalem.
23Is 2:4 He will settle disputes among the nations and provide arbitration for many peoples. They will turn their swords into plows and their spears into pruning knives. Nations will not take up the sword against [other] nations, and they will never again train for war.
23Is 2:5 House of Jacob, come and let us walk in the LORD's light.
23Is 2:6 For You have abandoned Your people, the house of Jacob, because they are full of [ divination] from the East and of fortune-tellers like the Philistines. They are in league with foreigners.
23Is 2:7 Their land is full of silver and gold, and there is no limit to their treasures; their land is full of horses, and there is no limit to their chariots.
23Is 2:8 Their land is full of idols; they bow down to the work of their hands, to what their fingers have made.
23Is 2:9 So humanity is brought low, and man is humbled. Do not forgive them!
23Is 2:10 Go into the rocks and hide in the dust from the terror of the LORD and from His majestic splendor.
23Is 2:11 Human pride will be humbled, and the loftiness of men will be brought low; the LORD alone will be exalted on that day.
23Is 2:12 For a day belonging to the LORD of Hosts is [coming] against all that is proud and lofty, against all that is lifted up-- it will be humbled--
23Is 2:13 against all the cedars of Lebanon, lofty and lifted up, against all the oaks of Bashan,
23Is 2:14 against all the high mountains, against all the lofty hills,
23Is 2:15 against every high tower, against every fortified wall,
23Is 2:16 against every ship of Tarshish, and against every splendid sea vessel.
23Is 2:17 So human pride will be brought low, and the loftiness of men will be humbled; the LORD alone will be exalted on that day.
23Is 2:18 The idols will vanish completely.
23Is 2:19 People will go into caves in the rocks and holes in the ground, away from the terror of the LORD and from His majestic splendor, when He rises to terrify the earth.
23Is 2:20 On that day people will throw their silver and gold idols, which they made to worship, to the moles and the bats.
23Is 2:21 They will go into the caves of the rocks and the crevices in the cliffs, away from the terror of the LORD and from His majestic splendor, when He rises to terrify the earth.
23Is 2:22 Put no more trust in man, who has only the breath in his nostrils. What is he really worth?
23Is 3:1 Observe this: The Lord God of Hosts is about to remove from Jerusalem and from Judah every kind of security: the entire supply of bread and water,
23Is 3:2 the hero and warrior, the judge and prophet, the fortune-teller and elder,
23Is 3:3 the commander of 50 and the dignitary, the counselor, cunning magician, and necromancer.
23Is 3:4 "I will make youths their leaders, and the unstable will govern them."
23Is 3:5 The people will oppress one another, man against man, neighbor against neighbor; the youth will act arrogantly toward the elder, and the worthless toward the honorable.
23Is 3:6 A man will even seize his brother in his father's house, [saying:] "You have a cloak-- you be our leader! This heap of rubble will be under your control."
23Is 3:7 On that day he will cry out, saying: "I'm not a healer. I don't even have food or clothing in my house. Don't make me the leader of the people!"
23Is 3:8 For Jerusalem has stumbled and Judah has fallen because they have spoken and acted against the LORD, defying His glorious presence.
23Is 3:9 The look on their faces testifies against them, and like Sodom, they flaunt their sin. They do not conceal it. Woe to them! For they have brought evil on themselves.
23Is 3:10 Tell the righteous that it will go well [for them], for they will eat the fruit of their deeds.
23Is 3:11 Woe to the wicked-- [it will go] badly [for them], for what they have done will be done to them.
23Is 3:12 Youths oppress My people, and women rule over them. My people, your leaders mislead you; they confuse the direction of your paths.
23Is 3:13 The LORD rises to argue the case and stands to judge the people.
23Is 3:14 The LORD brings [this] charge against the elders and leaders of His people: "You have devastated the vineyard. The plunder from the poor is in your houses.
23Is 3:15 Why do you crush My people and grind the faces of the poor?" says the Lord God of Hosts.
23Is 3:16 The LORD also says: Because the daughters of Zion are haughty, walking with heads held high and seductive eyes, going along with prancing steps, jingling their ankle bracelets,
23Is 3:17 the Lord will put scabs on the heads of the daughters of Zion, and the LORD will shave their foreheads bare.
23Is 3:18 On that day the Lord will strip their finery: ankle bracelets, headbands, crescents,
23Is 3:19 pendants, bracelets, veils,
23Is 3:20 headdresses, ankle jewelry, sashes, perfume bottles, amulets,
23Is 3:21 signet rings, nose rings,
23Is 3:22 festive robes, capes, cloaks, purses,
23Is 3:23 garments, linen clothes, turbans, and veils.
23Is 3:24 Instead of perfume there will be a stench; instead of a belt, a rope; instead of beautifully styled hair, baldness; instead of fine clothes, sackcloth; instead of beauty, branding.
23Is 3:25 Your men will fall by the sword, your warriors in battle.
23Is 3:26 Then her gates will lament and mourn; deserted, she will sit on the ground.
23Is 4:1 On that day seven women will seize one man, saying, "We will eat our own bread and provide our own clothing. Just let us be called by your name. Take away our disgrace."
23Is 4:2 On that day the branch of the LORD will be beautiful and glorious, and the fruit of the land will be the pride and glory of Israel's survivors.
23Is 4:3 Whoever remains in Zion and whoever is left in Jerusalem will be called holy-- all in Jerusalem who are destined to live--
23Is 4:4 when the Lord has washed away the filth of the daughters of Zion and cleansed the bloodguilt from the heart of Jerusalem by a spirit of judgment and a spirit of burning.
23Is 4:5 Then the LORD will create a cloud of smoke by day and a glowing flame of fire by night over the entire site of Mount Zion and over its assemblies. For there will be a canopy over all the glory,
23Is 4:6 and there will be a booth for shade from heat by day, and a refuge and shelter from storm and rain.
23Is 5:1 I will sing about the one I love, a song about my loved one's vineyard: The one I love had a vineyard on a very fertile hill.
23Is 5:2 He broke up the soil, cleared it of stones, and planted it with the finest vines. He built a tower in the middle of it and even hewed out a winepress there. He expected it to yield good grapes, but it yielded worthless grapes.
23Is 5:3 So now, residents of Jerusalem and men of Judah, please judge between Me and My vineyard.
23Is 5:4 What more could I have done for My vineyard than I did? Why, when I expected a yield of good grapes, did it yield worthless grapes?
23Is 5:5 Now I will tell you what I am about to do to My vineyard: I will remove its hedge, and it will be consumed; I will tear down its wall, and it will be trampled.
23Is 5:6 I will make it a wasteland. It will not be pruned or weeded; thorns and briers will grow up. I will also give orders to the clouds that rain should not fall on it.
23Is 5:7 For the vineyard of the LORD of Hosts is the house of Israel, and the men of Judah, the plant He delighted in. He looked for justice but saw injustice, for righteousness, but heard cries of wretchedness.
23Is 5:8 Woe to those who add house to house and join field to field until there is no more room and you alone are left in the land.
23Is 5:9 In my hearing the LORD of Hosts [has taken an oath]: Indeed, many houses will become desolate, grand and lovely ones without inhabitants.
23Is 5:10 For a ten-acre vineyard will yield only six gallons, and 10 bushels of seed will yield only [one] bushel.
23Is 5:11 Woe to those who rise early in the morning in pursuit of beer, who linger into the evening, inflamed by wine.
23Is 5:12 At their feasts they have lyre, harp, tambourine, flute, and wine. They do not perceive the LORD's actions, and they do not see the work of His hands.
23Is 5:13 Therefore My people go into exile because they lack knowledge; the dignitaries are starving, and the masses are parched with thirst.
23Is 5:14 Therefore Sheol enlarges its throat and opens wide its enormous jaws, and down go Zion's dignitaries, her masses, her crowds, and those who carouse in her!
23Is 5:15 Humanity is brought low, man is humbled, and haughty eyes are humbled.
23Is 5:16 But the LORD of Hosts is exalted by His justice, and the holy God is distinguished by righteousness.
23Is 5:17 Lambs will graze as [if in] their own pastures, and strangers will eat [among] the ruins of the rich.
23Is 5:18 Woe to those who drag wickedness with cords of deceit and [pull] sin along with cart ropes,
23Is 5:19 to those who say: "Let Him hurry up and do His work quickly so that we can see it! Let the plan of the Holy One of Israel take place so that we can know it!"
23Is 5:20 Woe to those who call evil good and good evil, who substitute darkness for light and light for darkness, who substitute bitter for sweet and sweet for bitter.
23Is 5:21 Woe to those who are wise in their own opinion and clever in their own sight.
23Is 5:22 Woe to those who are heroes at drinking wine, who are fearless at mixing beer,
23Is 5:23 who acquit the guilty for a bribe and deprive the innocent of justice.
23Is 5:24 Therefore, as a tongue of fire consumes straw and as dry grass shrivels in the flame, so their roots will become like something rotten and their blossoms will blow away like dust, for they have rejected the instruction of the LORD of Hosts, and they have despised the word of the Holy One of Israel.
23Is 5:25 Therefore the LORD's anger burns against His people. He raised His hand against them and struck them; the mountains quaked, and their corpses were like garbage in the streets. In all this, His anger is not removed, and His hand is still raised [to strike].
23Is 5:26 He raises a signal flag for the distant nations and whistles for them from the ends of the earth. Look-- how quickly and swiftly they come!
23Is 5:27 None of them grows weary or stumbles; no one slumbers or sleeps. No belt is loose, and no sandal strap broken.
23Is 5:28 Their arrows are sharpened, and all their bows strung. Their horses' hooves are like flint; their [chariot] wheels are like a whirlwind.
23Is 5:29 Their roaring is like a lion's; they roar like young lions; they growl and seize their prey and carry [it] off, and no one can rescue [it].
23Is 5:30 On that day they will roar over it, like the roaring of the sea. When one looks at the land, there will be darkness and distress; light will be obscured by clouds.
23Is 6:1 In the year that King Uzziah died, I saw the Lord seated on a high and lofty throne, and His robe filled the temple.
23Is 6:2 Seraphim were standing above Him; each one had six wings: with two he covered his face, with two he covered his feet, and with two he flew.
23Is 6:3 And one called to another: Holy, holy, holy is the LORD of Hosts; His glory fills the whole earth.
23Is 6:4 The foundations of the doorways shook at the sound of their voices, and the temple was filled with smoke.
23Is 6:5 Then I said: Woe is me, for I am ruined, because I am a man of unclean lips and live among a people of unclean lips, [and] because my eyes have seen the King, the LORD of Hosts.
23Is 6:6 Then one of the seraphim flew to me, and in his hand was a glowing coal that he had taken from the altar with tongs.
23Is 6:7 He touched my mouth [with it] and said: Now that this has touched your lips, your wickedness is removed, and your sin is atoned for.
23Is 6:8 Then I heard the voice of the Lord saying: Who should I send? Who will go for Us? I said: Here I am. Send me.
23Is 6:9 And He replied: Go! Say to these people: Keep listening, but do not understand; keep looking, but do not perceive.
23Is 6:10 Dull the minds of these people; deafen their ears and blind their eyes; otherwise they might see with their eyes and hear with their ears, understand with their minds, turn back, and be healed.
23Is 6:11 Then I said, "Until when, Lord?" And He replied: Until cities lie in ruins without inhabitants, houses are without people, the land is ruined and desolate,
23Is 6:12 and the LORD drives the people far away, leaving great emptiness in the land.
23Is 6:13 Though a tenth will remain in the land, it will be burned again. Like the terebinth or the oak, which leaves a stump when felled, the holy seed is the stump.
23Is 7:1 This took place during the reign of Ahaz, son of Jotham, son of Uzziah king of Judah: Rezin king of Aram, along with Pekah, son of Remaliah, king of Israel, waged war against Jerusalem, but he could not succeed.
23Is 7:2 When it became known to the house of David that Aram had occupied Ephraim, the heart of Ahaz and the hearts of his people trembled like trees of a forest shaking in a wind.
23Is 7:3 Then the LORD said to Isaiah, "Go out with your son Shear-jashub to meet Ahaz at the end of the conduit of the upper pool, by the road to the Fuller's Field.
23Is 7:4 Say to him: Calm down and be quiet. Don't be afraid or fainthearted because of these two smoldering stubs of firebrands, Rezin of Aram, and the son of Remaliah.
23Is 7:5 For Aram, along with Ephraim and the son of Remaliah, has plotted harm against you. They say:
23Is 7:6 Let us go up against Judah, terrorize it, and conquer it for ourselves. Then we can install Tabeel's son as king in it."
23Is 7:7 This is what the Lord God says: It will not happen; it will not occur.
23Is 7:8 The head of Aram is Damascus, the head of Damascus is Rezin (within 65 years Ephraim will be too shattered to be a people),
23Is 7:9 the head of Ephraim is Samaria, and the head of Samaria is the son of Remaliah. If you do not stand firm in your faith, then you will not stand at all.
23Is 7:10 Then the LORD spoke again to Ahaz:
23Is 7:11 "Ask for a sign from the LORD your God-- from the depths of Sheol to the heights of heaven."
23Is 7:12 But Ahaz replied, "I will not ask. I will not test the LORD."
23Is 7:13 Isaiah said, "Listen, house of David! Is it not enough for you to try the patience of men? Will you also try the patience of my God?
23Is 7:14 Therefore, the Lord Himself will give you a sign: The virgin will conceive, have a son, and name him Immanuel.
23Is 7:15 By the time he learns to reject what is bad and choose what is good, he will be eating butter and honey.
23Is 7:16 For before the boy knows to reject what is bad and choose what is good, the land of the two kings you dread will be abandoned.
23Is 7:17 The LORD will bring on you, your people, and the house of your father, such a time as has never been since Ephraim separated from Judah-- the king of Assyria [is coming].
23Is 7:18 On that day the LORD will whistle to the fly that is at the farthest streams of the Nile and to the bee that is in the land of Assyria.
23Is 7:19 All of them will come and settle in the steep ravines, in the clefts of the rocks, in all the thornbushes, and in all the water holes.
23Is 7:20 On that day the Lord will use a razor hired from beyond the Euphrates River-- the king of Assyria-- to shave the head, the hair on the legs, and to remove the beard as well.
23Is 7:21 On that day a man will raise a young cow and two sheep,
23Is 7:22 and from the abundant milk they give he will eat butter, for every survivor in the land will eat butter and honey.
23Is 7:23 And on that day every place where there were 1,000 vines, worth 1,000 pieces of silver, will become thorns and briers.
23Is 7:24 A man will go there with bow and arrows because the whole land will be thorns and briers.
23Is 7:25 You will not go to all the hills that were once tilled with a hoe, for fear of the thorns and briers. [Those hills] will be places for oxen to graze and for sheep to trample.
23Is 8:1 Then the LORD said to me, "Take a large piece of parchment and write on it with an ordinary pen: Maher-shalal-hash-baz.
23Is 8:2 I have appointed trustworthy witnesses-- Uriah the priest and Zechariah son of Jeberechiah."
23Is 8:3 I was then intimate with the prophetess, and she conceived and gave birth to a son. The LORD said to me, "Name him Maher-shalal-hash-baz,
23Is 8:4 for before the boy knows how to call out father or mother, the wealth of Damascus and the spoils of Samaria will be carried off to the king of Assyria."
23Is 8:5 The LORD spoke to me again:
23Is 8:6 Because these people rejected the slowly flowing waters of Shiloah and rejoiced with Rezin and the son of Remaliah,
23Is 8:7 the Lord will certainly bring against them the mighty rushing waters of the Euphrates River-- the king of Assyria and all his glory. It will overflow its channels and spill over all its banks.
23Is 8:8 It will pour into Judah, flood over it, and sweep through, reaching up to the neck; and its spreading streams will fill your entire land, Immanuel!
23Is 8:9 Band together, peoples, and be broken; pay attention, all you distant lands; prepare for war, and be broken; prepare for war, and be broken.
23Is 8:10 Devise a plan; it will fail. Make a prediction; it will not happen. For God is with us.
23Is 8:11 For this is what the LORD said to me with great power, to keep me from going the way of this people:
23Is 8:12 Do not call everything an alliance these people say is an alliance. Do not fear what they fear; do not be terrified.
23Is 8:13 You are to regard only the LORD of Hosts as holy. Only He should be feared; only He should be held in awe.
23Is 8:14 He will be a sanctuary; but for the two houses of Israel, He will be a stone to stumble over and a rock to trip over, and a trap and a snare to the inhabitants of Jerusalem.
23Is 8:15 Many will stumble over these; they will fall and be broken; they will be snared and captured.
23Is 8:16 Bind up the testimony. Seal up the instruction among my disciples.
23Is 8:17 I will wait for the Lord, who is hiding His face from the house of Jacob. I will wait for Him.
23Is 8:18 Here I am with the children the LORD has given me to be signs and wonders in Israel from the LORD of Hosts who dwells on Mount Zion.
23Is 8:19 When they say to you, "Consult the spirits of the dead and the spiritists who chirp and mutter," shouldn't a people consult their God? [Should they consult] the dead on behalf of the living?
23Is 8:20 To the law and to the testimony! If they do not speak according to this word, there will be no dawn for them.
23Is 8:21 They will wander through the land, dejected and hungry. When they are famished, they will become enraged, and, looking upward, will curse their king and their God.
23Is 8:22 They will look toward the earth and see only distress, darkness, and the gloom of affliction, and they will be driven into thick darkness.
23Is 9:1  Nevertheless, the gloom of the distressed land will not be like that of the former times when He humbled the land of Zebulun and the land of Naphtali. But in the future He will bring honor to the Way of the Sea, to the land east of the Jordan, and to Galilee of the nations.
23Is 9:2  The people walking in darkness have seen a great light; on those living in the land of darkness, a light has dawned.
23Is 9:3 You have enlarged the nation and increased its joy. [The people] have rejoiced before You as they rejoice at harvest time and as they rejoice when dividing spoils.
23Is 9:4 For You have shattered their burdensome yoke and the rod on their shoulders, the staff of their oppressor, just as [You did] on the day of Midian.
23Is 9:5 For the trampling boot of battle and the bloodied garments of war will be burned as fuel for the fire.
23Is 9:6 For a child will be born for us, a son will be given to us, and the government will be on His shoulders. He will be named Wonderful Counselor, Mighty God, Eternal Father, Prince of Peace.
23Is 9:7 The dominion will be vast, and its prosperity will never end. He will reign on the throne of David and over his kingdom, to establish and sustain it with justice and righteousness from now on and forever. The zeal of the LORD of Hosts will accomplish this.
23Is 9:8 The Lord sent a message against Jacob; it came against Israel.
23Is 9:9 All the people-- Ephraim and the inhabitants of Samaria-- will know it. They will say with pride and arrogance:
23Is 9:10 "The bricks have fallen, but we will rebuild with cut stones; the sycamores have been cut down, but we will replace them with cedars."
23Is 9:11 The LORD has raised up Rezin's adversaries against him and stirred up his enemies.
23Is 9:12 Aram from the east and Philistia from the west have consumed Israel with open mouths. In all this, His anger is not removed, and His hand is still raised [to strike].
23Is 9:13 The people did not turn to Him who struck them; they did not seek the LORD of Hosts.
23Is 9:14 So the LORD cut off Israel's head and tail, palm branch and reed in a single day.
23Is 9:15 The head is the elder, the honored one; the tail is the prophet, the lying teacher.
23Is 9:16 The leaders of the people mislead [them], and those they mislead are swallowed up.
23Is 9:17 Therefore the Lord does not rejoice over Israel's young men and has no compassion on its fatherless and widows, for everyone is a godless evildoer, and every mouth speaks folly. In all this, His anger is not removed, and His hand is still raised [to strike].
23Is 9:18 For wickedness burns like a fire that consumes thorns and briers and kindles the forest thickets so that they go up in a column of smoke.
23Is 9:19 The land is scorched by the wrath of the LORD of Hosts, and the people are like fuel for the fire. No one has compassion on his brother.
23Is 9:20 They carve [meat] on the right, but they are [still] hungry; they have eaten on the left, but they are [still] not satisfied. Each one eats the flesh of his own arm.
23Is 9:21 Manasseh is with Ephraim, and Ephraim with Manasseh; together, both are against Judah. In all this, His anger is not removed, and His hand is still raised [to strike].
23Is 10:1 Woe to those enacting crooked statutes and writing oppressive laws
23Is 10:2 to keep the poor from getting a fair trial and to deprive the afflicted among my people of justice, so that widows can be their spoil and they can plunder the fatherless.
23Is 10:3 What will you do on the day of punishment when devastation comes from far away? Who will you run to for help? Where will you leave your wealth?
23Is 10:4 [There will be nothing to do] except crouch among the prisoners or fall among the slain. In all this, His anger is not removed, and His hand is still raised [to strike].
23Is 10:5 Woe to Assyria, the rod of My anger-- the staff in their hands is My wrath.
23Is 10:6 I will send him against a godless nation; I will command him [to go] against a people destined for My rage, to take spoils, to plunder, and to trample them down like clay in the streets.
23Is 10:7 But this is not what he intends; this is not what he plans. It is his intent to destroy and to cut off many nations.
23Is 10:8 For he says: Aren't all my commanders kings?
23Is 10:9 Isn't Calno like Carchemish? Isn't Hamath like Arpad? Isn't Samaria like Damascus?
23Is 10:10 As my hand seized the idolatrous kingdoms, whose idols exceeded those of Jerusalem and Samaria,
23Is 10:11 and as I did to Samaria and its idols will I not also do to Jerusalem and its idols?
23Is 10:12 But when the Lord finishes all His work against Mount Zion and Jerusalem, [He will say,] "I will punish the king of Assyria for his arrogant acts and the proud look in his eyes."
23Is 10:13 For he said: I have done [this] by my own strength and wisdom, for I am clever. I abolished the borders of nations and plundered their treasures; like a mighty warrior, I subjugated the inhabitants.
23Is 10:14 My hand has reached out, as if into a nest, to seize the wealth of the nations. Like one gathering abandoned eggs, I gathered the whole earth. No wing fluttered; no beak opened or chirped.
23Is 10:15 Does an ax exalt itself above the one who chops with it? Does a saw magnify itself above the one who saws with it? As if a staff could wave those who lift it! As if a rod could lift what isn't wood!
23Is 10:16 Therefore the Lord God of Hosts will inflict an emaciating disease on the well-fed of Assyria, and He will kindle a burning fire under its glory.
23Is 10:17 Israel's Light will become a fire, and its Holy One, a flame. In one day it will burn up Assyria's thorns and thistles.
23Is 10:18 He will completely destroy the glory of its forests and orchards as a sickness consumes a person.
23Is 10:19 The remaining trees of its forest will be so few in number that a child could count them.
23Is 10:20 On that day the remnant of Israel and the survivors of the house of Jacob will no longer depend on the one who struck them, but they will faithfully depend on the LORD, the Holy One of Israel.
23Is 10:21 The remnant will return, the remnant of Jacob, to the Mighty God.
23Is 10:22 Israel, even if your people were as numerous as the sand of the sea, [only] a remnant of them will return. Destruction has been decreed; justice overflows.
23Is 10:23 For throughout the land the Lord God of Hosts is carrying out a destruction that was decreed.
23Is 10:24 Therefore, the Lord God of Hosts says this: "My people who dwell in Zion, do not fear Assyria, though he strikes you with a rod and raises his staff over you as the Egyptians did.
23Is 10:25 In just a little while My wrath will be spent and My anger will turn to their destruction."
23Is 10:26 And the LORD of Hosts will brandish a whip against him as [He did when He] struck Midian at the rock of Oreb; and He will raise His staff over the sea as [He did] in Egypt.
23Is 10:27 On that day his burden will fall from your shoulders, and his yoke from your neck. The yoke will be broken because of [his] fatness.
23Is 10:28 Assyria has come to Aiath and has gone through Migron, storing his equipment at Michmash.
23Is 10:29 They crossed over at the ford, saying, "We will spend the night at Geba." The people of Ramah are trembling; those at Gibeah of Saul have fled.
23Is 10:30 Cry aloud, daughter of Gallim! Listen, Laishah! Anathoth is miserable.
23Is 10:31 Madmenah has fled. The inhabitants of Gebim have sought refuge.
23Is 10:32 Today he will stand at Nob, shaking his fist at the mountain of Daughter Zion, the hill of Jerusalem.
23Is 10:33 Look, the Lord God of Hosts will chop off the branches with terrifying power, and the tall [trees] will be cut down, the high [trees] felled.
23Is 10:34 He is clearing the thickets of the forest with an ax, and Lebanon with its majesty will fall.
23Is 11:1 Then a shoot will grow from the stump of Jesse, and a branch from his roots will bear fruit.
23Is 11:2 The Spirit of the LORD will rest on Him-- a Spirit of wisdom and understanding, a Spirit of counsel and strength, a Spirit of knowledge and of the fear of the LORD.
23Is 11:3 His delight will be in the fear of the LORD. He will not judge by what He sees with His eyes, He will not execute justice by what He hears with His ears,
23Is 11:4 but He will judge the poor righteously and execute justice for the oppressed of the land. He will strike the land with discipline from His mouth, and He will kill the wicked with a command from His lips.
23Is 11:5 Righteousness and faithfulness will be a belt around His waist.
23Is 11:6 The wolf will live with the lamb, and the leopard will lie down with the goat. The calf, the young lion, and the fatling will be together, and a child will lead them.
23Is 11:7 The cow and the bear will graze, their young ones will lie down together, and the lion will eat straw like an ox.
23Is 11:8 An infant will play beside the cobra's pit, and a toddler will put his hand into a snake's den.
23Is 11:9 No one will harm or destroy on My entire holy mountain, for the land will be as full of the knowledge of the LORD as the sea is filled with water.
23Is 11:10 On that day the root of Jesse will stand as a banner for the peoples. The nations will seek Him, and His resting place will be glorious.
23Is 11:11 On that day the Lord will [extend] His hand a second time to recover-- from Assyria, Egypt, Pathros, Cush, Elam, Shinar, Hamath, and the coasts and islands of the west-- the remnant of His people who survive.
23Is 11:12 He will lift up a banner for the nations and gather the dispersed of Israel; He will collect the scattered of Judah from the four corners of the earth.
23Is 11:13 Ephraim's envy will cease; Judah's harassment will end. Ephraim will no longer be envious of Judah, and Judah will not harass Ephraim.
23Is 11:14 But they will swoop down on the Philistine flank to the west. Together they will plunder the people of the east. They will extend their power over Edom and Moab, and the Ammonites will be their subjects.
23Is 11:15 The LORD will divide the Gulf of Suez. He will wave His hand over the Euphrates with His mighty wind and will split it into seven streams, letting people walk through on foot.
23Is 11:16 There will be a highway for the remnant of His people who will survive from Assyria, as there was for Israel when they came up from the land of Egypt.
23Is 12:1 On that day you will say: "I will praise You, LORD, although You were angry with me. Your anger has turned away, and You have had compassion on me.
23Is 12:2 Indeed, God is my salvation. I will trust [Him] and not be afraid. Because Yah, the LORD, is my strength and my song, He has become my salvation."
23Is 12:3 You will joyfully draw water from the springs of salvation,
23Is 12:4 and on that day you will say: "Give thanks to the LORD; proclaim His name! Celebrate His deeds among the peoples. Declare that His name is exalted.
23Is 12:5 Sing to the LORD, for He has done glorious things. Let this be known throughout the earth.
23Is 12:6 Cry out and sing, citizen of Zion, for the Holy One of Israel is among you in [His] greatness."
23Is 13:1 An oracle against Babylon that Isaiah son of Amoz saw:
23Is 13:2 Lift up a banner on a barren mountain. Call out to them. Wave your hand, and they will go through the gates of the nobles.
23Is 13:3 I have commanded My chosen ones; I have also called My warriors, who exult in My triumph, to execute My wrath.
23Is 13:4 Listen, a tumult on the mountains, like that of a mighty people! Listen, an uproar among the kingdoms, like nations being gathered together! The LORD of Hosts is mobilizing an army for war.
23Is 13:5 They are coming from a far land, from the distant horizon-- the LORD and the weapons of His wrath-- to destroy the whole country.
23Is 13:6 Wail! For the day of the LORD is near. It will come like destruction from the Almighty.
23Is 13:7 Therefore everyone's hands will become weak, and every man's heart will melt.
23Is 13:8 They will be horrified; pain and agony will seize [them]; they will be in anguish like a woman in labor. They will look at each other, their faces flushed with fear.
23Is 13:9 Look, the day of the LORD is coming-- cruel, with rage and burning anger-- to make the earth a desolation and to destroy the sinners on it.
23Is 13:10 Indeed, the stars of the sky and its constellations will not give their light. The sun will be dark when it rises, and the moon will not shine.
23Is 13:11 I will bring disaster on the world, and their [own] iniquity, on the wicked. I will put an end to the pride of the arrogant and humiliate the insolence of tyrants.
23Is 13:12 I will make man scarcer than gold, and mankind more rare than the gold of Ophir.
23Is 13:13 Therefore I will make the heavens tremble, and the earth will shake from its foundations at the wrath of the LORD of Hosts, on the day of His burning anger.
23Is 13:14 Like wandering gazelles and like sheep without a shepherd, each one will turn to his own people, each one will flee to his own land.
23Is 13:15 Whoever is found will be stabbed, and whoever is caught will die by the sword.
23Is 13:16 Their children will be smashed [to death] before their eyes; their houses will be looted, and their wives raped.
23Is 13:17 Look! I am stirring up the Medes against them, who cannot be bought off with silver and who have no desire for gold.
23Is 13:18 [Their] bows will cut young men to pieces. They will have no compassion on little ones; they will not look with pity on children.
23Is 13:19 And Babylon, the jewel of the kingdoms, the glory of the pride of the Chaldeans, will be like Sodom and Gomorrah when God overthrew them.
23Is 13:20 It will never be inhabited or lived in from generation to generation; a nomad will not pitch his tent there, and shepherds will not let [their flocks] rest there.
23Is 13:21 But wild animals will lie down there, and owls will fill the houses. Ostriches will dwell there, and wild goats will leap about.
23Is 13:22 Hyenas will howl in the fortresses, and jackals, in the luxurious palaces. Babylon's time is almost up; her days are almost over.
23Is 14:1 For the LORD will have compassion on Jacob and will choose Israel again. He will settle them on their own land. The foreigner will join them and be united with the house of Jacob.
23Is 14:2 The nations will escort Israel and bring it to its homeland. Then the house of Israel will possess them as male and female slaves in the LORD's land. They will make captives of their captors and will rule over their oppressors.
23Is 14:3 When the LORD gives you rest from your pain, torment, and the hard labor you were forced to do,
23Is 14:4 you will sing this song [of contempt] about the king of Babylon and say: How the oppressor has quieted down, and how the raging has become quiet!
23Is 14:5 The LORD has broken the staff of the wicked, the scepter of the rulers.
23Is 14:6 It struck the peoples in anger with unceasing blows. It subdued the nations in rage with relentless persecution.
23Is 14:7 All the earth is calm and at rest; people shout with a ringing cry.
23Is 14:8 Even the cypresses and the cedars of Lebanon rejoice over you: "Since you have been laid low, no woodcutter has come against us."
23Is 14:9 Sheol below is eager to greet your coming. He stirs up the spirits of the departed for you-- all the rulers of the earth. He makes all the kings of the nations rise from their thrones.
23Is 14:10 They all respond to you, saying: "You too have become as weak as we are; you have become like us!
23Is 14:11 Your splendor has been brought down to Sheol, [along with] the music of your harps. Maggots are spread out under you, and worms cover you."
23Is 14:12 Shining morning star, how you have fallen from the heavens! You destroyer of nations, you have been cut down to the ground.
23Is 14:13 You said to yourself: "I will ascend to the heavens; I will set up my throne above the stars of God. I will sit on the mount of the [gods'] assembly, in the remotest parts of the North.
23Is 14:14 I will ascend above the highest clouds; I will make myself like the Most High."
23Is 14:15 But you will be brought down to Sheol into the deepest regions of the Pit.
23Is 14:16 Those who see you will stare at you; they will look closely at you: "Is this the man who caused the earth to tremble, who shook the kingdoms,
23Is 14:17 who turned the world into a wilderness, who trampled its cities and would not release the prisoners to return home?"
23Is 14:18 All the kings of the nations lie in splendor, each in his own tomb.
23Is 14:19 But you are thrown out without a grave, like a worthless branch, covered by those slain with the sword and dumped into a rocky pit like a trampled corpse.
23Is 14:20 You will not join them in burial, because you destroyed your land and slaughtered your own people. The offspring of evildoers will never be remembered.
23Is 14:21 Prepare a place of slaughter for his sons, because of the iniquity of their fathers. They never rise up to possess a land or fill the surface of the earth with cities.
23Is 14:22 "I will rise up against them"-- the declaration of the LORD of Hosts-- "and I will cut off from Babylon her reputation, remnant, offspring, and posterity"-- the LORD's declaration.
23Is 14:23 "I will make her a swampland and a region for wild animals, and I will sweep her away with a broom of destruction." [This is] the declaration of the LORD of Hosts.
23Is 14:24 The LORD of Hosts has sworn: As I have planned, so it will be; as I have purposed it, so it will happen.
23Is 14:25 I will break Assyria in My land; I will tread him down on My mountain. Then his yoke will be taken from them, and his burden will be removed from their shoulders.
23Is 14:26 This is the plan prepared for the whole earth, and this is the hand stretched out against all the nations.
23Is 14:27 The LORD of Hosts Himself has planned it; therefore, who can stand in its way? It is His hand that is outstretched, so who can turn it back?
23Is 14:28 In the year that King Ahaz died, this oracle came:
23Is 14:29 Don't rejoice, all of you [in] Philistia, because the rod of the one who struck you is broken. For a viper will come out of the root of a snake, and from its egg comes a flying serpent.
23Is 14:30 Then the firstborn of the poor will be well fed, and the impoverished will lie down in safety, but I will kill your root with hunger, and your remnant will be slain.
23Is 14:31 Wail, you gates! Cry out, city! Tremble with fear, all Philistia! For a cloud of dust is coming from the north, and there is no one missing from [the invader's] ranks.
23Is 14:32 What answer will be given to the messengers from that nation? The LORD has founded Zion, and His afflicted people find refuge in her.
23Is 15:1 An oracle against Moab: Ar in Moab is devastated, destroyed in a night. Kir in Moab is devastated, destroyed in a night.
23Is 15:2 Dibon went up to its temple to weep at its high places. Moab wails on Nebo and at Medeba. Every head is shaved; every beard is cut off.
23Is 15:3 In its streets they wear sackcloth; on its rooftops and in its public squares everyone wails, falling down and weeping.
23Is 15:4 Heshbon and Elealeh cry out; their voices are heard as far away as Jahaz. Therefore the soldiers of Moab cry out, and they tremble.
23Is 15:5 My heart cries out over Moab, whose fugitives [flee] as far as Zoar, to Eglath-shelishiyah; they go up the slope of Luhith weeping; they raise a cry of destruction on the road to Horonaim.
23Is 15:6 The waters of Nimrim are desolate; the grass is withered, the foliage is gone, and the vegetation has vanished.
23Is 15:7 So they carry their wealth and belongings over the Wadi of the Willows.
23Is 15:8 For their cry echoes throughout the territory of Moab. Their wailing reaches Eglaim; their wailing reaches Beer-elim.
23Is 15:9 The waters of Dibon are full of blood, but I will bring on Dibon even more [than this]-- a lion for those who escape from Moab, and for the survivors in the land.
23Is 16:1 Send lambs to the ruler of the land, from Sela in the desert to the mountain of Daughter Zion.
23Is 16:2 Like a bird fleeing, forced from the nest, the daughters of Moab will be at the fords of the Arnon.
23Is 16:3 Give us counsel and make a decision. [Shelter us] at noonday with shade that is as dark as night. Hide the refugee; do not betray the one who flees.
23Is 16:4 Let my refugees stay with you; be a refuge for Moab from the aggressor. When the oppressor has gone, destruction has ended, and marauders have vanished from the land.
23Is 16:5 Then in the tent of David a throne will be established by faithful love. A judge who seeks what is right and is quick to execute justice will sit on the throne forever.
23Is 16:6 We have heard of Moab's pride-- how very proud he is-- his haughtiness, his pride, his arrogance, and his empty boasting.
23Is 16:7 Therefore let Moab wail; let every one of them wail for Moab. Mourn, you who are completely devastated, for the raisin cakes of Kir-hareseth.
23Is 16:8 For Heshbon's terraced vineyards and the grapevines of Sibmah have withered. The rulers of the nations have trampled its choice vines that reached as far as Jazer and spread to the desert. Their shoots spread out and reached the Dead Sea.
23Is 16:9 So I join with Jazer to weep for the vines of Sibmah; I drench Heshbon and Elealeh with my tears. Triumphant shouts have fallen silent over your summer [fruit] and your harvest.
23Is 16:10 Joy and rejoicing have been removed from the orchard; no one is singing or shouting for joy in the vineyards. No one tramples grapes in the winepresses. I have put an end to the shouting.
23Is 16:11 Therefore I moan like [the sound of] a lyre for Moab, [as does] my innermost being for Kir-heres.
23Is 16:12 When Moab appears on the high place, when he tires himself out and comes to his sanctuary to pray, it will do him no good.
23Is 16:13 This is the message that the LORD previously announced about Moab.
23Is 16:14 And now the LORD says, "In three years, as a hired worker counts years, Moab's splendor will become an object of contempt, in spite of a very large population. And those who are left will be few and weak."
23Is 17:1 An oracle against Damascus: Look, Damascus is no longer a city. It has become a ruined heap.
23Is 17:2 The cities of Aroer are forsaken; they will be [places] for flocks. They will lie down without fear.
23Is 17:3 The fortress disappears from Ephraim, and a kingdom from Damascus. The remnant of Aram will be like the splendor of the Israelites. [This is] the declaration of the LORD of Hosts.
23Is 17:4 On that day the splendor of Jacob will fade, and his healthy body will become emaciated.
23Is 17:5 It will be as if a reaper had gathered standing grain-- his arm harvesting the heads of grain-- and as if one had gleaned heads of grain in the valley of Rephaim.
23Is 17:6 Only gleanings will be left in Israel, as if an olive tree had been beaten-- two or three berries at the very top of the tree, four or five on its fruitful branches. [This is] the declaration of the LORD, the God of Israel.
23Is 17:7 On that day people will look to their Maker and will turn their eyes to the Holy One of Israel.
23Is 17:8 They will not look to the altars they made with their hands or to the Asherahs and incense altars they made with their fingers.
23Is 17:9 On that day their strong cities will be like the abandoned woods and mountaintops that were abandoned because of the Israelites; there will be desolation.
23Is 17:10 For you have forgotten the God of your salvation, and you have failed to remember the rock of your strength; therefore you will plant beautiful plants and set out cuttings from exotic vines.
23Is 17:11 On the day that you plant, you will help them to grow, and in the morning you will help your seed to sprout, [but] the harvest will vanish on the day of disease and incurable pain.
23Is 17:12 Ah! The roar of many peoples-- they roar like the roaring of the seas. The raging of the nations-- they rage like the raging of mighty waters.
23Is 17:13 The nations rage like the raging of many waters. He rebukes them, and they flee far away, driven before the wind like chaff on the hills and like dead thistles before a gale.
23Is 17:14 In the evening-- sudden terror! Before morning-- it is gone! This is the fate of those who plunder us and the lot of those who ravage us.
23Is 18:1 Ah! The land of buzzing insect wings beyond the rivers of Cush
23Is 18:2 sends envoys by sea, in reed vessels on the waters. Go, swift messengers, to a nation tall and smooth-skinned, to a people feared near and far, a powerful nation with a strange language, whose land is divided by rivers.
23Is 18:3 All you inhabitants of the world and you who live on the earth, when a banner is raised on the mountains, look! When a trumpet sounds, listen!
23Is 18:4 For, the LORD said to me: I will quietly look out from My place, like shimmering heat in sunshine, like a rain cloud in harvest heat.
23Is 18:5 For before the harvest, when the blossoming is over and the blossom becomes a ripening grape, He will cut off the shoots with a pruning knife, and tear away and remove the branches.
23Is 18:6 They will all be left for the birds of prey on the hills and for the wild animals of the land. The birds will spend the summer on them, and all the animals, the winter on them.
23Is 18:7 At that time a gift will be brought to the LORD of Hosts from a people tall and smooth-skinned, a people feared near and far, a powerful nation with a strange language, whose land is divided by rivers-- to Mount Zion, the place of the name of the LORD of Hosts.
23Is 19:1 An oracle against Egypt: Look, the LORD rides on a swift cloud and is coming to Egypt. Egypt's idols will tremble before Him, and Egypt's heart will melt within it.
23Is 19:2 I will provoke Egypt against Egypt; each will fight against his brother and each against his friend, city against city, kingdom against kingdom.
23Is 19:3 Egypt's spirit will be disturbed within it, and I will frustrate its plans. Then they will seek idols, ghosts, spirits of the dead, and spiritists.
23Is 19:4 I will deliver Egypt into the hands of harsh masters, and a strong king will rule it. [This is] the declaration of the Lord God of Hosts.
23Is 19:5 The waters of the sea will dry up, and the river will be parched and dry.
23Is 19:6 The channels will stink; they will dwindle, and Egypt's canals will be parched. Reed and rush will die.
23Is 19:7 The reeds by the Nile, by the mouth of the river, and all the cultivated areas of the Nile will wither, blow away, and vanish.
23Is 19:8 Then the fishermen will mourn. All those who cast hooks into the Nile will lament, and those who spread nets on the water will shrivel up.
23Is 19:9 Those who work with flax will be dismayed; the combers and weavers will turn pale.
23Is 19:10 [Egypt's] weavers will be dejected; all her wage earners will be demoralized.
23Is 19:11 The princes of Zoan are complete fools; Pharaoh's wisest advisers give stupid advice! How can you say to Pharaoh, "I am one of the wise, a student of eastern kings."
23Is 19:12 Where then are your wise men? Let them tell you and reveal what the LORD of Hosts has planned against Egypt.
23Is 19:13 The princes of Zoan have been fools; the princes of Memphis are deceived. Her tribal chieftains have led Egypt astray.
23Is 19:14 The LORD has mixed within her a spirit of confusion. [The leaders] have made Egypt stagger in all she does, as a drunkard staggers in his vomit.
23Is 19:15 No head or tail, palm or reed, will be able to do anything for Egypt.
23Is 19:16 On that day Egypt will be like women. She will tremble with fear because of the threatening hand of the LORD of Hosts when He raises it against her.
23Is 19:17 The land of Judah will terrify Egypt; whenever Judah is mentioned, Egypt will tremble because of what the LORD of Hosts has planned against it.
23Is 19:18 On that day five cities in the land of Egypt will speak the language of Canaan and swear loyalty to the LORD of Hosts. One of the cities will be called the City of the Sun.
23Is 19:19 On that day there will be an altar to the LORD in the center of the land of Egypt and a pillar to the LORD near her border.
23Is 19:20 It will be a sign and witness to the LORD of Hosts in the land of Egypt. When they cry out to the LORD because of their oppressors, He will send them a savior and leader, and he will rescue them.
23Is 19:21 The LORD will make Himself known to Egypt, and Egypt will know the LORD on that day. They will offer sacrifices and offerings; they will make vows to the LORD and fulfill them.
23Is 19:22 The LORD will strike Egypt, striking and healing. Then they will return to the LORD and He will hear their prayers and heal them.
23Is 19:23 On that day there will be a highway from Egypt to Assyria. Assyria will go to Egypt, Egypt to Assyria, and Egypt will worship with Assyria.
23Is 19:24 On that day Israel will form a triple [alliance] with Egypt and Assyria-- a blessing within the land.
23Is 19:25 The LORD of Hosts will bless them, saying, "Blessed be Egypt My people, Assyria My handiwork, and Israel My inheritance."
23Is 20:1 In the year that the commander-in-chief, sent by Sargon king of Assyria, came to Ashdod and attacked and captured it--
23Is 20:2 during that time the LORD had spoken through Isaiah son of Amoz, saying, "Go, take off your sackcloth and remove the sandals from your feet," and he did so, going naked and barefoot--
23Is 20:3 the LORD said, "As My servant Isaiah has gone naked and barefoot three years as a sign and omen against Egypt and Cush,
23Is 20:4 so the king of Assyria will lead the captives of Egypt and the exiles of Cush, young and old alike, naked and barefoot, with bared buttocks, to Egypt's shame.
23Is 20:5 Those who made Cush their hope and Egypt their boast will be dismayed and ashamed.
23Is 20:6 And the inhabitants of this coastland will say on that day: Look, this is what has happened to those we relied on and fled to for help to rescue [us] from the king of Assyria! Now, how will we escape?"
23Is 21:1 An oracle against the desert by the sea: Like storms that pass over the Negev, it comes from the desert, from the land of terror.
23Is 21:2 A troubling vision is declared to me: "The treacherous one acts treacherously, and the destroyer destroys. Advance, Elam! Lay siege, you Medes! I will put an end to all her groaning."
23Is 21:3 Therefore I am filled with anguish. Pain grips me, like the pain of a woman in labor. I am too perplexed to hear, too dismayed to see.
23Is 21:4 My heart staggers; horror terrifies me. He has turned my last glimmer of hope into sheer terror.
23Is 21:5 Prepare a table, and spread out a carpet! Eat and drink! Rise up, you princes, and oil the shields!
23Is 21:6 For the Lord has said to me, "Go, post a lookout; let him report what he sees.
23Is 21:7 When he sees riders-- pairs of horsemen, riders on donkeys, riders on camels-- pay close attention."
23Is 21:8 Then the lookout reported, "Lord, I stand on the watchtower all day, and I stay at my post all night.
23Is 21:9 Look, riders come-- horsemen in pairs." And he answered, saying, "Babylon has fallen, has fallen. All the idols of her gods have been shattered on the ground."
23Is 21:10 My downtrodden and threshed people, I have declared to you what I have heard from the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel.
23Is 21:11 An oracle against Dumah: One calls to me from Seir, "Watchman, what is [left] of the night? Watchman, what is [left] of the night?"
23Is 21:12 The watchman said, "Morning has come, and also night. If you want to ask, ask! Come back again."
23Is 21:13 An oracle against Arabia: You will camp for the night in the scrublands of the desert, you caravans of Dedanites.
23Is 21:14 Bring water for the thirsty. The inhabitants of the land of Tema meet the refugees with food.
23Is 21:15 For they have fled from swords, from the drawn sword, and from the bent bow, from the stress of battle.
23Is 21:16 For the Lord said this to me: "Within one year, as a hired worker counts years, all the glory of Kedar will be gone.
23Is 21:17 The remaining Kedarite archers will be few in number." For the LORD, the God of Israel, has spoken.
23Is 22:1 An oracle against the Valley of Vision: What's the matter with you? Why have all of you gone up to the rooftops?
23Is 22:2 The noisy city, the jubilant town, is filled with revelry. Your dead did not die by the sword; they were not killed in battle.
23Is 22:3 All your rulers have fled together, captured without a bow. All your fugitives were captured together; they had fled far away.
23Is 22:4 Therefore I said, "Look away from me! Let me weep bitterly! Do not try to comfort me about the destruction of my dear people."
23Is 22:5 For the Lord God of Hosts had a day of tumult, trampling, and bewilderment in the Valley of Vision-- people shouting and crying to the mountains;
23Is 22:6 Elam took up a quiver with chariots and horsemen, and Kir uncovered the shield.
23Is 22:7 Your best valleys were full of chariots, and horsemen were positioned at the gates.
23Is 22:8 He removed the defenses of Judah. On that day you looked to the weapons in the House of the Forest.
23Is 22:9 You saw that there were many breaches in [the walls of] the city of David. You collected water from the lower pool.
23Is 22:10 You counted the houses of Jerusalem so that you could tear them down to fortify the wall.
23Is 22:11 You made a reservoir between the walls for the waters of the ancient pool, but you did not look to the One who made it, or consider the One who created it long ago.
23Is 22:12 On that day the Lord God of Hosts called for weeping, for wailing, for shaven heads, and for the wearing of sackcloth.
23Is 22:13 But look: joy and gladness, butchering of cattle, slaughtering of sheep, eating of meat, and drinking of wine-- "Let us eat and drink, for tomorrow we die!"
23Is 22:14 The LORD of Hosts has revealed [this] in my hearing: "This sin of yours will never be wiped out." The Lord God of Hosts has spoken.
23Is 22:15 The Lord God of Hosts said: "Go to Shebna, that steward who is in charge of the palace, [and say to him:]
23Is 22:16 What are you doing here? Who authorized you to carve out a tomb for yourself here, carving your tomb on the height and cutting a crypt for yourself out of rock?
23Is 22:17 Look, young man! The LORD is about to shake you violently. He will take hold of you,
23Is 22:18 wind you up into a ball, and sling you into a wide land. There you will die, and there your glorious chariots will be-- a disgrace to the house of your lord.
23Is 22:19 I will remove you from your office; you will be ousted from your position.
23Is 22:20 "On that day I will call for my servant, Eliakim son of Hilkiah.
23Is 22:21 I will clothe him with your robe and tie your sash around him. I will put your authority into his hand, and he will be like a father to the inhabitants of Jerusalem and to the House of Judah.
23Is 22:22 I will place the key of the House of David on his shoulder; what he opens, no one can close; what he closes, no one can open.
23Is 22:23 I will drive him, like a peg, into a firm place. He will be a throne of honor for his father's house.
23Is 22:24 They will hang on him the whole burden of his father's house: the descendants and the offshoots-- all the small vessels, from bowls to every kind of jar.
23Is 22:25 On that day"-- the declaration of the LORD of Hosts-- "the peg that was driven into a firm place will give way, be cut off, and fall, and the load on it will be destroyed." Indeed, the LORD has spoken.
23Is 23:1 An oracle against Tyre: Wail, ships of Tarshish, for your haven has been destroyed. Word has reached them from the land of Cyprus.
23Is 23:2 Mourn, inhabitants of the coastland, you merchants of Sidon; your agents have crossed the sea
23Is 23:3 on many waters. Tyre's revenue was the grain from Shihor-- the harvest of the Nile. She was the merchant among the nations.
23Is 23:4 Be ashamed Sidon, the stronghold of the sea, for the sea has spoken: "I have not been in labor or given birth. I have not raised young men [or] brought up young women."
23Is 23:5 When the news reaches Egypt, they will be in anguish over the news about Tyre.
23Is 23:6 Cross over to Tarshish; wail, inhabitants of the coastland!
23Is 23:7 Is this your jubilant [city], whose origin was in ancient times, whose feet have taken her to settle far away?
23Is 23:8 Who planned this against Tyre, the bestower of crowns, whose traders are princes, whose merchants are the honored ones of the earth?
23Is 23:9 The LORD of Hosts planned it, to desecrate all [its] glorious beauty, to disgrace all the honored ones of the earth.
23Is 23:10 Overflow your land like the Nile, daughter of Tarshish; there is no longer anything to restrain [you].
23Is 23:11 He stretched out His hand over the sea; He made kingdoms tremble. The LORD has commanded that the Canaanite fortresses be destroyed.
23Is 23:12 He said, "You will not rejoice any more, ravished young woman, daughter of Sidon. Get up and cross over to Cyprus-- even there you will have no rest!"
23Is 23:13 Look at the land of Chaldeans-- a people who no longer exist. Assyria destined it for wild beasts. They set up their siege towers and stripped its palaces. They made it a ruin.
23Is 23:14 Wail, ships of Tarshish, because your fortress is destroyed!
23Is 23:15 On that day Tyre will be forgotten for 70 years-- the life span of one king. At the end of 70 years, what the song [says] about the prostitute will happen to Tyre:
23Is 23:16 Pick up [your] harp, stroll through the city, prostitute forgotten [by men]. Play skillfully, sing many a song, and you will be thought of again.
23Is 23:17 And at the end of the 70 years, the LORD will restore Tyre and she will go back into business, prostituting herself with all the kingdoms of the world on the face of the earth.
23Is 23:18 But her profits and wages will be dedicated to the LORD. They will not be stored or saved, for her profit will go to those who live in the LORD's presence, to provide them with ample food and sacred clothing.
23Is 24:1 Look, the LORD is stripping the earth bare and making it desolate. He will twist its surface and scatter its inhabitants:
23Is 24:2 people and priest alike, servant and master, female servant and mistress, buyer and seller, lender and borrower, creditor and debtor.
23Is 24:3 The earth will be stripped completely bare and will be totally plundered, for the LORD has spoken this message.
23Is 24:4 The earth mourns and withers; the world wastes away and withers; the exalted people of the earth waste away.
23Is 24:5 The earth is polluted by its inhabitants, for they have transgressed teachings, overstepped decrees, and broken the everlasting covenant.
23Is 24:6 Therefore a curse has consumed the earth, and its inhabitants have become guilty; the earth's inhabitants have been burned, and only a few survive.
23Is 24:7 The new wine mourns; the vine withers. All the carousers now groan.
23Is 24:8 The joyful tambourines have ceased. The noise of the jubilant has stopped. The joyful lyre has ceased.
23Is 24:9 They no longer sing and drink wine; beer is bitter to those who drink it.
23Is 24:10 The city of chaos is shattered; every house is closed to entry.
23Is 24:11 In the streets they cry for wine. All joy grows dark; earth's rejoicing goes into exile.
23Is 24:12 Only desolation remains in the city; its gate has collapsed in ruins.
23Is 24:13 For this is how it will be on earth among the nations: like a harvested olive tree, like a gleaning after a grape harvest.
23Is 24:14 They raise their voices, they sing out; they proclaim in the west the majesty of the LORD.
23Is 24:15 Therefore in the east honor the LORD! In the islands of the west [honor] the name of the LORD, the God of Israel.
23Is 24:16 From the ends of the earth we hear songs: The Splendor of the Righteous One. But I said, "I waste away! I waste away! Woe is me." The treacherous act treacherously; the treacherous deal very treacherously.
23Is 24:17 Terror, pit, and snare [await] you who dwell on the earth.
23Is 24:18 Whoever flees at the sound of terror will fall into a pit, and whoever escapes from the pit will be caught in a snare. For the windows are opened from above, and the foundations of the earth are shaken.
23Is 24:19 The earth is completely devastated; the earth is split open; the earth is violently shaken.
23Is 24:20 The earth staggers like a drunkard and sways like a hut. Earth's rebellion weighs it down, and it falls, never to rise again.
23Is 24:21 On that day the LORD will punish the host of heaven above and kings of the earth below.
23Is 24:22 They will be gathered together like prisoners in a pit. They will be confined to a dungeon; after many days they will be punished.
23Is 24:23 The moon will be put to shame and the sun disgraced, because the LORD of Hosts will reign as king on Mount Zion in Jerusalem, and He will [display His] glory in the presence of His elders.
23Is 25:1 LORD, You are my God; I will exalt You. I will praise Your name, for You have accomplished wonders, plans [formed] long ago, with perfect faithfulness.
23Is 25:2 For You have turned the city into a pile of rubble, a fortified city, into a ruin; the fortress of barbarians is no longer a city; it will never be rebuilt.
23Is 25:3 Therefore, a strong people will honor You. A city of violent people will fear You.
23Is 25:4 For You have been a stronghold for the poor, a stronghold for the humble person in his distress, a refuge from the rain, a shade from the heat. When the breath of the violent is like rain [against] a wall,
23Is 25:5 like heat in a dry land, You subdue the uproar of barbarians. As the shade of a cloud [cools] the heat of the day, [so] He stills the song of the violent.
23Is 25:6 The LORD of Hosts will prepare a feast for all the peoples on this mountain-- a feast of aged wine, choice meat, finely aged wine.
23Is 25:7 On this mountain [He] will destroy the [burial] shroud, the shroud over all the peoples, the sheet covering all the nations;
23Is 25:8 He will destroy death forever. The Lord God will wipe away the tears from every face and remove His people's disgrace from the whole earth, for the LORD has spoken.
23Is 25:9 On that day it will be said, "Look, this is our God; we have waited for Him, and He has saved us. This is the Lord; we have waited for Him. Let us rejoice and be glad in His salvation."
23Is 25:10 For the LORD's power will rest on this mountain. But Moab will be trampled in his place as straw is trampled in a dung pile.
23Is 25:11 He will spread out his arms in the middle of it, as a swimmer spreads out [his arms] to swim. His pride will be brought low, along with the trickery of his hands.
23Is 25:12 The high-walled fortress will be brought down, thrown to the ground, to the dust.
23Is 26:1 On that day this song will be sung in the land of Judah: We have a strong city. Salvation is established as walls and ramparts.
23Is 26:2 Open the gates so a righteous nation can come in-- one that remains faithful.
23Is 26:3 You will keep in perfect peace the mind [that is] dependent [on You], for it is trusting in You.
23Is 26:4 Trust in the LORD forever, because in Yah, the LORD, is an everlasting rock!
23Is 26:5 For He has humbled those who live in lofty places-- an inaccessible city. He brings it down; He brings it down to the ground; He throws it to the dust.
23Is 26:6 Feet trample it, the feet of the humble, the steps of the poor.
23Is 26:7 The path of the righteous is level; You clear a straight path for the righteous.
23Is 26:8 Yes, LORD, we wait for You in the path of Your judgments. Our desire is for Your name and renown.
23Is 26:9 I long for You in the night; yes, my spirit within me diligently seeks You, for when Your judgments are [in] the land, the inhabitants of the world will learn righteousness.
23Is 26:10 [But if] the wicked is shown favor, he does not learn righteousness. In a righteous land he acts unjustly and does not see the majesty of the LORD.
23Is 26:11 LORD, Your hand is lifted up [to take action], but they do not see it. They will see [Your] zeal for [Your] people, and they will be put to shame. The fire for Your adversaries will consume them!
23Is 26:12 LORD, You will establish peace for us, for You have also done all our work for us.
23Is 26:13 LORD, our God, other lords than You have ruled over us, but we remember Your name alone.
23Is 26:14 The dead do not live; departed spirits do not rise up. Indeed, You have visited and destroyed them; You have wiped out all memory of them.
23Is 26:15 You have added to the nation, LORD. You have added to the nation; You are honored. You have expanded all the borders of the land.
23Is 26:16 LORD, they went to You in their distress; they poured out whispered [prayers because] Your discipline [fell] on them.
23Is 26:17 As a pregnant woman about to give birth writhes and cries out in her pains, so we were before You, LORD.
23Is 26:18 We became pregnant, we writhed in pain; we gave birth to wind. We have won no victories on earth, and the earth's inhabitants have not fallen.
23Is 26:19 Your dead will live; their bodies will rise. Awake and sing, you who dwell in the dust! For you will be covered with the morning dew, and the earth will bring forth the departed spirits.
23Is 26:20 Go, my people, enter your rooms and close your doors behind you. Hide for a little while until the wrath has passed.
23Is 26:21 For look, the LORD is coming from His place to punish the inhabitants of the earth for their iniquity. The earth will reveal the blood shed on it and will no longer conceal her slain.
23Is 27:1 On that day the LORD with His harsh, great, and strong sword, will bring judgment on Leviathan, the fleeing serpent-- Leviathan, the twisting serpent. He will slay the monster that is in the sea.
23Is 27:2 On that day sing about a desirable vineyard:
23Is 27:3 I, the LORD, watch over it; I water it regularly. I guard it night and day so that no one disturbs it.
23Is 27:4 I am not angry, but if it produces thorns and briers for Me, I will fight against it, trample it, and burn it to the ground.
23Is 27:5 Or let it take hold of My strength; let it make peace with Me-- make peace with Me.
23Is 27:6 In days to come, Jacob will take root. Israel will blossom and bloom and fill the whole world with fruit.
23Is 27:7 Did the LORD strike Israel as He struck the one who struck Israel? Was he killed like those killed by Him?
23Is 27:8 You disputed with her by banishing and driving her away. He removed [her] with His severe storm on the day of the east wind.
23Is 27:9 Therefore Jacob's iniquity will be purged in this way, and the result of the removal of his sin will be this: when he makes all the altar stones like crushed bits of chalk, no Asherah poles or incense altars will remain standing.
23Is 27:10 For the fortified city will be deserted, pastures abandoned and forsaken like a wilderness. Calves will graze there, and there they will spread out and strip its branches.
23Is 27:11 When its branches dry out, they will be broken off. Women will come and make fires with them, for they are not a people with understanding. Therefore their Maker will not have compassion on them, and their Creator will not be gracious to them.
23Is 27:12 On that day the LORD will thresh grain from the Euphrates River as far as the Wadi of Egypt, and you Israelites will be gathered one by one.
23Is 27:13 On that day a great trumpet will be blown, and those lost in the land of Assyria will come, as well as those dispersed in the land of Egypt; and they will worship the LORD at Jerusalem on the holy mountain.
23Is 28:1 Woe to the majestic crown of Ephraim's drunkards, and to the fading flower of its beautiful splendor, which is on the summit above the rich valley. [Woe] to those overcome with wine.
23Is 28:2 Look, the Lord has a strong and mighty one-- like a devastating hail storm, like a storm with strong flooding waters. He will bring it across the land with [His] hand.
23Is 28:3 The majestic crown of Ephraim's drunkards will be trampled underfoot.
23Is 28:4 The fading flower of his beautiful splendor, which is on the summit above the rich valley, will be like a ripe fig before the summer harvest. Whoever sees it will swallow it while it is still in his hand.
23Is 28:5 On that day the LORD of Hosts will become a crown of beauty and a diadem of splendor to the remnant of His people,
23Is 28:6 a spirit of justice to the one who sits in judgment, and strength to those who turn back the battle at the gate.
23Is 28:7 These also stagger because of wine and stumble under the influence of beer: priest and prophet stagger because of beer, they are confused by wine. They stumble because of beer, they are muddled in [their] visions, they stumble in [their] judgments.
23Is 28:8 Indeed, all their tables are covered with vomit; there is no place without a stench.
23Is 28:9 Who is he trying to teach? Who is he trying to instruct? Infants [just] weaned from milk? Babies removed from the breast?
23Is 28:10 For [he says]: "Law after law, law after law, line after line, line after line, a little here, a little there."
23Is 28:11 So He will speak to this people with stammering speech and in a foreign language.
23Is 28:12 He had said to them: "This is the place of rest, let the weary rest; this is the place of repose." But they would not listen.
23Is 28:13 Then the word of the LORD came to them: "Law after law, law after law, line after line, line after line, a little here, a little there," so they go stumbling backwards, to be broken, trapped, and captured.
23Is 28:14 Therefore hear the word of the LORD, you mockers who rule this people in Jerusalem.
23Is 28:15 For you said, "We have cut a deal with Death, and we have made an agreement with Sheol; when the overwhelming scourge passes through, it will not touch us, because we have made falsehood our refuge and have hidden behind treachery."
23Is 28:16 Therefore the Lord God said: "Look, I have laid a stone in Zion, a tested stone, a precious cornerstone, a sure foundation; the one who believes will be unshakable.
23Is 28:17 And I will make justice the measuring line and righteousness the mason's level." Hail will sweep away the false refuge, and water will flood your hiding place.
23Is 28:18 Your deal with Death will be dissolved, and your agreement with Sheol will not last. When the overwhelming scourge passes through, you will be trampled.
23Is 28:19 Every time it passes through, it will carry you away; it will pass through every morning-- every day and every night. Only terror will cause you to understand the message.
23Is 28:20 Indeed, the bed is too short to stretch out on, and its cover too small to wrap up in.
23Is 28:21 For the LORD will rise up as [He did] at Mount Perazim. He will rise in wrath, as at the valley of Gibeon, to do His work, His strange work, and to perform His task, His disturbing task.
23Is 28:22 So now, do not mock, or your shackles will become stronger. Indeed, I have heard from the Lord God of Hosts a decree of destruction for the whole land.
23Is 28:23 Listen and hear my voice. Pay attention and hear what I say.
23Is 28:24 Does the plowman plow every day to plant seed? Does he [continuously] break up and cultivate the soil?
23Is 28:25 When he has leveled its surface, does he not then scatter cumin and sow black cumin? He plants wheat in rows and barley in plots, with spelt as their border.
23Is 28:26 His God teaches him order; He instructs him.
23Is 28:27 Certainly black cumin is not threshed with a threshing board, and a cart wheel is not rolled over the cumin. But black cumin is beaten out with a stick, and cumin with a rod.
23Is 28:28 Bread grain is crushed, but is not threshed endlessly. Though the wheel of [the farmer's] cart rumbles, his horses do not crush it.
23Is 28:29 This also comes from the LORD of Hosts. He gives wonderful advice; He gives great wisdom.
23Is 29:1 Woe to Ariel, Ariel, the city where David camped! Continue year after year; let the festivals recur.
23Is 29:2 I will oppress Ariel, and there will be mourning and crying, and she will be to Me like an Ariel.
23Is 29:3 I will camp in a circle around you; I will besiege you with earth ramps, and I will set up my siege towers against you.
23Is 29:4 You will be brought down; you will speak from the ground, and your words will come from low in the dust. Your voice will be like that of a spirit from the ground; your speech will whisper from the dust.
23Is 29:5 The multitude of your foes will be like fine dust, and the multitude of the ruthless, like blowing chaff. Then suddenly, in an instant,
23Is 29:6 you will be visited by the LORD of Hosts with thunder, earthquake, and loud noise, storm, tempest, and a flame of consuming fire.
23Is 29:7 The multitude of all the nations going out to battle against Ariel-- all the attackers, the siege-works against her, and those who oppress her-- will then be like a dream, a vision in the night.
23Is 29:8 It will be like a hungry one who dreams he is eating, then wakes and is still hungry; and like a thirsty one who dreams he is drinking, then wakes and is still thirsty, longing for water. So will be the multitude of all the nations who go to battle against Mount Zion.
23Is 29:9 Stop and be astonished; blind yourselves and be blind! They are drunk, but not with wine; they stagger, but not with beer.
23Is 29:10 For the LORD has poured out on you an overwhelming urge to sleep; He has shut your eyes-- the prophets, and covered your heads-- the seers.
23Is 29:11 For you the entire vision will be like the words of a sealed document. If it is given to one who can read and he is asked to read it, he will say, "I can't read it, because it is sealed."
23Is 29:12 And if the document is given to one who cannot read and he is asked to read it, he will say, "I can't read."
23Is 29:13 The Lord said: Because these people approach Me with their mouths to honor Me with lip-service-- yet their hearts are far from Me, and their worship [consists of] man-made rules learned [by rote]--
23Is 29:14 therefore I will again confound these people with wonder after wonder. The wisdom of their wise men will vanish, and the understanding of the perceptive will be hidden.
23Is 29:15 Woe to those who go to great lengths to hide their plans from the LORD. [They do] their works in darkness, and say, "Who sees us? Who knows us?"
23Is 29:16 You have turned things around, as if the potter were the same as the clay. How can what is made say about its maker, "He didn't make me"? How can what is formed say about the one who formed it, "He doesn't understand [what he's doing]"?
23Is 29:17 Isn't [it true that] in just a little while Lebanon will become an orchard, and the orchard will seem like a forest?
23Is 29:18 On that day the deaf will hear the words of a document, and out of a deep darkness the eyes of the blind will see.
23Is 29:19 The humble will have joy after joy in the LORD, and the poor people will rejoice in the Holy One of Israel.
23Is 29:20 For the ruthless one will vanish, the scorner will disappear, and all those who lie in wait with evil intent will be killed--
23Is 29:21 those who, with [their] speech, accuse a person of wrongdoing, who set a trap at the gate for the mediator, and without cause deprive the righteous of justice.
23Is 29:22 Therefore, the LORD who redeemed Abraham says this about the house of Jacob: Jacob will no longer be ashamed and his face will no longer be pale.
23Is 29:23 For when he sees his children, the work of My hands within his [nation], they will honor My name, they will honor the Holy One of Jacob and stand in awe of the God of Israel.
23Is 29:24 Those who are confused will gain understanding and those who grumble will accept instruction.
23Is 30:1 Woe to the rebellious children! [This is] the LORD's declaration. They carry out a plan, but not Mine, They make an alliance, but against My will, piling sin on top of sin.
23Is 30:2 They set out to go down to Egypt without asking My advice, in order to seek shelter under Pharaoh's protection and take refuge in Egypt's shadow.
23Is 30:3 But Pharaoh's protection will become your shame, and refuge in Egypt's shadow your disgrace.
23Is 30:4 For though his princes are at Zoan and his messengers reach as far as Hanes,
23Is 30:5 everyone will be ashamed because of a people who can't help. They are of no benefit, they are no help; they are good for nothing but shame and reproach.
23Is 30:6 An oracle about the animals of the Negev: Through a land of trouble and distress, of lioness and lion, of viper and flying serpent, they carry their wealth on the backs of donkeys and their treasures on the humps of camels, to a people who will not help them.
23Is 30:7 Egypt's help is completely worthless; therefore, I call her: Rahab Who Just Sits.
23Is 30:8 Go now, write it on a tablet in their presence and inscribe it on a scroll; it will be for the future, forever and ever.
23Is 30:9 They are a rebellious people, deceptive children, children who do not obey the LORD's instruction.
23Is 30:10 They say to the seers, "Do not see," and to the prophets, "Do not prophesy the truth to us. Tell us flattering things. Prophesy illusions.
23Is 30:11 Get out of the way! Leave the pathway. Rid us of the Holy One of Israel."
23Is 30:12 Therefore the Holy One of Israel says: "Because you have rejected this message and have trusted in oppression and deceit, and have depended on them,
23Is 30:13 this iniquity of yours will be like a spreading breach, a bulge in a high wall whose collapse will come very suddenly.
23Is 30:14 Its collapse will be like the shattering of a potter's jar, crushed to pieces, so that not even a fragment of pottery will be found among its shattered remains-- no fragment large enough to take fire from a hearth or scoop water from a cistern."
23Is 30:15 For the Lord God, the Holy One of Israel, has said: "You will be delivered by returning and resting; your strength will lie in quiet confidence. But you are not willing."
23Is 30:16 You say, "No! We will escape on horses"-- therefore you will escape!-- and, "We will ride on fast horses"-- but those who pursue you will be faster.
23Is 30:17 One thousand [will flee] at the threat of one, at the threat of five you will flee, until you alone remain like a [solitary] pole on a mountaintop or a banner on a hill.
23Is 30:18 Therefore the LORD is waiting to show you mercy, and is rising up to show you compassion, for the LORD is a just God. Happy are all who wait patiently for Him.
23Is 30:19 For you people will live on Zion in Jerusalem and will never cry again. He will show favor to you at the sound of your cry; when He hears, He will answer you.
23Is 30:20 The Lord will give you meager bread and water during oppression, but your Teacher will not hide Himself any longer. Your eyes will see your Teacher,
23Is 30:21 and whenever you turn to the right or to the left, your ears will hear this command behind you: "This is the way. Walk in it."
23Is 30:22 Then you will defile your silver-plated idols and your gold-plated images. You will throw them away like menstrual cloths, and call them filth.
23Is 30:23 Then He will send rain for your seed that you have sown in the ground, and the food, the produce of the ground, will be rich and plentiful. On that day your cattle will graze in open pastures.
23Is 30:24 The oxen and donkeys that work the ground will eat salted fodder scattered with winnowing shovel and fork.
23Is 30:25 Streams and watercourses will be on every high mountain and every raised hill on the day of great slaughter when the towers fall.
23Is 30:26 The moonlight will be as bright as the sunlight, and the sunlight will be seven times brighter-- like the light of seven days-- on the day that the LORD bandages His people's injuries and heals the wounds He inflicted.
23Is 30:27 Look, Yahweh comes from far away, His anger burning and heavy with smoke. His lips are full of fury, and His tongue is like a consuming fire.
23Is 30:28 His breath is like an overflowing torrent that rises to the neck. [He comes] to sift the nations in a sieve of destruction and to put a bridle on the jaws of the peoples to lead [them] astray.
23Is 30:29 Your singing will be like that on the night of a holy festival, And [your] heart will rejoice like one who walks [to the music] of a flute, going up to the mountain of the LORD, to the Rock of Israel.
23Is 30:30 And the LORD will make the splendor of His voice heard and reveal His arm striking in angry wrath and a flame of consuming fire, in driving rain, a torrent, and hailstones.
23Is 30:31 Assyria will be shattered by the voice of the LORD. He will strike with a rod.
23Is 30:32 And every stroke of the appointed staff that the LORD brings down on him will be [to the sound] of tambourines and lyres; He will fight against him with brandished weapons.
23Is 30:33 Indeed! Topheth has been ready for the king for a long time now. His funeral pyre is deep and wide, with plenty of fire and wood. The breath of the LORD, like a torrent of brimstone, kindles it.
23Is 31:1 Woe to those who go down to Egypt for help and who depend on horses! They trust in the number of chariots and in the great strength of charioteers. They do not look to the Holy One of Israel and they do not seek the LORD's help.
23Is 31:2 But He also is wise and brings disaster. He does not go back on what He says; He will rise up against the house of wicked men and against the allies of evildoers.
23Is 31:3 Egyptians are men, not God; their horses are flesh, not spirit. When the LORD raises His hand [to strike], the helper will stumble and the helped will fall; both will perish together.
23Is 31:4 For this is what the LORD said to me: As a lion or young lion growls over its prey when a band of shepherds is called out against it, and is not terrified by their shouting or subdued by their noise, so the LORD of Hosts will come down to fight on Mount Zion and on its hill.
23Is 31:5 Like hovering birds, so the LORD of Hosts will protect Jerusalem-- by protecting [it], He will rescue [it], by sparing [it], He will deliver [it].
23Is 31:6 Return to the One the Israelites have greatly rebelled against.
23Is 31:7 For on that day, each one will reject the silver and gold idols that your own hands have sinfully made.
23Is 31:8 Then Assyria will fall, but not by human sword; a sword will devour him, but not one made by man. He will flee from the sword, his young men will be put to forced labor.
23Is 31:9 His rock will pass away because of fear, and his officers will be afraid because of the signal flag. [This is] the LORD's declaration-- whose fire is in Zion and whose furnace is in Jerusalem.
23Is 32:1 Indeed, a king will reign righteously, and rulers will rule justly.
23Is 32:2 Each will be like a shelter from the wind, a refuge from the rain, like streams of water in a dry land and the shade of a massive rock in an arid land.
23Is 32:3 Then the eyes of those who see will not be closed, and the ears of those who hear will listen.
23Is 32:4 The reckless mind will gain knowledge, and the stammering tongue will speak clearly and fluently.
23Is 32:5 A fool will no longer be called a noble, nor a scoundrel said to be important.
23Is 32:6 For a fool speaks foolishness and his mind plots iniquity. He lives in a godless way and speaks falsely about the LORD. He leaves the hungry empty and deprives the thirsty of drink.
23Is 32:7 The scoundrel's weapons are destructive; he hatches plots to destroy the needy with lies, and by charging the poor during a judgment.
23Is 32:8 But a noble person plans noble things; he stands up for noble causes.
23Is 32:9 Stand up, you complacent women; listen to me. Pay attention to what I say, you overconfident daughters.
23Is 32:10 In a little more than a year you overconfident ones will shudder, for the vintage will fail and the harvest will not come.
23Is 32:11 Shudder, you complacent ones; tremble, you overconfident ones! Strip yourselves bare and put [ sackcloth] about your waists.
23Is 32:12 Beat your breasts [in mourning] for the delightful fields and the fruitful vines,
23Is 32:13 for the ground of my people growing thorns and briers, indeed, for every joyous house in the joyful city.
23Is 32:14 For the palace will be forsaken, the busy city abandoned. The hill and the watchtower will become barren places forever, the joy of wild asses, and a pasture for flocks,
23Is 32:15 until the Spirit from heaven is poured out on us. Then the desert will become an orchard, and the orchard will seem like a forest.
23Is 32:16 Then justice will inhabit the wilderness, and righteousness will dwell in the orchard.
23Is 32:17 The result of righteousness will be peace; the effect of righteousness will be quiet confidence forever.
23Is 32:18 Then my people will dwell in a peaceful place, and in safe and restful dwellings.
23Is 32:19 But hail will level the forest, and the city will sink into the depths.
23Is 32:20 Happy are you who sow seed beside abundant waters, who let ox and donkey range freely.
23Is 33:1 Woe, you destroyer never destroyed, you traitor never betrayed! When you have finished destroying, you will be destroyed. When you have finished betraying, they will betray you.
23Is 33:2 LORD, be gracious to us! We wait for You. Be our strength every morning, and our salvation in time of trouble.
23Is 33:3 The peoples flee at the thunderous noise; the nations scatter when You rise in Your majesty.
23Is 33:4 Your spoil will be gathered as locusts are gathered; people will swarm over it like an infestation of locusts.
23Is 33:5 The LORD is exalted, for He dwells on high; He has filled Zion with justice and righteousness.
23Is 33:6 There will be times of security for you-- a storehouse of salvation, wisdom, and knowledge. The fear of the LORD is Zion's treasure.
23Is 33:7 Listen! Their warriors cry loudly in the streets; the messengers of peace weep bitterly.
23Is 33:8 The highways are deserted; travel has ceased. An agreement has been broken, and cities despised. and human life disregarded.
23Is 33:9 The land mourns and withers; Lebanon is ashamed and decayed. Sharon is like a desert; Bashan and Carmel shake off [their] leaves.
23Is 33:10 "Now I will rise up," says the LORD. "Now I will lift Myself up. Now I will be exalted.
23Is 33:11 You will conceive chaff; you will give birth to stubble. Your breath is fire that will consume you.
23Is 33:12 The peoples will be burned to ashes, like thorns cut down and burned in a fire.
23Is 33:13 You who are far off, hear what I have done; you who are near, know My strength."
23Is 33:14 The sinners in Zion are afraid; trembling seizes the ungodly: "Who among us can dwell with a consuming fire? Who among us can dwell with ever-burning flames?"
23Is 33:15 The one who lives righteously and speaks rightly, who refuses gain from extortion, whose hand never takes a bribe, who stops his ears from listening to murderous plots and shuts his eyes to avoid endorsing evil--
23Is 33:16 he will dwell on the heights; his refuge will be the rocky fortresses, his food provided, his water assured.
23Is 33:17 Your eyes will see the king in his beauty; you will see a vast land.
23Is 33:18 Your mind will meditate on the [past] terror: "Where is the accountant? Where is the tribute collector? Where is the one who spied out our defenses?"
23Is 33:19 You will no longer see the barbarians, a people whose speech is difficult to comprehend-- who stammer in a language that is not understood.
23Is 33:20 Look at Zion, the city of our festival times. Your eyes will see Jerusalem, a peaceful pasture, a tent that does not wander; its tent pegs will not be pulled up nor will any of its cords be loosened.
23Is 33:21 For there the majestic One, the LORD, will be for us, a place of rivers and broad streams, where ships that are rowed will not go, and majestic vessels will not pass.
23Is 33:22 For the LORD is our Judge, the LORD is our lawgiver, the LORD is our King. He will save us.
23Is 33:23 Your ropes are slack; they cannot hold the base of the mast or spread out the flag. Then abundant spoil will be divided, the lame will plunder it,
23Is 33:24 and none there will say, "I am sick." The people who dwell there will be forgiven [their] iniquity.
23Is 34:1 You nations, come here and listen; you peoples, pay attention! Let the earth hear, and all that fills it, the world and all that comes from it.
23Is 34:2 The LORD is angry with all the nations-- furious with all their armies. He will set them apart for destruction, giving them over to slaughter.
23Is 34:3 Their slain will be thrown out, and the stench of their corpses will rise; the mountains flow with their blood.
23Is 34:4 All the heavenly bodies will dissolve. The skies will roll up like a scroll, and their stars will all wither as leaves wither on the vine, and foliage on the fig tree.
23Is 34:5 When My sword has drunk its fill in the heavens it will then come down on Edom and on the people I have set apart for destruction.
23Is 34:6 The LORD's sword is covered with blood. It drips with fat, with the blood of lambs and goats, with the fat of the kidneys of rams. For the LORD has a sacrifice in Bozrah, a great slaughter in the land of Edom.
23Is 34:7 The wild oxen will be struck down with them, and young bulls with the mighty bulls. Their land will be soaked with blood, and their soil will be saturated with fat.
23Is 34:8 For the LORD has a day of vengeance, a time of paying back [Edom] for its hostility against Zion.
23Is 34:9 [Edom's] streams will be turned into pitch, her soil into sulfur; her land will become burning pitch.
23Is 34:10 It will never go out-- day or night. Its smoke will go up forever. It will be desolate, from generation to generation; no one will pass through it forever and ever.
23Is 34:11 The desert owl and the hedgehog will possess it, and the great owl and the raven will dwell there. [The LORD] will stretch out a measuring line and a plumb line over her for [her] destruction and chaos.
23Is 34:12 No nobles will be left to proclaim a king, and all her princes will come to nothing.
23Is 34:13 Her palaces will be overgrown with thorns; her fortified cities, with thistles and briers. She will become a dwelling for jackals, an abode for ostriches.
23Is 34:14 The wild beasts will meet hyenas, and one wild goat will call to another. Indeed, the screech owl will stay there and will find a resting place for herself.
23Is 34:15 The sand partridge will make her nest there; she will lay and hatch her eggs and will gather [her brood] under her shadow. Indeed, the birds of prey will gather there, each with its mate.
23Is 34:16 Search and read the scroll of the LORD: Not one of them will be missing, none will be lacking its mate, because He has ordered it by my mouth, and He will gather them by His Spirit.
23Is 34:17 He has ordained a lot for them; His hand allotted their portion with a measuring line. They will possess it forever; they will dwell in it from generation to generation.
23Is 35:1 The wilderness and the dry land will be glad; the desert will rejoice and blossom like a rose.
23Is 35:2 It will blossom abundantly and will also rejoice with joy and singing. The glory of Lebanon will be given to it, the splendor of Carmel and Sharon. They will see the glory of the LORD, the splendor of our God.
23Is 35:3 Strengthen the weak hands, steady the shaking knees!
23Is 35:4 Say to the faint-hearted: "Be strong; do not fear! Here is your God; vengeance is coming. God's retribution is coming; He will save you."
23Is 35:5 Then the eyes of the blind will be opened, and the ears of the deaf unstopped.
23Is 35:6 Then the lame will leap like a deer, and the tongue of the mute will sing for joy, for water will gush in the wilderness, and streams in the desert;
23Is 35:7 the parched ground will become a pool of water, and the thirsty land springs of water. In the haunt of jackals, in their lairs, there will be grass, reeds, and papyrus.
23Is 35:8 A road will be there and a way; it will be called the Holy Way. The unclean will not travel on it, but it will be for him who walks the path. Even the fool will not go astray.
23Is 35:9 There will be no lion there, and no vicious beast will go up on it; they will not be found there. But the redeemed will walk [on it],
23Is 35:10 and the ransomed of the LORD will return and come to Zion with singing, crowned with unending joy. Joy and gladness will overtake [them], and sorrow and sighing will flee.
23Is 36:1 In the fourteenth year of King Hezekiah, Sennacherib king of Assyria advanced against all the fortified cities of Judah and captured them.
23Is 36:2 Then the king of Assyria sent the Rabshakeh, along with a massive army, from Lachish to King Hezekiah at Jerusalem. The Assyrian stood near the conduit of the upper pool, by the road to the Fuller's Field.
23Is 36:3 Eliakim son of Hilkiah, who was in charge of the palace, Shebna the scribe, and Joah son of Asaph, the record keeper, came out to him.
23Is 36:4 The Rabshakeh said to them, "Tell Hezekiah: The great king, the king of Assyria, says this: 'What are you basing your confidence on?
23Is 36:5 I say that your plans and military preparedness are mere words. Now who are you trusting in that you have rebelled against me?
23Is 36:6 Look, you are trusting in Egypt, that splintered reed of a staff, which will enter and pierce the hand of anyone who leans on it. This is how Pharaoh king of Egypt is to all who trust in him.
23Is 36:7 Suppose you say to me: We trust in the LORD our God. Isn't He the One whose high places and altars Hezekiah has removed, saying to Judah and Jerusalem: You are to worship at this altar?
23Is 36:8 Now make a deal with my master, the king of Assyria. I'll give you 2,000 horses if you can put riders on them!
23Is 36:9 How then can you repel [the attack of even] the weakest of my master's officers, and trust in Egypt for chariots and horsemen?
23Is 36:10 Have I attacked this land to destroy it without the LORD's [approval]? The LORD said to me, 'Attack this land and destroy it.'"
23Is 36:11 Then Eliakim, Shebna, and Joah said to the Rabshakeh, "Please speak to your servants in Aramaic, for we understand [it]; don't speak to us in Hebrew within earshot of the people who are on the wall."
23Is 36:12 But the Rabshakeh replied, "Has my master sent me to speak these words to your master and to you, and not to the men who sit on the wall, [who are destined] with you to eat their excrement and drink their urine?"
23Is 36:13 Then the Rabshakeh stood and called out loudly in Hebrew: Listen to the words of the great king, the king of Assyria!
23Is 36:14 The king says: "Don't let Hezekiah deceive you, for he cannot deliver you.
23Is 36:15 Don't let Hezekiah persuade you to trust the LORD, saying, 'The LORD will surely deliver us. This city will not be handed over to the king of Assyria.'"
23Is 36:16 Don't listen to Hezekiah. For the king of Assyria says: "Make peace with me and surrender to me; then every one of you will eat from his own vine and his own fig tree and drink water from his own cistern
23Is 36:17 until I come and take you away to a land like your land, a land of grain and new wine, a land of bread and vineyards.
23Is 36:18 [Beware] that Hezekiah does not mislead you by saying, 'The LORD will deliver us.' Has any one of the gods of the nations delivered his land from the hand of the king of Assyria?
23Is 36:19 Where are the gods of Hamath and Arpad? Where are the gods of Sepharvaim? Have they delivered Samaria from my hand?
23Is 36:20 Who of all the gods of these lands [ever] delivered his land from my hand, that the LORD should deliver Jerusalem?"
23Is 36:21 But they were silent and did not answer him at all, for the king's command was, "Don't answer him."
23Is 36:22 Then Eliakim son of Hilkiah, who was in charge of the palace, Shebna the scribe, and Joah son of Asaph, the record keeper, came to Hezekiah with their clothes torn, and they reported to him the words of the Rabshakeh.
23Is 37:1 When King Hezekiah heard [their report], he tore his clothes, put on sackcloth, and went to the house of the LORD.
23Is 37:2 Then he sent Eliakim, who was in charge of the palace, Shebna the scribe, and the older priests, wearing sackcloth, to the prophet Isaiah son of Amoz.
23Is 37:3 They said to him, "Hezekiah says: 'Today is a day of distress, rebuke, and disgrace, [as] when children come to the point of birth, and there is no strength to deliver them.
23Is 37:4 Perhaps the LORD your God will hear the words of the Rabshakeh, whom his master, the king of Assyria, sent to mock the living God, and will rebuke [him for] the words that the LORD your God has heard. Therefore offer a prayer for the surviving remnant.'"
23Is 37:5 When King Hezekiah's servants came to Isaiah,
23Is 37:6 Isaiah said to them, "Say this to your master, 'The LORD says: Don't be afraid because of the words you have heard, which the king of Assyria's attendants have blasphemed Me with.
23Is 37:7 Look! I am putting a spirit in him and he will hear a rumor and return to his own land, where I will cause him to fall by the sword.'"
23Is 37:8 When the Rabshakeh heard that the king had left Lachish, he returned and discovered that the king of Assyria was fighting against Libnah.
23Is 37:9 The king had heard this about Tirhakah, king of Cush: "He has set out to fight against you." So when he heard this, he sent messengers to Hezekiah, saying,
23Is 37:10 "Say this to Hezekiah king of Judah: 'Don't let your God, whom you trust, deceive you by saying that Jerusalem won't be handed over to the king of Assyria.
23Is 37:11 Look, you have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all the countries; they destroyed them completely. Will you be rescued?
23Is 37:12 Did the gods of the nations that my predecessors destroyed rescue them-- Gozan, Haran, Rezeph, and the Edenites in Telassar?
23Is 37:13 Where is the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad, the king of the city of Sepharvaim, Hena, or Ivvah?'"
23Is 37:14 Hezekiah took the letter from the messengers, read it, then went up to the LORD's house and spread it out before the LORD.
23Is 37:15 Hezekiah prayed to the LORD:
23Is 37:16 "LORD of Hosts, God of Israel, who is enthroned above the cherubim, You are God-- You alone-- of all the kingdoms of the earth. You made the heavens and the earth.
23Is 37:17 Listen closely, LORD, and hear; open Your eyes, LORD, and see; hear all the words that Sennacherib has sent to mock the living God.
23Is 37:18 LORD, it is true that the kings of Assyria have devastated all these countries and their lands
23Is 37:19 and have thrown their gods into the fire; for they were not gods but made by human hands-- wood and stone. So they have destroyed them.
23Is 37:20 Now, LORD our God, save us from his hand so that all the kingdoms of the earth may know that You are the LORD-- You alone."
23Is 37:21 Then Isaiah son of Amoz sent [a message] to Hezekiah: "The LORD, the God of Israel, says: 'Because you prayed to Me about Sennacherib king of Assyria,
23Is 37:22 this is the word the LORD has spoken against him: The young woman, Daughter Zion, despises you and scorns you: Daughter Jerusalem shakes [her] head behind your back.
23Is 37:23 Who is it you have mocked and blasphemed? Who have you raised [your] voice against and lifted your eyes in pride? Against the Holy One of Israel!
23Is 37:24 You have mocked the LORD through your servants. You have said: With my many chariots I have gone up to the heights of the mountains, to the far recesses of Lebanon. I cut down its tallest cedars, its choice cypress trees. I came to its remotest heights, its densest forest.
23Is 37:25 I dug [wells] and drank water. I dried up all the streams of Egypt with the soles of my feet.
23Is 37:26 Have you not heard? I designed it long ago; I planned it in days gone by. I have now brought it to pass, and you have crushed fortified cities into piles of rubble.
23Is 37:27 Their inhabitants have become powerless, dismayed, and ashamed. They are plants of the field, tender grass, grass on the rooftops, blasted by the east wind.
23Is 37:28 But I know your sitting down, your going out and your coming in, and your raging against Me.
23Is 37:29 Because your raging against Me and your arrogance has reached My ears, I will put My hook in your nose and My bit in your mouth; I will make you go back the way you came.
23Is 37:30 " 'This will be the sign for you: This year you will eat what grows on its own, and in the second year what grows from that. But in the third year sow and reap, plant vineyards and eat their fruit.
23Is 37:31 The surviving remnant of the house of Judah will again take root downward and bear fruit upward.
23Is 37:32 For a remnant will go out from Jerusalem, and survivors from Mount Zion. The zeal of the LORD of Hosts will accomplish this.'
23Is 37:33 " 'Therefore, this is what the LORD says about the king of Assyria: He will not enter this city or shoot an arrow there or come before it with a shield or build up an assault ramp against it.
23Is 37:34 He will go back on the road that he came and he will not enter this city. [This is] the LORD's declaration.
23Is 37:35 I will defend this city and rescue it, because of Me and because of My servant David.'"
23Is 37:36 Then the angel of the LORD went out and struck down 185,000 in the camp of the Assyrians. When the people got up the [next] morning-- there were all the dead bodies!
23Is 37:37 So Sennacherib king of Assyria broke camp and left. He returned [home] and lived in Nineveh.
23Is 37:38 One day, while he was worshiping in the temple of his god Nisroch, his sons Adrammelech and Sharezer struck him down with the sword and escaped to the land of Ararat. Then his son Esar-haddon became king in his place.
23Is 38:1 In those days Hezekiah became terminally ill. The prophet Isaiah son of Amoz came and said to him, "This is what the LORD says: 'Put your affairs in order, for you are about to die; you will not recover.'"
23Is 38:2 Then Hezekiah turned his face to the wall and prayed to the LORD.
23Is 38:3 He said, "Please, LORD, remember how I have walked before You faithfully and wholeheartedly, and have done what is good in Your sight." And Hezekiah wept bitterly.
23Is 38:4 Then the word of the LORD came to Isaiah:
23Is 38:5 "Go and tell Hezekiah that this is what the LORD God of your ancestor David says: I have heard your prayer; I have seen your tears. Look, I am going to add 15 years to your life.
23Is 38:6 And I will deliver you and this city from the hand of the king of Assyria; I will defend this city.
23Is 38:7 This is the sign to you from the LORD that the LORD will do what He has promised:
23Is 38:8 I am going to make the sun's shadow that goes down on Ahaz's stairway return by 10 steps." So the sun's shadow went back the 10 steps it had descended.
23Is 38:9 A poem by Hezekiah king of Judah after he had been sick and had recovered from his illness:
23Is 38:10 I said: In the prime of my life I must go to the gates of Sheol; I am deprived of the rest of my years.
23Is 38:11 I said: I will never see the LORD, the LORD in the land of the living; I will not look on humanity any longer with the inhabitants of what is passing away.
23Is 38:12 My dwelling is plucked up and removed from me like a shepherd's tent. I have rolled up my life like a weaver; He cuts me off from the loom. You make an end of me from day until night.
23Is 38:13 I thought until the morning: He will break all my bones like a lion; You make an end of me day and night.
23Is 38:14 I chirp like a swallow [or] a crane; I moan like a dove. My eyes grow weak looking upward. Lord, I am oppressed; support me.
23Is 38:15 What can I say? He has spoken to me, and He Himself has done it. I walk along slowly all my years because of the bitterness of my soul,
23Is 38:16 Lord, because of these [promises] people live, and in all of them is the life of my spirit as well; You have restored me to health and let me live.
23Is 38:17 Indeed, it was for [my own] welfare that I had such great bitterness; but Your love [has delivered] me from the Pit of destruction, for You have thrown all my sins behind Your back.
23Is 38:18 For Sheol cannot thank You; Death cannot praise You. Those who go down to the Pit cannot hope for Your faithfulness.
23Is 38:19 The living, only the living can thank You, as I do today; a father will make Your faithfulness known to children
23Is 38:20 The LORD will save me; we will play stringed instruments all the days of our lives at the house of the LORD.
23Is 38:21 Now Isaiah had said, "Let them take a lump of figs and apply it to his infected skin, so that he may recover."
23Is 38:22 And Hezekiah had asked, "What is the sign that I will go up to the LORD's temple?"
23Is 39:1 At that time Merodach-baladan son of Baladan, king of Babylon, sent letters and a gift to Hezekiah since he heard that he had been sick and had recovered.
23Is 39:2 Hezekiah was pleased with them, and showed them his treasure house-- the silver, the gold, the spices, and the precious oil-- and all his armory, and everything that was found in his treasuries. There was nothing in his palace and in all his realm that Hezekiah did not show them.
23Is 39:3 Then Isaiah the prophet came to King Hezekiah and asked him, "What did these men say? The men who came to you-- where were they from?" Hezekiah replied, "They came to me from a distant country, from Babylon."
23Is 39:4 And he asked, "What have they seen in your palace?" Hezekiah answered, "They have seen everything in my palace. There isn't anything in my storehouses that I didn't show them."
23Is 39:5 Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, "Hear the word of the LORD of Hosts:
23Is 39:6 'The time will certainly come when everything in your palace and all that your fathers have stored up until this day will be carried off to Babylon; nothing will be left,' says the LORD.
23Is 39:7 'Some of your descendants who come from you will be taken away, and they will be eunuchs in the palace of the king of Babylon.'"
23Is 39:8 Then Hezekiah said to Isaiah, "The word of the LORD that you have spoken is good." For he thought: There will be peace and security during my lifetime.
23Is 40:1 "Comfort, comfort My people," says your God.
23Is 40:2 Speak tenderly to Jerusalem, and announce to her that her time of servitude is over, her iniquity has been pardoned, and she has received from the LORD's hand double for all her sins.
23Is 40:3 A voice of one crying out: Prepare the way of the LORD in the wilderness; make a straight highway for our God in the desert.
23Is 40:4 Every valley will be lifted up, and every mountain and hill will be leveled; the uneven ground will become smooth, and the rough places a plain.
23Is 40:5 And the glory of the LORD will appear, and all humanity will see [it] together, for the mouth of the LORD has spoken.
23Is 40:6 A voice was saying, "Cry out!" Another said, "What should I cry out?" "All humanity is grass, and all its goodness is like the flower of the field.
23Is 40:7 The grass withers, the flowers fade when the breath of the LORD blows on them; indeed, the people are grass.
23Is 40:8 The grass withers, the flowers fade, but the word of our God remains forever."
23Is 40:9 Zion, herald of good news, go up on a high mountain. Jerusalem, herald of good news, raise your voice loudly. Raise it, do not be afraid! Say to the cities of Judah, "Here is your God!"
23Is 40:10 See, the Lord God comes with strength, and His power establishes His rule. His reward is with Him, and His gifts accompany Him.
23Is 40:11 He protects His flock like a shepherd; He gathers the lambs in His arms and carries [them] in the fold of His [garment]. He gently leads those that are nursing.
23Is 40:12 Who has measured the waters in the hollow of his hand or marked off the heavens with the span [of his hand]? Who has gathered the dust of the earth in a measure or weighed the mountains in a balance and the hills in scales?
23Is 40:13 Who has directed the Spirit of the LORD, or who gave Him His counsel?
23Is 40:14 Who did He consult with? Who gave Him understanding and taught Him the paths of justice? Who taught Him knowledge and showed Him the way of understanding?
23Is 40:15 Look, the nations are like a drop in a bucket; they are considered as a speck of dust on the scales; He lifts up the islands like fine dust.
23Is 40:16 Lebanon is not enough for fuel, or its animals enough for a burnt offering.
23Is 40:17 All the nations are as nothing before Him; they are considered by Him as nothingness and emptiness.
23Is 40:18 Who will you compare God with? What likeness will you compare Him to?
23Is 40:19 To an idol?-- [something that] a smelter casts, and a metalworker plates with gold and makes silver welds [for it]?
23Is 40:20 To one who shapes a pedestal, choosing wood that does not rot? He looks for a skilled craftsman to set up an idol that will not fall over.
23Is 40:21 Do you not know? Have you not heard? Has it not been declared to you from the beginning? Have you not considered the foundations of the earth?
23Is 40:22 God is enthroned above the circle of the earth; its inhabitants are like grasshoppers. He stretches out the heavens like thin cloth and spreads them out like a tent to live in.
23Is 40:23 He reduces princes to nothing and makes the judges of the earth to be irrational.
23Is 40:24 They are barely planted, barely sown, their stem hardly takes root in the ground when He blows on them and they wither, and a whirlwind carries them away like stubble.
23Is 40:25 "Who will you compare Me to, or who is My equal?" asks the Holy One.
23Is 40:26 Look up and see: who created these? He brings out the starry host by number; He calls all of them by name. Because of His great power and strength, not one of them is missing.
23Is 40:27 Jacob, why do you say, and Israel, why do you assert: "My way is hidden from the LORD, and my claim is ignored by my God"?
23Is 40:28 Do you not know? Have you not heard? Yahweh is the everlasting God, the Creator of the whole earth. He never grows faint or weary; there is no limit to His understanding.
23Is 40:29 He gives strength to the weary and strengthens the powerless.
23Is 40:30 Youths may faint and grow weary, and young men stumble and fall,
23Is 40:31 but those who trust in the LORD will renew their strength; they will soar on wings like eagles; they will run and not grow weary; they will walk and not faint.
23Is 41:1 "Be silent before Me, islands! And let peoples renew their strength. Let them approach, then let them testify; let us come together for the trial.
23Is 41:2 Who has stirred him up from the east? He calls righteousness to his feet. The LORD hands nations over to him, and he subdues kings. He makes [them] like dust [with] his sword, like wind-driven stubble [with] his bow.
23Is 41:3 He pursues them, going on safely, hardly touching the path with his feet.
23Is 41:4 Who has performed and done [this], calling the generations from the beginning? I, the LORD, am the first, and with the last-- I am He."
23Is 41:5 The islands see and are afraid, the ends of the earth tremble. They approach and arrive.
23Is 41:6 Each one helps the other, and says to another, "Take courage!"
23Is 41:7 The craftsman encourages the metalworker; the one who flattens with the hammer [supports] the one who strikes the anvil, saying of the soldering, "It is good." He fastens it with nails so that it will not fall over.
23Is 41:8 But you, Israel, My servant, Jacob, whom I have chosen, descendant of Abraham, My friend--
23Is 41:9 I brought you from the ends of the earth and called you from its farthest corners. I said to you: You are My servant; I have chosen you and not rejected you.
23Is 41:10 Do not fear, for I am with you; do not be afraid, for I am your God. I will strengthen you; I will help you; I will hold on to you with My righteous right hand.
23Is 41:11 Be sure that all who are enraged against you will be ashamed and disgraced; those who contend with you will become as nothing and will perish.
23Is 41:12 You will look for those who contend with you, but you will not find them. Those who war against you will become absolutely nothing.
23Is 41:13 For I, the LORD your God, hold your right hand and say to you: Do not fear, I will help you.
23Is 41:14 Do not fear, you worm Jacob, you men of Israel: I will help you-- the LORD's declaration. Your Redeemer is the Holy One of Israel.
23Is 41:15 See, I will make you into a sharp threshing board, new, with many teeth. You will thresh mountains and pulverize [them], and make hills like chaff.
23Is 41:16 You will winnow them and a wind will carry them away, and a gale will scatter them. But you will rejoice in the LORD; you will boast in the Holy One of Israel.
23Is 41:17 The poor and the needy seek water, but there is none; their tongues are parched with thirst. I, the LORD, will answer them; I, the God of Israel, do not forsake them.
23Is 41:18 I will open rivers on the barren heights, and springs in the middle of the plains. I will turn the desert into a pool of water and dry land into springs of water.
23Is 41:19 I will plant cedars in the desert, acacias, myrtles, and olive trees. I will put cypress trees in the desert, elms and box trees together,
23Is 41:20 so that all may see and know, consider and understand, that the hand of the LORD has done this, the Holy One of Israel has created it.
23Is 41:21 "Submit your case," says the LORD. "Present your arguments," says Jacob's King.
23Is 41:22 "Let them come and tell us what will happen. Tell us the past events, so that we may reflect on it and know the outcome. Or tell us the future.
23Is 41:23 Tell us the coming events, then we will know that you are gods. Indeed, do [something] good or bad, then we will be in awe and perceive.
23Is 41:24 Look, you are nothing and your work is worthless. Anyone who chooses you is detestable.
23Is 41:25 "I have raised up one from the north, and he has come, one from the east who invokes My name. He will march over rulers as if they were mud, like a potter who treads the clay.
23Is 41:26 Who told about this from the beginning, so that we might know, and from times past, so that we might say: He is right? No one announced it, no one told it, no one heard your words.
23Is 41:27 I was the first to say to Zion: Look! Here they are! and I gave a herald of good news to Jerusalem.
23Is 41:28 When I look, there is no one; there is no counselor among them; when I ask them, they have nothing to say.
23Is 41:29 Look, all of them are a delusion; their works are nonexistent; their images are wind and emptiness.
23Is 42:1 "This is My Servant; I strengthen Him, [this is] My Chosen One; I delight in Him. I have put My Spirit on Him; He will bring justice to the nations.
23Is 42:2 He will not cry out or shout or make His voice heard in the streets.
23Is 42:3 He will not break a bruised reed, and He will not put out a smoldering wick; He will faithfully bring justice.
23Is 42:4 He will not grow weak or be discouraged until He has established justice on earth. The islands will wait for His instruction."
23Is 42:5 This is what God the LORD says-- who created the heavens and stretched them out, who spread out the earth and what comes from it, who gives breath to the people on it and life to those who walk on it--
23Is 42:6 "I, the LORD, have called you for a righteous [purpose], and I will hold you by your hand. I will keep you, and I make you a covenant for the people [and] a light to the nations,
23Is 42:7 in order to open blind eyes, to bring out prisoners from the dungeon, [and] those sitting in darkness from the prison house.
23Is 42:8 I am Yahweh, that is My name; I will not give My glory to another, or my praise to idols.
23Is 42:9 The past events have indeed happened. Now I declare new events; I announce them to you before they occur."
23Is 42:10 Sing a new song to the LORD; [sing] His praise from the ends of the earth, you who go down to the sea with all that fills it, you islands with your inhabitants.
23Is 42:11 Let the desert and its cities shout, the settlements where Kedar dwells [cry aloud]. Let the inhabitants of Sela sing for joy; let them cry out from the mountaintops.
23Is 42:12 Let them give glory to the LORD, and declare His praise in the islands.
23Is 42:13 The LORD advances like a warrior; He stirs up His zeal like a soldier. He shouts, He roars aloud, He prevails over His enemies.
23Is 42:14 "I have kept silent from ages past; I have been quiet and restrained Myself. [But now,] I will groan like a woman in labor, gasping breathlessly.
23Is 42:15 I will lay waste mountains and hills, and dry up all their vegetation. I will turn rivers into islands, and dry up marshes.
23Is 42:16 I will lead the blind by a way they did not know; I will guide them on paths they have not known. I will turn darkness to light in front of them, and rough places into level ground. This is what I will do for them, and I will not forsake them.
23Is 42:17 They will be turned back [and] utterly ashamed-- those who trust in idols and say to metal-plated images: You are our gods!
23Is 42:18 "Listen, you deaf! Look, you blind, so that you may see.
23Is 42:19 Who is blind but My servant, or deaf like My messenger I am sending? Who is blind like [My] dedicated one, or blind like the servant of the LORD?
23Is 42:20 Though seeing many things, you do not obey. Though [his] ears are open, he does not listen."
23Is 42:21 The LORD was pleased, because of His righteousness, to magnify [His] instruction and make it glorious.
23Is 42:22 But this is a people plundered and looted, all of them trapped in holes or imprisoned in dungeons. They have become plunder, with no one to rescue them, and loot, with no one saying "Give [it] back!"
23Is 42:23 Who among you will pay attention to this? Let him listen and obey in the future.
23Is 42:24 Who gave Jacob to the robber, and Israel to the plunderers? Was it not the LORD? Have we not sinned against Him? They were not willing to walk in His ways, and they would not listen to His instruction.
23Is 42:25 So He poured out on Jacob His furious anger and the power of war. It surrounded him with fire, but he did not know [it]; it burned him, but he paid no attention.
23Is 43:1 Now this is what the LORD says-- the One who created you, Jacob, and the One who formed you, Israel-- "Do not fear, for I have redeemed you; I have called you by your name; you are Mine.
23Is 43:2 I will be with you when you pass through the waters, and [when you pass] through the rivers, they will not overwhelm you. You will not be scorched when you walk through the fire, and the flame will not burn you.
23Is 43:3 For I the LORD your God, the Holy One of Israel, and your Savior, give Egypt as a ransom for you, Cush and Seba in your place.
23Is 43:4 Because you are precious in My sight and honored, and I love you, I will give human beings in your place, and peoples in place of your life.
23Is 43:5 Do not fear, for I am with you; I will bring your descendants from the east, and gather you from the west.
23Is 43:6 I will say to the north: Give [them] up! and to the south: Do not hold [them] back! Bring My sons from far away, and My daughters from the ends of the earth--
23Is 43:7 everyone called by My name and created for My glory. I have formed him; indeed, I have made him."
23Is 43:8 Bring out a people who are blind, yet have eyes, and are deaf, yet have ears.
23Is 43:9 All the nations are gathered together, and the peoples are assembled. Who among them can declare this, and tell us the former things? Let them present their witnesses to vindicate [themselves], so that people may hear and say, "It is true."
23Is 43:10 "You are My witnesses"-- the LORD's declaration-- "and My servant whom I have chosen, so that you may know and believe Me and understand that I am He. No god was formed before Me, and there will be none after Me.
23Is 43:11 I, I am the LORD, and there is no other Savior but Me.
23Is 43:12 I alone declared, saved, and proclaimed-- and not some foreign god among you. So you are My witnesses"-- the LORD's declaration-- "and I am God.
23Is 43:13 Also, from today on I am He [alone], and no one can take [anything] from My hand. I act, and who can reverse it?"
23Is 43:14 This is what the LORD, your Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel says: Because of you, I will send to Babylon and bring all of them as fugitives, even the Chaldeans in the ships in which they rejoice.
23Is 43:15 I am the LORD, your Holy One, the Creator of Israel, your King.
23Is 43:16 This is what the LORD says-- who makes a way in the sea, and a path through surging waters,
23Is 43:17 who brings out the chariot and horse, the army and the mighty one together (they lie down, they do not rise again; they are extinguished, quenched like a wick)--
23Is 43:18 "Do not remember the past events, pay no attention to things of old.
23Is 43:19 Look, I am about to do something new; even now it is coming. Do you not see it? Indeed, I will make a way in the wilderness, rivers in the desert.
23Is 43:20 The animals of the field will honor Me, jackals and ostriches, because I provide water in the wilderness, and rivers in the desert, to give drink to My chosen people.
23Is 43:21 The people I formed for Myself will declare My praise.
23Is 43:22 "But Jacob, you have not called on Me, because, Israel, you have become weary of Me.
23Is 43:23 You have not brought Me your sheep for burnt offerings or honored Me with your sacrifices. I have not burdened you with offerings or wearied you with incense.
23Is 43:24 You have not bought Me aromatic cane with silver, or satisfied Me with the fat of your sacrifices. But you have burdened Me with your sins; you have wearied Me with your iniquities.
23Is 43:25 "It is I who sweep away your transgressions for My own sake and remember your sins no more.
23Is 43:26 Take Me to court; let us argue our case together. State your [case], so that you may be vindicated.
23Is 43:27 Your first father sinned, and your mediators have rebelled against Me.
23Is 43:28 So I defiled the officers of the sanctuary, and gave Jacob over to total destruction and Israel to abuse.
23Is 44:1 "And now listen, Jacob My servant, Israel whom I have chosen.
23Is 44:2 This is the word of the LORD your Maker who shaped you from birth; He will help you: Do not fear; Jacob is My servant; I have chosen Jeshurun.
23Is 44:3 For I will pour water on the thirsty land, and streams on the dry ground; I will pour out My Spirit on your descendants and My blessing on your offspring.
23Is 44:4 They will sprout among the grass like poplars by the streambeds.
23Is 44:5 This one will say: I am the LORD's; another will call [himself] by the name of Jacob; still another will write on his hand: The LORD's, and name [himself] by the name of Israel."
23Is 44:6 This is what the LORD, the King of Israel and its Redeemer, the LORD of Hosts, says: I am the first and I am the last. There is no God but Me.
23Is 44:7 Who, like Me, can announce [the future]? Let him say so and make a case before Me, since I have established an ancient people. Let these gods declare the coming things, and what will take place.
23Is 44:8 Do not be startled or afraid. Have I not told you and declared it long ago? You are my witnesses! Is there any God but Me? There is no [other] Rock; I do not know any.
23Is 44:9 All who make idols are nothing, and what they treasure does not profit. Their witnesses do not see or know [anything], so they will be put to shame.
23Is 44:10 Who makes a god or casts a metal image for no profit?
23Is 44:11 Look, all its worshipers will be put to shame, and the craftsmen are humans. They all will assemble and stand; they all will be startled and put to shame.
23Is 44:12 The ironworker labors over the coals, shapes the idol with hammers, and works it with his strong arm. Also he grows hungry and his strength fails; he doesn't drink water and is faint.
23Is 44:13 The woodworker stretches out a measuring line, he outlines it with a stylus; he shapes it with chisels and outlines it with a compass. He makes it according to a human likeness, like a beautiful person, to dwell in a temple.
23Is 44:14 He cuts down cedars for his use, or he takes a cypress or an oak. He lets it grow strong among the trees of the forest. He plants a laurel, and the rain makes it grow.
23Is 44:15 It serves as fuel for man. He takes some of it and warms himself; also he kindles a fire and bakes bread; he even makes it into a god and worships it; he makes it an idol and bows down to it.
23Is 44:16 He burns half of it in a fire, and he roasts meat on that half. He eats the roast and is satisfied. He warms himself and says, "Ah! I am warm, I see the blaze."
23Is 44:17 He makes a god or his idol with the rest of it. He bows down to it and worships; He prays to it, "Save me, for you are my god."
23Is 44:18 Such people do not comprehend and cannot understand, for He has shut their eyes so they cannot see, and their minds so they cannot understand.
23Is 44:19 No one reflects, no one has the perception or insight to say, "I burned half of it in the fire, I also baked bread on its coals, I roasted meat and ate. I will make something detestable with the rest of it, and I will bow down to a block of wood."
23Is 44:20 He feeds on ashes. [His] deceived mind has led him astray, and he cannot deliver himself, or say, "Isn't there a lie in my right hand?"
23Is 44:21 Remember these things, Jacob, and Israel, for you are My servant; I formed you, you are My servant; Israel, you will never be forgotten by Me.
23Is 44:22 I have swept away your transgressions like a cloud, and your sins like a mist. Return to Me, for I have redeemed you.
23Is 44:23 Rejoice, heavens, for the LORD has acted; shout, depths of the earth. Break out into singing, mountains, forest, and every tree in it. For the LORD has redeemed Jacob, and glorifies Himself through Israel.
23Is 44:24 This is what the LORD, your Redeemer who formed you from the womb, says: I am the LORD, who made everything; who stretched out the heavens by Myself; who alone spread out the earth;
23Is 44:25 who destroys the omens of the false prophets and makes fools of diviners; who confounds the wise and makes their knowledge foolishness;
23Is 44:26 who confirms the message of His servant and fulfills the counsel of His messengers; who says to Jerusalem: She will be inhabited, and to the cities of Judah: They will be rebuilt, and I will restore her ruins;
23Is 44:27 who says to the depths of the sea: Be dry, and I will dry up your rivers;
23Is 44:28 who says to Cyrus: My shepherd, he will fulfill all My pleasure and say to Jerusalem: She will be rebuilt, and of the temple: Its foundation will be laid.
23Is 45:1 The LORD says this to Cyrus, His anointed, whose right hand I have grasped to subdue nations before him, to unloose the loins of kings, to open the doors before him and the gates will not be shut:
23Is 45:2 "I will go before you and level the uneven places; I will shatter the bronze doors and cut the iron bars in two.
23Is 45:3 I will give you the treasures of darkness and riches from secret places, so that you may know that I, the LORD, the God of Israel call you by your name.
23Is 45:4 I call you by your name, because of Jacob My servant and Israel My chosen one. I give a name to you, though you do not know Me.
23Is 45:5 I am the LORD, and there is no other; there is no God but Me. I will strengthen you, though you do not know Me,
23Is 45:6 so that all may know from the rising of the sun to its setting that there is no one but Me. I am the LORD, and there is no other.
23Is 45:7 I form light and create darkness, I make success and create disaster; I, the LORD, do all these things.
23Is 45:8 "Heavens, sprinkle from above, and let the skies shower righteousness. Let the earth open up that salvation sprout and righteousness spring up with it. I, the LORD, have created it.
23Is 45:9 "Woe to the one who argues with his Maker-- one clay pot among many. Does clay say to the one forming it: What are you making? Or does your work [say]: He has no hands?
23Is 45:10 How absurd is the one who says to [his] father: What are you fathering? or to [his] mother: What are you giving birth to?"
23Is 45:11 This is what the LORD, the Holy One of Israel and its Maker, says: "Ask Me what is to happen to My sons, and instruct Me about the work of My hands.
23Is 45:12 I made the earth, and created man on it. It was My hands that stretched out the heavens, and I commanded all their host.
23Is 45:13 I have raised him up in righteousness, and will level all roads for him. He will rebuild My city, and set My exiles free, not for a price or a bribe," says the LORD of Hosts.
23Is 45:14 This is what the LORD says: The products of Egypt and the merchandise of Cush and the Sabeans, men of stature, will come over to you and will be yours; they will follow you, they will come over in chains; and bow down to you. They will confess to you: God is indeed with you, and there is no other; there is no other God.
23Is 45:15 Yes, You are a God who hides Himself, God of Israel, Savior.
23Is 45:16 All of them are put to shame, even humiliated; the makers of idols go in humiliation together.
23Is 45:17 Israel will be saved by the LORD with an everlasting salvation; you will not be put to shame or humiliated for all eternity.
23Is 45:18 For this is what the LORD says-- God is the Creator of the heavens. He formed the earth and made it; He established it; He did not create it to be empty, [but] formed it to be inhabited-- "I am the LORD, and there is no other.
23Is 45:19 I have not spoken in secret, somewhere in a land of darkness. I did not say to the descendants of Jacob: Seek Me in a wasteland. I, the LORD, speak truthfully; I say what is right.
23Is 45:20 "Come, gather together, and draw near, you fugitives of the nations. Those who carry their wooden idols, and pray to a god who cannot save, have no knowledge.
23Is 45:21 Speak up and present [your case]-- yes, let them take counsel together. Who predicted this long ago? Who announced it from ancient times? Was it not I, the LORD? There is no other God but Me, a righteous God and Savior; there is no one except Me.
23Is 45:22 Turn to Me and be saved, all the ends of the earth. For I am God, and there is no other.
23Is 45:23 By Myself I have sworn; Truth has gone from My mouth, a word that will not be revoked: Every knee will bow to Me, every tongue will swear allegiance.
23Is 45:24 It will be said to Me: Only in the LORD is righteousness and strength." All who are incensed against Him will come to Him and be put to shame.
23Is 45:25 All the descendants of Israel will be justified and find glory through the LORD.
23Is 46:1 Bel crouches; Nebo cowers. Their idols are consigned to beasts and cattle. The [images] you carry are loaded, as a burden for the weary [animal].
23Is 46:2 The gods cower; they crouch together; they are not able to rescue the burden, but they themselves go into captivity.
23Is 46:3 "Listen to Me, house of Jacob, all the remnant of the house of Israel, who have been sustained from the womb, carried along since birth.
23Is 46:4 I will be the same until [your] old age, and I will bear [you] up when you turn gray. I have made [you], and I will carry [you]; I will bear and save [you].
23Is 46:5 "Who will you compare Me or make Me equal to? Who will you measure Me with, so that we should be like each other?
23Is 46:6 Those who pour out their bags of gold and weigh out silver on a scales-- they hire a goldsmith and he makes it into a god. Then they kneel and bow down to it.
23Is 46:7 They lift it to their shoulder and bear it along; they set it in its place, and there it stands; it does not budge from its place. They cry out to it but it doesn't answer; it saves no one from his trouble.
23Is 46:8 "Remember this and be brave; take it to heart, you transgressors!
23Is 46:9 Remember what happened long ago, for I am God, and there is no other; [I am] God, and no one is like Me.
23Is 46:10 I declare the end from the beginning, and from long ago what is not yet done, saying: My plan will take place, and I will do all My will.
23Is 46:11 I call a bird of prey from the east, a man for My purpose from a far country. Yes, I have spoken; so I will also bring it about. I have planned it; I will also do it.
23Is 46:12 Listen to me, you hardhearted, far removed from justice:
23Is 46:13 I am bringing My justice near; it is not far away, and My salvation will not delay. I will put salvation in Zion, My splendor in Israel.
23Is 47:1 "Go down and sit in the dust, Virgin Daughter Babylon. Sit on the ground without a throne, Daughter Chaldea! For you will no longer be called pampered and spoiled.
23Is 47:2 Take millstones and grind meal; remove your veil, strip off [your] skirt, bare your thigh, wade through the streams.
23Is 47:3 Your nakedness will be uncovered, and your shame will be exposed. I will take vengeance; I will spare no one.
23Is 47:4 The Holy One of Israel is our Redeemer; the LORD of Hosts is His name.
23Is 47:5 "Daughter Chaldea, sit in silence and go into darkness. For you will no longer be called mistress of kingdoms.
23Is 47:6 I was angry with My people; I profaned My possession, and I placed them under your control. You showed them no mercy; you made your yoke very heavy on the elderly.
23Is 47:7 You said: I will be the mistress forever. You did not take these things to heart or think about their outcome.
23Is 47:8 "So now hear this, lover of luxury, who sits securely, who says to herself: I, and no one else, will never be a widow or know the loss of children.
23Is 47:9 These two things will happen to you suddenly, in one day: loss of children and widowhood. They will happen to you in their entirety, in spite of your many sorceries and the potency of your spells.
23Is 47:10 You were secure in your wickedness; you said: No one sees me. Your wisdom and knowledge led you astray. You said to yourself: I, and no one else.
23Is 47:11 But disaster will happen to you; you will not know how to avert it. And it will fall on you, but you will be unable to ward it off. Devastation will happen to you suddenly and unexpectedly.
23Is 47:12 So take your stand with your spells and your many sorceries, which you have wearied yourself with from your youth. Perhaps you will be able to succeed; perhaps you will inspire terror!
23Is 47:13 You are worn out with your many consultations. So let them stand and save you-- the astrologers, who observe the stars, who predict monthly what will happen to you.
23Is 47:14 Look, they are like stubble; fire burns them up. They cannot deliver themselves from the power of the flame. This is not a coal for warming themselves, or a fire to sit beside!
23Is 47:15 This is what they are to you-- those who have wearied you and have traded with you from your youth-- each wanders on his own way; no one can save you.
23Is 48:1 "Listen to this, house of Jacob-- those who are called by the name Israel and have descended from Judah, who swear by the name of the LORD and declare the God of Israel, [but] not in truth or righteousness.
23Is 48:2 For they are named after the Holy City, and lean on the God of Israel; His name is Yahweh of Hosts.
23Is 48:3 I declared the past events long ago; they came out of My mouth; I proclaimed them. Suddenly I acted, and they occurred.
23Is 48:4 Because I know that you are stubborn, and your neck is iron and your forehead bronze,
23Is 48:5 therefore I declared to you long ago; I announced it to you before it occurred, so you could not claim: My idol caused them; my carved image and cast idol control them.
23Is 48:6 You have heard it. Observe it all. Will you not acknowledge it? From now on I will announce new things to you, hidden things that you have not known.
23Is 48:7 They have been created now, and not long ago; you have not heard of them before today, so you could not claim, "I already knew them!"
23Is 48:8 You have never heard; you have never known; For a long time your ears have not been open. For I knew that you were very treacherous, and were known as a rebel from birth.
23Is 48:9 I will delay My anger for the honor of My name, and I will restrain Myself for your benefit and [for] My praise, so that you will not be destroyed.
23Is 48:10 Look, I have refined you, but not as silver; I have tested you in the furnace of affliction.
23Is 48:11 I will act for My own sake, indeed, My own, for how can I be defiled? I will not give My glory to another.
23Is 48:12 "Listen to Me, Jacob, and Israel, the one called by Me: I am He; I am the first, I am also the last.
23Is 48:13 My own hand founded the earth, and My right hand spread out the heavens; when I summoned them, they stood up together.
23Is 48:14 All of you, assemble and listen! Who among the idols has declared these things? The LORD loves him; he will accomplish His will against Babylon, and His arm [will be against] the Chaldeans.
23Is 48:15 I-- I have spoken; yes, I have called him; I have brought him, and he will succeed in his mission.
23Is 48:16 Approach Me and listen to this. From the beginning I have not spoken in secret; from the time anything existed, I was there." And now the Lord God has sent me and His Spirit.
23Is 48:17 This is what the LORD, your Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel says: I am the LORD your God, who teaches you for [your] benefit, who leads you in the way you should go.
23Is 48:18 If only you had paid attention to My commands. Then your peace would have been like a river, and your righteousness like the waves of the sea.
23Is 48:19 Your descendants would have been as [countless] as the sand, and the offspring of your body like its grains; their name would not be cut off or eliminated from My presence.
23Is 48:20 Leave Babylon, flee from the Chaldeans! Declare with a shout of joy, proclaim this, let it go out to the end of the earth; announce, "The LORD has redeemed His servant Jacob!"
23Is 48:21 They did not thirst when He led them through the deserts; He made water flow for them from the rock; He split the rock, and water gushed out.
23Is 48:22 "There is no peace," says the LORD, "for the wicked."
23Is 49:1 Coastlands, listen to me; distant peoples, pay attention. The LORD called me before I was born. He named me while I was in my mother's womb.
23Is 49:2 He made my words like a sharp sword; He hid me in the shadow of His hand. He made me like a sharpened arrow; He hid me in His quiver.
23Is 49:3 He said to me, "You are My servant, Israel; I will be glorified in him."
23Is 49:4 But I myself said: I have labored in vain, I have spent my strength for nothing and futility; yet my vindication is with the LORD, and my reward is with my God.
23Is 49:5 And now, says the LORD, who formed me from the womb to be His servant, to bring Jacob back to Him so that Israel might be gathered to Him; for I am honored in the sight of the LORD, and my God is my strength--
23Is 49:6 He says, "It is not enough for you to be My servant raising up the tribes of Jacob and restoring the protected ones of Israel. I will also make you a light for the nations, to be My salvation to the ends of the earth."
23Is 49:7 This is what the LORD, the Redeemer of Israel, his Holy One says to one who is despised, to one abhorred by people, to a servant of rulers: "Kings will see and stand up, and princes will bow down, because of the LORD, who is faithful, the Holy One of Israel-- and He has chosen you."
23Is 49:8 This is what the LORD says: I will answer you in a time of favor, and I will help you in the day of salvation. I will keep you, and I will appoint you to be a covenant for the people, to restore the land, to make them possess the desolate inheritances,
23Is 49:9 saying to the prisoners: Come out, and to those who are in darkness: Show yourselves. They will feed along the pathways, and their pastures will be on all the barren heights.
23Is 49:10 They will not hunger or thirst, the scorching heat or sun will not strike them; for their compassionate One will guide them, and lead them to springs of water.
23Is 49:11 I will make all My mountains into a road, and My highways will be raised up.
23Is 49:12 See, these will come from far away, from the north and from the west, and from the land of Sinim.
23Is 49:13 Shout for joy, you heavens! Earth, rejoice! Mountains break into joyful shouts! For the LORD has comforted His people, and will have compassion on His afflicted ones.
23Is 49:14 Zion says, "The LORD has abandoned me; The Lord has forgotten me!"
23Is 49:15 "Can a woman forget her nursing child, or lack compassion for the child of her womb? Even if these forget, yet I will not forget you.
23Is 49:16 Look, I have inscribed you on the palms of My hands; your walls are continually before Me.
23Is 49:17 Your builders hurry; those who destroy and devastate you will leave you.
23Is 49:18 Look up, and look around. They all gather together; they come to you. As I live"-- the LORD's declaration-- "you will wear all your children as jewelry, and put them on as a bride does.
23Is 49:19 For your waste and desolate places and your land marked by ruins-- will now be indeed too small for the inhabitants, and those who swallowed you up will be far away.
23Is 49:20 The children that you have been deprived of will yet say in your hearing: This place is too small for me; make room for me so that I may settle.
23Is 49:21 Then you will say within yourself: Who fathered these for me? I was deprived of my children and barren, exiled and wandering-- but who brought them up? See, I was left by myself-- but these, where did they come from?"
23Is 49:22 This is what the Lord God says: Look, I will lift up My hand to the nations, and raise My banner to the peoples. They will bring your sons in their arms, and your daughters will be carried on their shoulders.
23Is 49:23 Kings will be your foster fathers, and their queens your nursing mothers. They will bow down to you with their faces to the ground, and lick the dust at your feet. Then you will know that I am the LORD; those who put their hope in Me will not be put to shame.
23Is 49:24 Can the prey be taken from the mighty, or the captives of the righteous be delivered?
23Is 49:25 For this is what the LORD says: "Even the captives of a mighty man will be taken, and the prey of a tyrant will be delivered; I will contend with the one who contends with you, and I will save your children.
23Is 49:26 I will make your oppressors eat their own flesh, and they will be drunk with their own blood as with sweet wine. Then all flesh will know that I, the LORD, am your Savior, and your Redeemer, the Mighty One of Jacob."
23Is 50:1 This is what the LORD says: Where is your mother's divorce certificate that I used to send her away? Or who were My creditors that I sold you to? Look, you were sold for your iniquities, and your mother was put away because of your transgressions.
23Is 50:2 Why was no one there when I came? Why was there no one to answer when I called? Is My hand too short to redeem? Or do I have no power to deliver? Look, I dry up the sea by My rebuke; I turn the rivers into a wilderness; their fish rot because of lack of water and die of thirst.
23Is 50:3 I dress the heavens in black and make sackcloth their clothing.
23Is 50:4 The Lord God has given Me the tongue of those who are instructed to know how to sustain the weary with a word. He awakens [Me] each morning; He awakens My ear to listen like those being instructed.
23Is 50:5 The Lord God has opened My ear, and I was not rebellious; I did not turn back.
23Is 50:6 I gave My back to those who beat Me, and My cheeks to those who tore out My beard. I did not hide My face from scorn and spitting.
23Is 50:7 The Lord God will help Me; therefore I have not been humiliated; therefore I have set My face like flint, and I know I will not be put to shame.
23Is 50:8 The One who justifies Me is near; who will contend with Me? Let us confront each other. Who has a case against Me? Let him come near Me!
23Is 50:9 In truth, the Lord God will help Me; who is he who will condemn Me? Indeed, all of them will wear out like a garment; a moth will devour them.
23Is 50:10 Who among you fears the LORD, listening to the voice of His servant? Who [among you] walks in darkness, and has no light? Let him trust in the name of the LORD; let him lean on his God.
23Is 50:11 Look, all you who kindle a fire, who encircle yourselves with firebrands; walk in the light of your fire and in the firebrands you have lit! This is what you'll get from My hand: you will lie down in a place of torment.
23Is 51:1 Listen to Me, you who pursue righteousness, you who seek the LORD: Look to the rock from which you were cut, and to the quarry from which you were dug.
23Is 51:2 Look to Abraham your father, and to Sarah who gave birth to you in pain. When I called him, he was only one; I blessed him and made him many.
23Is 51:3 For the LORD will comfort Zion; He will comfort all her waste places, and He will make her wilderness like Eden, and her desert like the garden of the LORD. Joy and gladness will be found in her, thanksgiving and melodious song.
23Is 51:4 Pay attention to Me, My people, and listen to Me, My nation; for instruction will come from Me, and My justice for a light to the nations. I will bring it about quickly.
23Is 51:5 My righteousness is near, My salvation appears, and My arms will bring justice to the nations. The coastlands will put their hope in Me, and they will look to My strength.
23Is 51:6 Look up to the heavens, and look at the earth beneath; for the heavens will vanish like smoke, the earth will wear out like a garment, and its inhabitants will die in like manner. But My salvation will last forever, and My righteousness will never be shattered.
23Is 51:7 Listen to Me, you who know righteousness, the people in whose heart is My instruction: do not fear disgrace by men, and do not be shattered by their taunts.
23Is 51:8 For the moth will devour them like a garment, and the worm will eat them like wool. But My righteousness will last forever, and My salvation for all generations.
23Is 51:9 Wake up, wake up! Put on the strength of the LORD's power. Wake up as in days past, as in generations of long ago. Wasn't it You who hacked Rahab to pieces, who pierced the sea monster?
23Is 51:10 Wasn't it You who dried up the sea, the waters of the great deep, who made the sea-bed into a road for the redeemed to pass over?
23Is 51:11 And the ransomed of the LORD will return and come to Zion with singing, crowned with unending joy. Joy and gladness will overtake [them], and sorrow and sighing will flee.
23Is 51:12 I-- I am the One who comforts you. Who are you that you should fear man who dies, or a son of man who is given up like grass?
23Is 51:13 But you have forgotten the LORD, your Maker, who stretched out the heavens and laid the foundations of the earth. You are in constant dread all day long because of the fury of the oppressor, who has set himself to destroy. But where is the fury of the oppressor?
23Is 51:14 The prisoner is soon to be set free; he will not die [and go] to the Pit, and his food will not be lacking.
23Is 51:15 For I am the LORD your God who stirs up the sea so that its waves roar-- His name is Yahweh of Hosts.
23Is 51:16 I have put My words in your mouth, and covered you in the shadow of My hand, in order to plant the heavens, to found the earth, and to say to Zion, "You are My people."
23Is 51:17 Wake yourself, wake yourself up! Stand up, Jerusalem, you who have drunk the cup of His fury from the hand of the LORD; you who have drunk the goblet to the dregs-- the cup that [causes people] to stagger.
23Is 51:18 There is no one to guide her among all the children she has raised; there is no one to take hold of her hand among all the offspring she has brought up.
23Is 51:19 These two things have happened to you: devastation and destruction, famine and sword. Who will grieve for you? How can I comfort you?
23Is 51:20 Your children have fainted; they lie at the head of every street like an antelope in a net. They are full of the LORD's fury, the rebuke of your God.
23Is 51:21 So listen to this, afflicted and drunken one-- but not with wine.
23Is 51:22 This is what your Lord says-- Yahweh, even your God, who defends His people-- "Look, I have removed the cup of staggering from your hand; that goblet, the cup of My fury. You will never drink it again.
23Is 51:23 I will put it into the hands of your tormenters, who said to you: Lie down, so we can walk over you. You made your back like the ground, and like a street for those who walk on it.
23Is 52:1 "Wake up, wake up; put on your strength, Zion! Put on your beautiful garments, Jerusalem, the Holy City! For the uncircumcised and the unclean will no longer enter you.
23Is 52:2 Stand up, shake the dust off yourself! Take your seat, Jerusalem. Remove the bonds from your neck, captive Daughter Zion."
23Is 52:3 For this is what the LORD says: "You were sold for nothing, and you will be redeemed without silver."
23Is 52:4 For this is what the Lord God says: "At first My people went down to Egypt to live there, then Assyria oppressed them without cause.
23Is 52:5 So now what have I here"-- the LORD's declaration-- "that My people are taken away for nothing? Its rulers wail"-- the LORD's declaration-- "and My name is continually blasphemed all day long.
23Is 52:6 Therefore My people will know My name; therefore [they will know] on that day that I am He who says: Here I am."
23Is 52:7 How beautiful on the mountains are the feet of the herald, who proclaims peace, who brings news of good things, who proclaims salvation, who says to Zion, "Your God reigns!"
23Is 52:8 The voices of your watchmen-- they lift up their voices, shouting for joy together; for every eye will see when the LORD returns to Zion.
23Is 52:9 Be joyful, rejoice together, you ruins of Jerusalem! For the LORD has comforted His people; He has redeemed Jerusalem.
23Is 52:10 The LORD has displayed His holy arm in the sight of all the nations; all the ends of the earth will see the salvation of our God.
23Is 52:11 Leave, leave, go out from there! Do not touch anything unclean; go out from her, purify yourselves, you who carry the vessels of the LORD.
23Is 52:12 For you will not leave in a hurry, and you will not have to take flight; because the LORD is going before you, and the God of Israel is your rear guard.
23Is 52:13 See, My servant will act wisely; He will be raised and lifted up and greatly exalted.
23Is 52:14 Just as many were appalled at You-- His appearance was so disfigured that He did not look like a man, and His form did not resemble a human being--
23Is 52:15 so He will sprinklemany nations. Kings will shut their mouths because of Him, For they will see what had not been told them, and they will understand what they had not heard.
23Is 53:1 Who has believed what we have heard? And who has the arm of the LORD been revealed to?
23Is 53:2 He grew up before Him like a young plant and like a root out of dry ground. He had no form or splendor that we should look at Him, no appearance that we should desire Him.
23Is 53:3 He was despised and rejected by men, a man of suffering who knew what sickness was. He was like one people turned away from; He was despised, and we didn't value Him.
23Is 53:4 Yet He Himself bore our sicknesses, and He carried our pains; but we in turn regarded Him stricken, struck down by God, and afflicted.
23Is 53:5 But He was pierced because of our transgressions, crushed because of our iniquities; punishment for our peace was on Him, and we are healed by His wounds.
23Is 53:6 We all went astray like sheep; we all have turned to our own way; and the LORD has punished Him for the iniquity of us all.
23Is 53:7 He was oppressed and afflicted, yet He did not open His mouth. Like a lamb led to the slaughter and like a sheep silent before her shearers, He did not open His mouth.
23Is 53:8 He was taken away because of oppression and judgment; and who considered His fate? For He was cut off from the land of the living; He was struck because of My people's rebellion.
23Is 53:9 They made His grave with the wicked, and with a rich man at His death, although He had done no violence and had not spoken deceitfully.
23Is 53:10 Yet the LORD was pleased to crush Him, and He made Him sick. When You make Him a restitution offering, He will see [His] seed, He will prolong His days, and the will of the LORD will succeed by His hand.
23Is 53:11 He will see [it] out of His anguish, and He will be satisfied with His knowledge. My righteous servant will justify many, and He will carry their iniquities.
23Is 53:12 Therefore I will give Him the many as a portion, and He will receive the mighty as spoil, because He submitted Himself to death, and was counted among the rebels; yet He bore the sin of many and interceded for the rebels.
23Is 54:1 "Rejoice, barren one, who did not give birth; burst into song and shout, you who have not been in labor! For the children of the forsaken one will be more than the children of the married woman," says the LORD.
23Is 54:2 "Enlarge the site of your tent, and let your tent curtains be stretched out; do not hold back; lengthen your ropes, and drive your pegs deep.
23Is 54:3 For you will spread out to the right and to the left, and your descendants will dispossess nations and inhabit the desolate cities.
23Is 54:4 "Do not be afraid, for you will not be put to shame; don't be humiliated, for you will not be disgraced. For you will forget the shame of your youth, and you will no longer remember the disgrace of your widowhood.
23Is 54:5 For your husband is your Maker-- His name is Yahweh of Hosts-- and the Holy One of Israel is your Redeemer; He is called the God of all the earth.
23Is 54:6 For the LORD has called you, like a wife deserted and wounded in spirit, a wife of one's youth when she is rejected," says your God.
23Is 54:7 "I deserted you for a brief moment, but I will take you back with great compassion.
23Is 54:8 In a surge of anger I hid My face from you for a moment, but I will have compassion on you with everlasting love," says the LORD your Redeemer.
23Is 54:9 "For this is like the days of Noah to Me: when I swore that the waters of Noah would never flood the earth again, so I have sworn that I will not be angry with you or rebuke you.
23Is 54:10 Though the mountains move and the hills shake, My love will not be removed from you and My covenant of peace will not be shaken," says your compassionate LORD.
23Is 54:11 "Poor [Jerusalem], storm-tossed, and not comforted, I will set your stones in black mortar, and lay your foundations in sapphires.
23Is 54:12 I will make your battlements of rubies, your gates of sparkling stones, and all your walls of precious stones.
23Is 54:13 Then all your children will be taught by the LORD, their prosperity will be great,
23Is 54:14 and you will be established on [a foundation of] righteousness. You will be far from oppression, you will certainly not be afraid; you will be far from terror, it will certainly not come near you.
23Is 54:15 If anyone attacks you, it is not from Me; whoever attacks you will fall before you.
23Is 54:16 Look, I have created the craftsman who blows on the charcoal fire and produces a weapon suitable for its task; and I have created the destroyer to work havoc.
23Is 54:17 No weapon formed against you will succeed, and you will refute any accusation raised against you in court. This is the heritage of the LORD's servants, and their righteousness is from Me." [This is] the LORD's declaration.
23Is 55:1 "Come, everyone who is thirsty, come to the waters; and you without money, come, buy, and eat! Come, buy wine and milk without money and without cost!
23Is 55:2 Why do you spend money on what is not food, and your wages on what does not satisfy? Listen carefully to Me, and eat what is good, and you will enjoy the choicest of foods.
23Is 55:3 Pay attention and come to Me; listen, so that you will live. I will make an everlasting covenant with you, the promises assured to David.
23Is 55:4 Since I have made him a witness to the peoples, a leader and commander for the peoples,
23Is 55:5 so you will summon a nation you do not know, and nations who do not know you will run to you. For the LORD your God, even the Holy One of Israel, has glorified you."
23Is 55:6 Seek the LORD while He may be found; call to Him while He is near.
23Is 55:7 Let the wicked one abandon his way, and the sinful one his thoughts; let him return to the LORD, so He may have compassion on him, and to our God, for He will freely forgive.
23Is 55:8 "For My thoughts are not your thoughts, and your ways are not My ways." [This is] the LORD's declaration.
23Is 55:9 "For as heaven is higher than earth, so My ways are higher than your ways, and My thoughts than your thoughts.
23Is 55:10 For just as rain and snow fall from heaven, and do not return there without saturating the earth, and making it germinate and sprout, and providing seed to sow and food to eat,
23Is 55:11 so My word that comes from My mouth will not return to Me empty, but it will accomplish what I please, and will prosper in what I send it [to do]."
23Is 55:12 You will indeed go out with joy and be peacefully guided; the mountains and the hills will break into singing before you, and all the trees of the field will clap [their] hands.
23Is 55:13 Instead of the thornbush, a cypress will come up, and instead of the brier, a myrtle will come up; it will make a name for the LORD as an everlasting sign that will not be destroyed.
23Is 56:1 This is what the LORD says: Preserve justice and do what is right, for My salvation is coming soon, and My righteousness will be revealed.
23Is 56:2 Happy is the man who does this, anyone who maintains this, who keeps the Sabbath without desecrating it, and keeps his hand from doing any evil.
23Is 56:3 No foreigner who has converted to the LORD should say, "The LORD will exclude me from His people"; and the eunuch should not say, "Look, I am a dried-up tree."
23Is 56:4 For the LORD says this: "For the eunuchs who keep My Sabbaths, and choose what pleases Me, and hold firmly to My covenant,
23Is 56:5 I will give them, in My house and within My walls, a memorial and a name better than sons and daughters. I will give each [of them] an everlasting name that will never be cut off.
23Is 56:6 And the foreigners who convert to the LORD, minister to Him, love the LORD's name, and are His servants, all who keep the Sabbath without desecrating it, and who hold firmly to My covenant--
23Is 56:7 I will bring them to My holy mountain and let them rejoice in My house of prayer. Their burnt offerings and sacrifices will be acceptable on My altar, for My house will be called a house of prayer for all nations."
23Is 56:8 [This is] the declaration of the Lord God, who gathers the dispersed of Israel: "I will gather to them still others besides those already gathered."
23Is 56:9 All you animals of the field and forest, come and eat!
23Is 56:10 Israel's watchmen are blind, all of them, they know nothing; all of them are mute dogs, they cannot bark; they dream, lie down, and love to sleep.
23Is 56:11 These dogs have fierce appetites; they never have enough. And they are shepherds who have no discernment; all of them turn to their own way, every last one for his own gain.
23Is 56:12 "Come, let me get [some] wine, let's guzzle [some] beer; and tomorrow will be like today, only far better!"
23Is 57:1 The righteous one perishes, and no one takes it to heart; faithful men are swept away, with no one realizing that the righteous one is swept away from the presence of evil.
23Is 57:2 He will enter into peace-- they will rest on their beds-- everyone who lives uprightly.
23Is 57:3 But come here, you sons of a sorceress, offspring of an adulterer and a prostitute!
23Is 57:4 Who is it you are mocking? Who is it you are opening your mouth and sticking out your tongue at? Isn't it you, you rebellious children, you race of liars,
23Is 57:5 who burn with lust among the oaks, under every flourishing tree, who slaughter children in the wadis below the clefts of the rocks?
23Is 57:6 Your portion is among the smooth [stones] of the wadi; indeed, they are your lot. You have even poured out a drink offering to them; you have offered a grain offering; should I be satisfied with these?
23Is 57:7 You have placed your bed on a high and lofty mountain; you also went up there to offer sacrifice.
23Is 57:8 You have set up your memorial behind the door and doorpost. For away from Me, you stripped, went up, and made your bed wide, and you have made a bargain for yourself with them. You have loved their bed; you have gazed on their genitals.
23Is 57:9 You went to the king with oil and multiplied your perfumes; you sent your envoys far away and sent [them] down even to Sheol.
23Is 57:10 You became weary on your many journeys, [but] you did not say, "I give up!" You found a renewal of your strength; therefore you did not grow weak.
23Is 57:11 Who was it you dreaded and feared, so that you lied and didn't remember Me or take it to heart? Have I not kept silent for such a long time and you do not fear Me?
23Is 57:12 I will expose your righteousness, and your works-- they will not profit you.
23Is 57:13 When you cry out, let your collection [of idols] deliver you! The wind will carry all of them off, a breath will take them away. But whoever takes refuge in Me will inherit the land and possess My holy mountain.
23Is 57:14 He said, "Build it up, build it up, prepare the way, remove [every] obstacle from My people's way."
23Is 57:15 For the High and Exalted One who lives forever, whose name is Holy says this: "I live in a high and holy place, and with the oppressed and lowly of spirit, to revive the spirit of the lowly and revive the heart of the oppressed.
23Is 57:16 For I will not accuse [you] forever, and I will not always be angry; for then the spirit would grow weak before Me, even the breath [of man], which I have made.
23Is 57:17 Because of his sinful greed I was angry, so I struck him; I was angry and hid; but he went on turning back to the desires of his heart.
23Is 57:18 I have seen his ways, but I will heal him; I will lead him and comfort him and his mourners,
23Is 57:19 creating words of praise." The LORD says, "Peace, peace to the one who is far or near, and I will heal him.
23Is 57:20 But the wicked are like the storm-tossed sea, for it cannot be still, and its waters churn up mire and muck.
23Is 57:21 There is no peace for the wicked," says my God.
23Is 58:1 "Cry out loudly, don't hold back! Raise your voice like a trumpet. Tell My people their transgression, and the house of Jacob their sins.
23Is 58:2 They seek Me day after day and delight to know My ways, like a nation that does what is right and does not abandon the justice of their God. They ask Me for righteous judgments; they delight in the nearness of God."
23Is 58:3 "Why have we fasted, but You have not seen? We have denied ourselves, but You haven't noticed!" "Look, you do as you please on the day of your fast, and oppress all your workers.
23Is 58:4 You fast [with] contention and strife to strike viciously with [your] fist. You cannot fast as [you do] today, [hoping] to make your voice heard on high.
23Is 58:5 Will the fast I choose be like this: A day for a person to deny himself, to bow his head like a reed, and to spread out sackcloth and ashes? Will you call this a fast and a day acceptable to the LORD?
23Is 58:6 Isn't the fast I choose: To break the chains of wickedness, to untie the ropes of the yoke, to set the oppressed free, and to tear off every yoke?
23Is 58:7 Is it not to share your bread with the hungry, to bring the poor and homeless into your house, to clothe the naked when you see him, and to not ignore your own flesh [and blood]?
23Is 58:8 Then your light will appear like the dawn, and your recovery will come quickly. Your righteousness will go before you, and the LORD's glory will be your rear guard.
23Is 58:9 At that time, when you call, the LORD will answer; when you cry out, He will say: Here I am. If you get rid of the yoke from those around you, the finger-pointing and malicious speaking,
23Is 58:10 and if you offer yourself to the hungry, and satisfy the afflicted one, then your light will shine in the darkness, and your night will be like noonday.
23Is 58:11 The LORD will always lead you, satisfy you in a parched land, and strengthen your bones. You will be like a watered garden and like a spring whose waters never run dry.
23Is 58:12 Some of you will rebuild the ancient ruins; you will restore the foundations laid long ago; you will be called the repairer of broken walls, the restorer of streets where people live.
23Is 58:13 "If you keep from desecrating the Sabbath, from doing whatever you want on My holy day; if you call the Sabbath a delight, and the holy [day] of the LORD honorable; if you honor it, not going your own ways, seeking your own pleasure, or talking too much;
23Is 58:14 then you will delight yourself in the LORD, and I will make you ride over the heights of the land, and let you enjoy the heritage of your father Jacob." For the mouth of the LORD has spoken.
23Is 59:1 Indeed, the LORD's hand is not too short to save, and His ear is not too deaf to hear.
23Is 59:2 But your iniquities have built barriers between you and your God, and your sins have made Him hide [His] face from you so that He does not listen.
23Is 59:3 For your hands are defiled with blood, and your fingers with iniquity; your lips have spoken lies, and you mutter injustice.
23Is 59:4 No one makes claims justly; no one pleads honestly. They trust in empty and worthless words; they conceive trouble and give birth to iniquity.
23Is 59:5 They hatch viper's eggs and weave spider's webs. Whoever eats their eggs will die; crack one open, and a viper is hatched.
23Is 59:6 Their webs cannot become clothing, and they cannot cover themselves with their works. Their works are sinful works, and violent acts are in their hands.
23Is 59:7 Their feet run after evil, and they rush to shed innocent blood. Their thoughts are sinful thoughts; ruin and wretchedness are in their paths.
23Is 59:8 They have not known the path of peace, and there is no justice in their ways. They have made their roads crooked; no one who walks on them will know peace.
23Is 59:9 Therefore justice is far from us, and righteousness does not reach us. We hope for light, but there is darkness; for brightness, but we live in the night.
23Is 59:10 We grope along a wall like the blind; we grope like those without eyes. We stumble at noon as though it were twilight; [we are] like the dead among those who are healthy.
23Is 59:11 We all growl like bears and moan like doves. We hope for justice, but there is none; for salvation, [but] it is far from us.
23Is 59:12 For our transgressions have multiplied before You, and our sins testify against us. For our transgressions are with us, and we know our iniquities:
23Is 59:13 transgression and deception against the LORD, turning away from following our God, speaking oppression and revolt, conceiving and uttering lying words from the heart.
23Is 59:14 Justice is turned back, and righteousness stands far off. For truth has stumbled in the public square, and honesty cannot enter.
23Is 59:15 Truth is missing, and whoever turns from evil is plundered. The LORD saw that there was no justice, and He was offended.
23Is 59:16 He saw that there was no man-- He was amazed that there was no one interceding; so His own arm brought salvation, and His own righteousness supported Him.
23Is 59:17 He put on righteousness like a breastplate, and a helmet of salvation on His head; He put on garments of vengeance for clothing, and He wrapped Himself in zeal as in a cloak.
23Is 59:18 Thus He will repay according to [their] deeds: fury to His enemies, retribution to His foes, and He will repay the coastlands.
23Is 59:19 They will fear the name of the LORD in the west, and His glory in the east; for He will come like a rushing stream driven by the wind of the LORD.
23Is 59:20 The Redeemer will come to Zion, and to those in Jacob who turn from transgression. [This is] the LORD's declaration.
23Is 59:21 "As for Me, this is My covenant with them," says the LORD: "My Spirit who is on you, and My words that I have put in your mouth, will not depart from your mouth, or from the mouth of your children, or from the mouth of your children's children, from now on and forever," says the LORD.
23Is 60:1 Arise, shine, for your light has come, and the glory of the LORD shines over you.
23Is 60:2 For look, darkness covers the earth, and total darkness the peoples; but the LORD will shine over you, and His glory will appear over you.
23Is 60:3 Nations will come to your light, and kings to the brightness of your radiance.
23Is 60:4 Raise your eyes and look around: they all gather and come to you; your sons will come from far away, and your daughters will be carried on the hip.
23Is 60:5 Then you will see and be radiant, and your heart will tremble and rejoice, because the riches of the sea will become yours, and the wealth of the nations will come to you.
23Is 60:6 Caravans of camels will cover your land-- young camels of Midian and Ephah-- all of them will come from Sheba. They will carry gold and frankincense and proclaim the praises of the LORD.
23Is 60:7 All the flocks of Kedar will be gathered to you; the rams of Nebaioth will serve you and go up on My altar as an acceptable [sacrifice]. I will glorify My beautiful house.
23Is 60:8 Who are these who fly like a cloud, like doves to their shelters?
23Is 60:9 Yes, the islands will wait for Me with the ships of Tarshish in the lead, to bring your children from far away, their silver and gold with them, for the honor of the LORD your God, the Holy One of Israel, who has glorified you.
23Is 60:10 Foreigners will build up your walls, and their kings will serve you. Although I struck you in My wrath, yet I will show mercy to you with My favor.
23Is 60:11 Your gates will always be open; they will never be shut day or night so that the wealth of the nations may be brought into you, with their kings being led [in procession].
23Is 60:12 For the nation and the kingdom that will not serve you will perish; those nations will be annihilated.
23Is 60:13 The glory of Lebanon will come to you-- [its] pine, fir, and cypress together-- to beautify the place of My sanctuary, and I will glorify My dwelling place.
23Is 60:14 The sons of your oppressors will come and bow down to you; all who reviled you will fall down on their faces at your feet. They will call you the City of the LORD, Zion of the Holy One of Israel.
23Is 60:15 Instead of your being deserted and hated, with no one passing through, I will make you an object of eternal pride, a joy from age to age.
23Is 60:16 You will nurse on the milk of nations, and nurse at the breast of kings; you will know that I, the LORD, am your Savior and Redeemer, the Mighty One of Jacob.
23Is 60:17 I will bring gold instead of bronze; I will bring silver instead of iron, bronze instead of wood, and iron instead of stones. I will appoint peace as your guard and righteousness as your ruler.
23Is 60:18 Violence will never again be heard of in your land; devastation and destruction [will be gone from] your borders. But you will name your walls salvation, and your gates praise.
23Is 60:19 The sun will no longer be your light by day, and the brightness of the moon will not shine on you; but the LORD will be your everlasting light, and your God will be your splendor.
23Is 60:20 Your sun will no longer set, and your moon will not fade; for the LORD will be your everlasting light, and the days of your sorrow will be over.
23Is 60:21 Then all your people will be righteous; they will possess the land forever; they are the branch I planted, the work of My hands, so that I may be glorified.
23Is 60:22 The least will become a thousand, the smallest a mighty nation. I am the LORD; I will accomplish it quickly in its time.
23Is 61:1 The Spirit of the Lord God is on Me, because the LORD has anointed Me to bring good news to the poor. He has sent Me to heal the brokenhearted, to proclaim liberty to the captives, and freedom to the prisoners;
23Is 61:2 to proclaim the year of the LORD's favor, and the day of our God's vengeance; to comfort all who mourn,
23Is 61:3 to provide for those who mourn in Zion; to give them a crown of beauty instead of ashes, festive oil instead of mourning, and splendid clothes instead of despair. And they will be called righteous trees, planted by the LORD, to glorify Him.
23Is 61:4 They will rebuild the ancient ruins; they will restore the former devastations; they will renew the ruined cities, the devastations of many generations.
23Is 61:5 Strangers will stand and feed your flocks, and foreigners will be your plowmen and vinedressers.
23Is 61:6 But you will be called the LORD's priests; they will speak of you as ministers of our God; you will eat the wealth of the nations, and you will boast in their riches.
23Is 61:7 Because your shame was double, and they cried out, "Disgrace is their portion," therefore, they will possess double in their land, and eternal joy will be theirs.
23Is 61:8 For I the LORD love justice; I hate robbery and injustice; I will faithfully reward them and make an everlasting covenant with them.
23Is 61:9 Their descendants will be known among the nations, and their posterity among the peoples. All who see them will recognize that they are a people the LORD has blessed.
23Is 61:10 I greatly rejoice in the LORD, I exult in my God; for He has clothed me with the garments of salvation and wrapped me in a robe of righteousness, as a bridegroom wears a turban and as a bride adorns herself with her jewels.
23Is 61:11 For as the earth brings forth its growth, and as a garden enables what is sown to spring up, so the Lord God will cause righteousness and praise to spring up before all the nations.
23Is 62:1 I will not keep silent because of Zion, and I will not keep still because of Jerusalem until her righteousness shines like a bright light, and her salvation like a flaming torch.
23Is 62:2 Nations will see your righteousness, and all kings your glory. You will be called by a new name that the LORD's mouth will announce.
23Is 62:3 You will be a glorious crown in the LORD's hand, and a royal diadem in the palm of your God.
23Is 62:4 You will no longer be called Deserted, and your land will not be called Desolate; instead, you will be called My Delight is in Her, and your land Married; for the LORD delights in you, and your land will be married.
23Is 62:5 For as a young man marries a virgin, so your sons will marry you; and as a bridegroom rejoices over [his] bride, so your God will rejoice over you.
23Is 62:6 Jerusalem, I have appointed watchmen on your walls; they will never be silent, day or night. You, who remind the LORD, no rest for you!
23Is 62:7 Do not give Him rest until He establishes and makes her Jerusalem the praise of the earth.
23Is 62:8 The LORD has sworn with His right hand and His strong arm: I will no longer give your grain to your enemies for food, and foreigners will not drink your new wine you have labored for.
23Is 62:9 For those who gather grain will eat it and praise the LORD, and those who harvest the grapes will drink [the wine] in My holy courts.
23Is 62:10 Go out, go out through the gates; prepare a way for the people! Build it up, build up the highway; clear away the stones! Raise a banner for the peoples.
23Is 62:11 Look, the LORD has proclaimed to the end of the earth, "Say to Daughter Zion: Look, your salvation is coming, His reward is with Him, and His recompense is before Him."
23Is 62:12 And they will be called the Holy People, the LORD's Redeemed; and you will be called Cared For, A City Not Deserted.
23Is 63:1 Who is this coming from Edom in crimson-stained garments from Bozrah-- this One who is splendid in His apparel, rising up proudly in His great might? It is I, proclaiming vindication, powerful to save.
23Is 63:2 Why is Your clothing red, and Your garments like one who treads a winepress?
23Is 63:3 I trampled the winepress alone, and no one from the nations was with Me. I trampled them in My anger and ground them underfoot in My fury; their blood spattered My garments, and all My clothes were stained.
23Is 63:4 For I planned the day of vengeance, and the year of My redemption came.
23Is 63:5 I looked, but there was no one to help, and I was amazed that no one assisted; so My arm accomplished victory for Me, and My wrath assisted Me.
23Is 63:6 I crushed nations in My anger; I made them drunk with My wrath and poured out their blood on the ground.
23Is 63:7 I will make known the LORD's faithful love [and] the LORD's praiseworthy acts, because of all the LORD has done for us-- even the many good things [He has done] for the house of Israel and has done for them based on His compassions and the abundance of His faithful love.
23Is 63:8 He said, "They are indeed My people, children who will not be disloyal," and He became their Savior.
23Is 63:9 In all their suffering, He suffered, and the Angel of His Presence saved them. He redeemed them because of His love and compassion; He lifted them up and carried them all the days of the past.
23Is 63:10 But they rebelled, and grieved His Holy Spirit. So He became their enemy [and] fought against them.
23Is 63:11 Then He remembered the days of the past, [the days] of Moses [and] his people. Where is He who brought them up out of the sea with the shepherds of His flock? Where is He who put His Holy Spirit among the flock?
23Is 63:12 He sent His glorious arm at Moses' right hand, divided the waters before them to obtain eternal fame for Himself,
23Is 63:13 and led them through the depths like a horse in the wilderness, so that they did not stumble.
23Is 63:14 Like cattle that go down into the valley, the Spirit of the LORD gave them rest. You led Your people this way to make a glorious name for Yourself.
23Is 63:15 Look down from heaven and see from Your lofty home-- holy and beautiful. Where is Your zeal and Your might? Your yearning and Your compassion are withheld from me.
23Is 63:16 Yet You are our Father, even though Abraham does not know us and Israel doesn't recognize us. You, LORD, are our Father; from ancient times, Your name is our Redeemer.
23Is 63:17 Why, LORD, do You make us stray from Your ways? You harden our hearts so we do not fear You. Return, because of Your servants, the tribes of Your heritage.
23Is 63:18 Your holy people had a possession for a little while, [but] our enemies have trampled down Your sanctuary.
23Is 63:19 We have become like those You never ruled over, like those not called by Your name.
23Is 64:1  If only You would tear the heavens open [and] come down, so that mountains would quake at Your presence--
23Is 64:2 as fire kindles the brushwood, and fire causes water to boil-- to make Your name known to Your enemies, so that nations will tremble at Your presence!
23Is 64:3 When You did awesome deeds that we did not expect, You came down, and the mountains quaked at Your presence.
23Is 64:4 From ancient times no one has heard, no one has listened, no eye has seen any God except You, who acts on behalf of the one who waits for Him.
23Is 64:5 You welcome the one who joyfully does what is right; they remember You in Your ways. But we have sinned, and You were angry; we will remain in Your ways and be saved.
23Is 64:6 All of us have become like something unclean, and all our righteous acts are like a polluted garment; all of us wither like a leaf, and our iniquities carry us away like the wind.
23Is 64:7 No one calls on Your name, striving to take hold of You. For You have hidden Your face from us and made us melt because ofour iniquity.
23Is 64:8 Yet LORD, You are our Father; we are the clay, and You are our potter; we all are the work of Your hands.
23Is 64:9 LORD, do not be terribly angry or remember [our] iniquity forever. Please look-- all of us are Your people!
23Is 64:10 Your holy cities have become a wilderness; Zion has become a wilderness, Jerusalem a desolation.
23Is 64:11 Our holy and beautiful temple, where our fathers praised You, has been burned with fire, and all that was dear to us lies in ruins.
23Is 64:12 LORD, after all this, will You restrain Yourself? Will You keep silent and afflict severely?
23Is 65:1 "I was sought by those who did not ask; I was found by those who did not seek Me. I said: Here I am, here I am, to a nation that was not called by My name.
23Is 65:2 I spread out My hands all day long to a rebellious people who walk in the wrong path, following their own thoughts.
23Is 65:3 These people continually provoke Me to My face, sacrificing in gardens, burning incense on bricks,
23Is 65:4 sitting among the graves, spending nights in secret places, eating swine's flesh, and putting polluted broth in their bowls.
23Is 65:5 They say: Keep to yourself, don't come near me, for I am too holy for you! These practices are smoke in My nostrils, a fire that burns all day long.
23Is 65:6 It is written before Me: I will not keep silent, but I will repay; I will repay them fully
23Is 65:7 [for] your iniquities and the iniquities of your fathers together," says the LORD. "Because they burned incense on the mountains and reproached Me on the hills, I will reward them fully for their former deeds."
23Is 65:8 The LORD says this: As the new wine is found in a bunch of grapes, and one says: Don't destroy it, for there's some good in it, so I will act because of My servants and not destroy them all.
23Is 65:9 I will produce descendants from Jacob, and heirs to My mountains from Judah; My chosen ones will possess it, and My servants will dwell there.
23Is 65:10 Sharon will be a pasture for flocks, and the Valley of Achor a place for cattle to lie down, for My people who have sought Me.
23Is 65:11 But you who abandon the LORD, who forget My holy mountain, who prepare a table for Fortune and fill bowls of mixed wine for Destiny,
23Is 65:12 I will destine you for the sword, and all of you will kneel down to be slaughtered, because I called and you did not answer, I spoke and you did not hear; you did what was evil in My sight and chose what I did not delight in.
23Is 65:13 Therefore, this is what the Lord God says: My servants will eat, but you will be hungry; My servants will drink, but you will be thirsty; My servants will rejoice, but you will be put to shame.
23Is 65:14 My servants will shout for joy from a glad heart, but you will cry out from an anguished heart, and you will lament out of a broken spirit.
23Is 65:15 You will leave your name behind as a curse for My chosen ones, and the Lord God will kill you; but He will give His servants another name.
23Is 65:16 Whoever is blessed in the land will be blessed by the God of truth, and whoever swears in the land will swear by the God of truth. For the former troubles will be forgotten and hidden from My sight.
23Is 65:17 "For I will create a new heaven and a new earth; the past events will not be remembered or come to mind.
23Is 65:18 Then be glad and rejoice forever in what I am creating; for I will create Jerusalem to be a joy, and its people to be a delight.
23Is 65:19 I will rejoice in Jerusalem and be glad in My people. The sound of weeping and crying will no longer be heard in her.
23Is 65:20 In her, a nursing infant will no longer live only a few days, or an old man not live out his days. Indeed, the youth will die at a hundred years, and the one who misses a hundred years will be cursed.
23Is 65:21 People will build houses and live [in them]; they will plant vineyards and eat their fruit.
23Is 65:22 They will not build and others live [in them]; they will not plant and others eat. For My people's lives will be like the lifetime of a tree. My chosen ones will fully enjoy the work of their hands.
23Is 65:23 They will not labor without success or bear children [destined] for disaster, for they will be a people blessed by the LORD along with their descendants.
23Is 65:24 Even before they call, I will answer; while they are still speaking, I will hear.
23Is 65:25 The wolf and the lamb will feed together, and the lion will eat straw like the ox, but the serpent's food will be dust! They will not do what is evil or destroy on My entire holy mountain," says the LORD.
23Is 66:1 This is what the LORD says: Heaven is My throne, and earth is My footstool. What house could you possibly build for Me? And what place could be My home?
23Is 66:2 My hand made all these things, and so they all came into being. [This is] the LORD's declaration. I will look favorably on this kind of person: one who is humble, submissive in spirit, and who trembles at My word.
23Is 66:3 One slaughters an ox, one kills a man; one sacrifices a lamb, one breaks a dog's neck; one offers a grain offering, one offers swine's blood; one offers incense, one praises an idol-- all these have chosen their ways and delight in their abominations.
23Is 66:4 So I will choose their punishment, and I will bring on them what they dread, because I called and no one answered; I spoke and they didn't hear; they did what is evil in My sight and chose what I didn't delight in.
23Is 66:5 You who tremble at His word, hear the word of the LORD: "Your brothers who hate and exclude you because of Me have said: Let the LORD be glorified, so that we can see your joy! But they will be put to shame."
23Is 66:6 A sound of uproar from the city! A voice from the temple-- the voice of the LORD, paying back His enemies what they deserve!
23Is 66:7 Before Zion was in labor, she gave birth; before she was in pain, she delivered a boy.
23Is 66:8 Who has heard of such a thing? Who has seen such things? Can a land be born in one day, or a nation be delivered in an instant? Yet as soon as Zion was in labor, she gave birth to her sons.
23Is 66:9 "Will I bring a baby to the point of birth and not deliver [it]?" says the LORD; "or will I who deliver, close [the womb]?" says your God.
23Is 66:10 Be glad for Jerusalem and rejoice over her, all who love her. Rejoice greatly with her, all who mourn over her--
23Is 66:11 so that you may nurse and be satisfied from her comforting breast and drink deeply and delight yourselves from her glorious breasts.
23Is 66:12 For this is what the LORD says: I will make peace flow to her like a river, and the wealth of nations like a flood; you will nurse and be carried on [her] hip, and bounced on [her] lap.
23Is 66:13 As a mother comforts her son, so I will comfort you, and you will be comforted in Jerusalem.
23Is 66:14 You will see, you will rejoice, and you will flourish like grass; then the LORD's power will be revealed to His servants, but He will show His wrath against His enemies.
23Is 66:15 Look, the LORD will come with fire-- His chariots are like the whirlwind-- to execute His anger with fury, and His rebuke with flames of fire.
23Is 66:16 For the LORD will execute judgment on all flesh with His fiery sword, and many will be slain by the LORD.
23Is 66:17 "Those who dedicate and purify themselves to [enter] the groves following their leader, eating meat from pigs, vermin, and rats, will perish together." [This is] the LORD's declaration.
23Is 66:18 "Knowing their works and their thoughts, I have come to gather all nations and languages; they will come and see My glory.
23Is 66:19 I will establish a sign among them, and I will send survivors from them to the nations-- to Tarshish, Put, Lud (who are archers), Tubal, Javan, and the islands far away-- who have not heard of My fame or seen My glory. And they will proclaim My glory among the nations.
23Is 66:20 They will bring all your brothers from all the nations as a gift to the LORD on horses and chariots, in litters, and on mules and camels, to My holy mountain Jerusalem, says the LORD, just as the Israelites bring an offering in a clean vessel to the house of the LORD.
23Is 66:21 I will also take some of them as priests and Levites," says the LORD.
23Is 66:22 "For just as the new heavens and the new earth, which I will make, will endure before Me"-- the LORD's declaration-- "so will your offspring and your name endure.
23Is 66:23 All mankind will come to worship Me, from one New Moon to another, and from one Sabbath to another," says the LORD.
23Is 66:24 "As they leave, they will see the dead bodies of the men who have rebelled against Me; for their maggots will never die, their fire will never go out, and they will be a horror to all mankind."
